al Journal of Dermatology37: 673-676.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Traor&eacute; A, Kou&eacute;ta F, Sanou I, Kam K, Dao L, et al. (1999) Les dermatoses courantes de l&rsquo;enfant dans un service de dermatologie en milieu tropical. Publications p&eacute;diatriques au Burkina Faso.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0151963818301960\">S.Semikenke, H.Ad&eacute;gbidi, J.Minani, G.Bisimwa (2018) Les dermatoses de l&rsquo;enfant en milieu hospitalier &agrave; Bukavu : aspects &eacute;pid&eacute;miologiques et cliniques. Annales de Dermatologie et de V&eacute;n&eacute;r&eacute;ologie 145 : 40.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Mulumba MP (1990) Le paludisme de l&rsquo;enfant &agrave; Kinshasa (Zaire) : Influence de saison, de l&rsquo;&acirc;ge, de l&rsquo;environnement et du standing familial. M&eacute;d. Trop 50: 53-54. </span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15304181\">Mishri L (2004) Spectrum of skin diseases in Yemen (Hajjah and adjacent region) in International Journal of Dermatology 43: 580-581.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1365-4632.2004.02140.x\">Shahram B, Shahram Z, and Abdoul-Ali M (2005) Report: Skin disease patterns in Hormozigan, Iran MD. International Journal of Dermatology 44: 641-645.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"http://europepmc.org/abstract/MED/21699521\">&nbsp;El-Khateeb EA, Imam AA, Mohammed A (2011) Pattern of skin diseases in Cairo, Egypt. International Journal of Dermatology 50: 844-853.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"http://www.panafrican-med-journal.com/content/article/29/162/full/\">Ayanlowo O, Puddicombe O, Gold-Olufadi S (2018) Pattern of skin diseasesamongstchildrenattending a dermatologyclinic in Lagos, Nigeria. Pan AfricanMedical Journal 29:162.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.em-consulte.com/en/article/770675\" target=\"_blank\">Tounkara TM,<strong> </strong>M.M. Soumah , M. Keita , B. Dian&eacute; , M. Bangoura, et al<strong>. </strong>(2012) Profil &eacute;pid&eacute;miologique et clinique des dermatoses infectieuses chez les enfants au service de dermatologie de l&rsquo;h&ocirc;pital national Donka. Annales de Dermatologie et de V&eacute;n&eacute;r&eacute;ologie 139 :137- 138.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19250398\" target=\"_blank\">Sardana K, Supriya M, Rashmi S, Vibhu M, Premanshu B et al. (2009) The spectrum of skin disease among Indianchildren. PediadricDermatology 26: 6 - 23.</a> </span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18705828\" target=\"_blank\">Tamer E, Mustafa N, Ilhan, Muhterem P, Nurdan L, et al. (2008). Prevalence of skin diseases among pediatric patients in Turkey. Journal of Dermatology 35: 413 - 418.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21738964\" target=\"_blank\">Flavia F, Luiz F, Camargo C. (2011) Prevalence of pediatric dermatoses in a universityhospital in southeastern Brazil. An Bras Dermato 86: 477 - 482.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9830292\" target=\"_blank\">Anand I, Gupta S. (1998) A profile of skin disorders in children in Saurashtra. J Indian Med Assoc 96 : 245 - 246.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11085661\" target=\"_blank\">Shibeshi, D. (2000) Pattern of Skin Disease at the Ethio-SwedishPediatricHospital, AddisAbeba, Ethiopia. PediatricDermatology 17: 357 - 359.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20825532\">El-Khateeb EA (2011) The spectrum of paediatric dermatoses in a universityhospital in Cairo, Egypt. J EurAcadDermatolVenereol 25: 666-672.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20456558\">Kramkimel N, Soussan V, Beauchet A, Duhamel A, Chevalier B, et al. (2010) High frequency, diversity and severity of skin diseases in a paediatric emergency department. J EurAcadDermatolVenereol 24: 1468-1475.</a></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">