ochemistry and molecular biology from East China Normal University, China. Since 2013, she served as an associate professor in Institute for Fetology at the First Hospital of Soochow University. DNA methylation/histone modifications, as well as epigenetic reprogramming are her areas of expertise. Her current research focused on the mechanisms in developmental programming of adult diseases, and the etiology of pregnancy complications, especially preeclampsia.</p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-11 19:06:12','2018-08-28 15:28:29',1),(135,17,20,'1531316426.jpg','Kourlaba Georgia','kurlaba@gmail.com','00000000000','Center for Clinical Epidemiology and Outcomes Research','Editorial board member','Greece','Center for Clinical Epidemiology and Outcomes Research','11','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Georgia Kourlaba is the Associate Scientific Director of the non-profit company &ldquo;Collaborative Center of Clinical Epidemiology and Outcomes Research (CLEO)&rdquo; focusing on control and prevention of healthcare associated infections. She earned her MSc in Biostatistics from the University of Athens and her Ph.D. in Nutritional Epidemiology-Biostatistics from Harokopio University, in Athens, Greece. She has been teaching for 10 years, a year-long Research Methods postgraduate course at the Medical School, University of Athens.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Prior to joining CLEO in 2012, Dr Kourlaba had served as biostatistics research fellow in the Dietetics and Nutritional Science Department of Harokopio University and at the National School of Public Health, both in Athens, gaining research experience in the design and statistical analysis of cross-sectional studies, clinical trials and economic evaluation studies. She has published over 100 papers in international scientific journals and has received a significant number of references to her work <strong>(h-index per googlescholar: 26).</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Her main experience and expertise include: economic evaluation of pharmaceuticals, devices, and diagnostics; analysis and modeling of medical care costs; design and analysis of market research, epidemiologic studies and clinical trials. Her analytic experience includes Markov modeling, regression analysis, mediation analysis, meta-analyses, and longitudinal modeling. She has extensive experience building economic models in Excel, and developing user-friendly model interfaces. Her analytical skills include good mastering of SAS, R, STATA, and SPSS.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-11 19:10:26','2018-07-25 20:41:42',1),(138,24,20,'1531327531.jpg','Monica V Butnariu','monicabutnariu@yahoo.com','','Professor, habilitated doctor, chemist, Chemistry & Biochemistry Discipline','Editorial board member','Romania','Banats University of Agricultural Sciences and Veterinary Medicine','03','<p>Monica Butnariu has completed her PhD in 2005 (Banat University, RO), since 2013 is<em> </em>habilitated doctor from Cluj Napoca University, RO. She is the professor of University of Agricultural Sciences and Veterinary Medicine of Banat &quot;<em>King Mihai I of Romania</em>&quot; in Timisoara, 300645, Romania (<em>Chemistry &amp; Biochemistry Discipline</em>). She has numerous articles published in the <a href=\"https://www.brainmap.ro/profile/monica-butnariu\">Science Citation Index (SCI) / International Scientific Indexing (ISI)</a> / <a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-7217-2010\">Web of Science Core Collection-Clarivate Analytics</a> that have been cited over 1200 times, and her publication H-index is 25 (<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/ProfileView.action?returnCode=ROUTER.Unauthorized&amp;Init=Yes&amp;SrcApp=CR&amp;queryString=KG0UuZjN5Wl8XyNMzOtL/fFQot2kP4VlgZg8IvV20fc=\">Citation Metrics</a>) and she has been serving as an editorial board member of reputed Journals and she has <a href=\"https://publons.com/author/313852/monica-butnariu#profile\">peer review activity</a>. So far, he has written several books and book chapters in different areas of chemistry (<a href=\"https://link.springer.com/search?query=Monica+Butnariu+Chapter\">such as</a>). In addition, he received the Romanian Academy Award for Chapter Chemical Composition of Vegetables and their Products in book <a href=\"https://link.springer.com/referenceworkentry/10.1007/978-3-642-41609-5_17-1\">Handbook of Food Chemistry</a>. It should be noted that currently is head of the <a href=\"http://www.conem.org/about-conem/groups/europe/\">Head&ndash;CONEM Romania Biotechnology and Environmental Sciences Group</a><strong> </strong>and also <a href=\"http://iapbhome.com/correspondent?profile=Romania-Monica-Butnariu\">National Correspondent of the International Association for Plant Biotechnology</a></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-11 22:15:31','2018-07-24 21:04:15',1),(139,24,20,'1531329788.jpg','Volodymyr Korolenko','v_korolenko@yahoo.com','380444841591','Department of Health','Editorial board member','Ukraine','Banats University of Agricultural Sciences and Veterinary Medicine','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Many in the healthcare, public administration and medical business community regard Dr. Volodymyr Korolenko as a leading authority and much-sought-after speaker on career development, marketing and entrepreneurship.&nbsp; His enthusiasm helps him to quickly connect with people and make an impact on them to take action.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Korolenko has over twenty years of experience in medical services including leadership positions at Dept. of Health, Kyiv Regional State Administration, at Executive apparatus of Kyiv Regional Council, and educational positions at the National O.O.Bogomolets Medical University.&nbsp; As the lecturer and executive at Ukrainian &quot;Znannya&quot; (Knowledge) Society he was honored with the 2008 Gold Medal. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He founded&nbsp; Club of Kyiv, a non-profit NGO in social services, which focuses on policy and development counseling for government bodies and other NGOs.&nbsp; He has been an editor, a member of editorial boards and reviewer for a number of scientific medical joutnals.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-11 22:53:07','2018-07-24 21:03:50',1),(140,23,20,'1531330493.jpg','Adekunle Sanyaolu','sanyakunle@hotmail.com','4032857540','Healthcare Consultant (Global Communicable Diseases)','Editorial board member','Canada','AMOOF consulting enterprise','04','<p>Dr Sanyaolu is a Medical Microbiologist with over 20 years of work experience in the area of public health, clinical and teaching duties. His expertise and research interest lies in the area of clinical and public health microbiology with specialized focus on communicable diseases (infectious / tropical diseases). Dr. Sanyaolu completed his Bachelor&rsquo;s (B.Sc Hons, 1989) degree, Master&rsquo;s (M.Sc., 1992) degree and Doctoral (PhD, 2000) from the University of Lagos, Lagos, Nigeria; Between the year 2005 and 2006,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Sanyaolu worked as a Postdoctoral Research Fellow in the area of Global Health Communicable Diseases at the College of Public Health, Department of Global Health, University of South Florida,Tampa Florida; also during this period, he worked as a Healthcare Specialist with the Veterans&rsquo; Administration (VA) healthcare centre in Tampa Florida. His career experience includes laboratory diagnosis for communicable diseases, teaching / training and research. His public health work experience includes epidemiological surveillance, intervention, outbreak investigation, infectious diseases prevention and control, as well as project coordination and management. He is a member of many professional associations in the UK, Canada and the US.</p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-11 23:04:53','2018-09-25 12:24:45',1),(141,26,20,'1531368211.jpg','Jose Antonio F. Ramires','jose.ramires@incor.usp.br','551126615443','Head Professor','Editorial board member','Brazil','University of So Paulo ','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Jose Antonio F. Ramires, MD, PhD has completed his PhD at the age of 28 years from University of S&atilde;o Paulo Medical School, Brasil and postdoctoral studies from the same University. He was the Scientific Director, Learn Director and General Director&nbsp; of the Instituto do Cora&ccedil;&atilde;o-INCOR (Heart Institute) of the University of S&atilde;o Paulo. Actually, he is Head Professor of Cardiology of the Instituto do Cora&ccedil;&atilde;o-INCOR and coordinator of medical graduate of the INCOR.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Ramires was President of the S&atilde;o Paulo State Cardiology Society, Brazilian Society of Cardiology and Brazilian Heart Foundation (FUNCOR) and Vice-President of the InterAmerican Cardiology Society. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">During five years (2005-2010) was President of the Professors and Researchers Evaluation Committee of the University of S&atilde;o Paulo. He has published more than 500 papers in reputed journals and has been serving as an editorial board member of repute.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-12 09:33:31','2018-07-30 20:47:27',1),(142,26,20,'1531414023.jpg','Samer Ellahham','ellahs@ccf.org','2164488250','DIRECTOR, PARAGON CARDIOVASCULAR FOUNDATION','Editorial board member','USA','Paragon Cardiovascular Foundation','01','',1,'2018-07-12 22:17:03','2018-07-30 20:46:54',1),(143,32,20,'1531414722.jpg','Evangelos M.Mazaris','evmazaris@yahoo.gr','442033121006','Department of Urology','Editorial board member','United Kingdom','St. Mary\'s and Charing Cross Hospital','03','<p>Evangelos M.Mazaris completed his urological training at the 2nd Department of Urology at the University of Athens Greece in 2009 and became accredited in Urology after successful exit exams. In the same year he also passed with excellent marks the Fellow of European Board of Urology (FEBU) exams.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the same year he took up a post as a Senior Fellow in Urology/Uro-oncology at the Lister Hospital in Stevenage UK for 2 years including training in robotic surgery. He was then promoted to the same hospital to a L. Consultant for 1 year. He subsequently took up a post of L. Consultant at Imperial College NHS Trust for 2 years working both at St. Mary&rsquo;s as well as Charing Cross hospitals in London. From April 2014 he was appointed as a Consultant at Hinchingbrooke Hospitalin Huntingdon Cambridgeshire creating with my colleagues a totally new Department of Urology in the hospital.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2005 he obtained an MSc in Surgical Science by Imperial College London in 2009 and he obtained an MD from the University of Athens with a thesis title &lsquo;use of NSAIDs for analgesia after radical retropubic prostatectomy&rsquo;.In 2010 he obtained a Ph.D. from Imperial College London with my thesis titled &lsquo;ethical issues in live donor kidney transplantation&rsquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evangelos M.Mazaris have published book chapters and articles in national and international journals. He has presented at national and international meetings. He was an editorial board member for several journals and he also reviews papers for journals. He was referenced in &lsquo;Who is who in medicine and healthcare&rsquo; during 2009-2012 and also in &lsquo;Who is who in the world&rsquo; in 2013.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Research Interests:</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>His research interest focuses is on stone disease, male and female LUTS, cancer diagnostics, laser prostatectomies and UTIs.</p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-12 22:28:42','2018-07-17 22:36:19',1),(144,32,20,'','Subhash Singla','subhashsingla2@gmail.com','09878055786','Department of Radio-diagnosis','Editorial board member','India','Christian medical college & Hospital','04','',1,'2018-07-12 22:35:11','2018-07-17 22:36:38',1),(145,23,20,'1531675352.jpg','Sanket Awate','sanket.awate@nih.gov','','Laboratory of Molecular Gerontology,National Institute on Aging','Editorial board member','USA','National Institute of Health','03','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Awate received his Master&rsquo;s in Biochemistry &amp; Molecular Biology from George Washington University in 2010. Her Master&rsquo;s Thesis focused on the transcriptional regulation of Estrogen Receptor &alpha; by BP1, transcription factor activated in breast cancer. He then decided to pursue his Ph.D. in the Department of Biochemistry &amp; Molecular Biology from Louisiana State University. During his Ph.D. he identified inhibitors of Tousled-like Kinase 1B that is overexpressed in Breast, ovarian and prostate cancers. He was awarded her Ph.D. in 2016 and then went on to join the Robert Brosh laboratory at NIH/NIA as a postdoctoral Fellow.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is currently studying the molecular functions and genetic roles of DNA helicases engaged in the replication stress response.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-15 22:52:32','2018-09-25 12:23:54',1),(146,30,20,'1531676186.jpg','Victor Manuel Vargas Hernandez','vvargashernandez@yahoo.com.mx','(55) 5747 7503','Direction of Research','Editorial board member','Mexico','Jurez Hospital of Mexico','03','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Victor Manuel Vargas Hernandez Participation as a tenured professor, associate or associate in different conferences, national and international meetings.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Professor of the course of biology of Human Reproduction, Medicine Internal, General Surgery, Oncology, and Gynecology and 