ecutive Committee of African and Middle East Federation of IADR</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">The first research prize in Prosthodontics from Society of Arab Dental Faculties (SARDF) 2010</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Fellowship of the International Academy for Dento-Facial Esthetics FIADFE/2012</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Fellowship of the International College of Dentists FICD/2015</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Fellowship of the Academy of Dentistry International FADI/2016</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Fellowship of the Pierre Fauchard Academy FPFA/2017</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Membership of the Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Glasgow (MFDSRCPS-Glasg)/2017</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Membership of the Royal College of Surgeons of Edinburgh (MFDSRCS-Ed)/2017</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Membership of Faculty of General Dental Practice; MFGDP(UK)/ 2017</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Membership of Royal College of Surgeons of England (MFDSRCS Eng) /2017&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is currently involved in teaching undergraduate and graduate students in all field of Prosthodontics in addition to involvement in advanced programs for MFDS Trainees, High specialty trainees and advanced clinical trainees in Prosthodontics&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He supervised several MSc students as a main and a co advisor and as an examiner for 27 theses in all disciplines of Prosthodontics with more than 49 publications in high impact international journals. In addition, he works as a reviewer for 41 International Peer reviewed Journals and on editorial board of 46 International Journals. He attended more than 39 local and international conferences and more than 24 workshops in disciplines of Implant dentistry, Prosthodontics, Cone Beam CT, Dental education, Quality assurance and health informatics.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He was a Member of the International advisory group formed by FDI for publishing the Dental Ethics Manual in 2007 and carried out its translation into Arabic Language to be available to all Arabic natives.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><u><strong>Research Interests:</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Standards of clinical and laboratory procedures for construction of fixed and removable prostheses</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Oral Infections related to removable prostheses</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Infection Control</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Esthetics Dentistry</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Implant Dentistry</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Restoration of Endodontically treated teeth</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Periodontics-Restorative Dentistry Interface</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Shortened Dental arch</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,'2018-07-15 23:23:51','2018-07-17 23:18:57',1),(149,15,20,'1531678644.jpg','Abu-Hussein Muhamad','abuhusseinmuhamad@gmail.com','','Department of Pediatric Dentistry','Editorial board member','Greece','University of Athens','08','',1,'2018-07-15 23:47:23','2018-07-15 23:47:23',1),(150,15,20,'1531839417.jpg','Adnan Catovic','catovic@fzg.hr','','Head of Polyclinic Dental Clinic University Hospital Center Zagreb','Editorial board member','Europe','University of Zagreb','03','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Adnan Catovic is a specialist and primarius in Prosthodontics. He is full Professor of Fixed Prosthodontics and Geriatric Dentistry at the School of Dentistry, University of Zagreb and Dental Clinic University Hospital Centre in Zagreb, Croatia. He is a regular member of the Croatian Academy of Medical Sciences, graduated from the School of Dental Medicine in Zagreb 1977. He was research assistant at the Department of Fixed Prosthodontics, Faculty of Dentistry in Zagreb, university lecturer and research associate in 1987. He was an Associate Professor and senior research associate in 1995. and Full Professor and scientific advisor in 1999, Head of the Department of Fixed Prosthodontics, Faculty of Dentistry, University of Zagrebu from 1999 to 2001. He was Head of the Department of Fixed Prosthodontics, School of Medicine, Study of Dental Medicine,University of Rijeka from 2001 to 2003. Now he is the Head of the Geriatric Dentistry at the School of Dental Medicine University of Zagreb and Head of the Polyclinic of Dental Clinic University Hospital Center Zagreb.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He was a lecturer at numerous scientific and professional conferences and has published over 150 scientific papers. He was a leader and principal investigator of the scientific project &rdquo;Teeth, materials and prosthetics appliances&nbsp; in adolescent and geriatric population&rdquo; author of two textbooks in Fixed prosthodontics and Geriatric dentistry and co author in textbook Geriatrics .He is a regular member of the Croatian Academy of Medical Sciences, editorial board Journal Medix, Croatian Society for Prosthetic Dentistry, Croatian Medical Association, European Prosthodontic Association (EPA) and the European College of Gerodontology (ECG). He is a member of several Editorial boards of the Journals in Dental Medicine.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research Interest:</strong></span></span></u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Fixed prosthodontics and Implantology, Biomechanics of teeth and prosthetic appliances, Dental care for Elderly , Ergonomics in Dentistry.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-17 20:26:56','2018-07-17 23:20:13',1),(151,16,20,'1531845309.jpg','Qiang Zhang','qiangz@med.umich.edu','(336) 970-3553','Department of Radiation Oncology','Editorial board member','USA','University of Michigan','02','<p>Dr. Zhang&rsquo;s research is focused on identifying novel molecular targets in pancreatic cancer that are important in the cellular response to radiation-induced DNA damage. He is involved with several translational therapeutic projects to optimize the use of agents targeting FBXW7, ATM and PARP1 in pancreatic cancer. More recently, Dr. Zhang has initiated new research focused on improving the efficacy of immune checkpoint therapies in pancreatic cancer by combining agents targeting the DNA damage response with radiation. Dr. Zhang also has extensive experience in mechanism-based studies of DNA double-strand break repair pathways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em></u><br />\r\nMajor areas of investigation:<br />\r\n1) Pancreatic Cancer<br />\r\n2) DNA Damage Response and Repair<br />\r\n3) Combination of immunotherapy and Radiotherapy<br />\r\n4) Radiation Therapy<br />\r\n5) E3 Ubiquitin Ligase</p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-17 22:05:09','2018-07-17 22:05:09',1),(152,21,20,'1531846083.jpg','Michael Olin','olin0012@umn.edu','612-616-3123','Department of Pediatrics','Editorial board member','USA','University of Minnesota','01','<p>Dr. Olin is an Assistant Professor in the Department of Pediatrics, Division of Hematology/Oncology. Dr. Olin graduated from the University of Minnesota, Duluth, in 1995 with a BS in biochemistry and a BA in chemistry. After graduating, he worked in industry for 5 years before returning to the U of M to complete his PhD in Veterinary Medicine (Infectious Disease) in 2005. From 2006-2008 Dr. Olin did a postdoctoral fellowship with Dr. Philip Peterson studying the effects of opioids on tuberculosis meningitis, and from 2008-2011 he did a second post doctoral fellowship with Dr. John Ohlfest in brain tumor immunotherapy. Dr. Olin joined the Department of Pediatrics Faculty as an Assistant Professor in 2011.</p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-17 22:17:07','2018-07-18 22:54:15',1),(153,32,20,'1531846845.jpg','Daben Dawam','bnd861@aol.com','','Department of Urology','Editorial board member','United Kingdom','Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dawam graduated from the University of Jos, Nigeria with BMBCH in 1985. He undertook Residency Training in Urological Surgery at Ahmadu Bello University Teaching Hospital Zaria,Nigeria gaining the Fellowship of the National Postgraduate Medical College of Nigeria in 1995. He took up appointment as Consultant Urological Surgeon and Lecturer at the Ahmadu Bello University Teaching Hospital and Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria respectively. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Mr Dawam moved to the UK in 1999 as a UICC Fellow to the Royal Marsden Hospital, London where he spent time working with Mr W.F. Hendry and Prof. C.R.J. Woodhouse undertaking some of the best practices in modern urological cancer diagnosis and treatment at a world renowned Cancer Centre. He was awarded the Fellowship of the Royal College of Surgeons of England FRCS(Urol) in 2010. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">This was later followed by Fellowships at the University Hospitals of Coventry and Warwickshire(UHCW) in the United Kingdom and famous Queen Elizabeth Hospital Birmingham all in the United Kingdom, between 2012 and 2013. To further incorporate some of the best practices in modern urological surgery, Mr Dawam also undertook Mini-Fellowships at Institute of Urology and Nephrology, Mansoura with Prof. Hassan Abou El-Enein ,and also with with Prof. Urs Studer at Inselspital, University of Berne, Switzerland as well as Mini Fellowships with Prof. Inderbir Gill at Keck Medicine of University of Southern California(USC), Los Angeles where he is a Visiting Physician. Mr Dawam joined Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust in 2014 as Consultant Urological Surgeon . </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">His research interests and sub-specialist practice are Pelvic Uro-oncology and Laparoscopy /Robotic Surgery.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-17 22:30:47','2018-07-17 22:36:02',1),(154,24,20,'1531847991.jpg','Hironobu Ihn','ihn-der@kumamoto-u.ac.jp','','Vice President, Faculty of Life Sciences','Editorial board member','Japan','Kumamoto University Hospital','01','<p>Prof. Hironobu Ihn was born in 1964 at Kobe, Japan and graduated from University of Tokyo in 1990. He became assistant professor, Department of Dermatology, Faculty of Medicine, University of Tokyo in 1990, and worked as the research fellow in Division of Rheumatology &amp; Immunology, Medical University of South Carolina, SC, USA between 1994 and 1997. He worked as the lecturer, Department of Dermatology, Faculty of Medicine between 2001 and 2005 and became the associate Professor, Department of Dermatology, Faculty of Medicine, University of Tokyo. He was elected as the professor &amp; Chairman, Department of Dermatology &amp; Plastic Surgery, Faculty Life Sciences, Kumamoto University in 2005 and became the Vice President, Kumamoto University Hospital in 2013.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He obtained Japanese Society of Connective Tissue Research Award in 2001, Japanese Society of Investigative Dermatology Award in 2005, and Japan Rheumatism Foundation Award in 2006.</p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-17 22:49:50','2018-07-17 22:49:50',1),(155,28,20,'1531848391.jpg','Akira Sugawara','akiras2i@med.tohoku.ac.jp','','Professor, Department of Molecular Endocrinology','Editorial board member','Japan','Tohoku University Graduate School of Medicine','05','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Professor Akira Sugawara belongs to the Department of Molecular Endocrinology, Tohoku University Graduate School of Medicine, Sendai, Japan. He graduated from Tohoku University School of Medicine on 1987 (M.D.), and got Ph.D. on 1991 from Tohoku University Graduate School of Medicine. He performed Postdoctoral Fellowship in William Chin&rsquo;s laboratory at the Women&rsquo;s Hospital/Harvard Medical School in Boston from 1991 to 1994. His major is general internal medicine, endocrinology and metabolism and hypertension and nephrology.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research interest:</strong></em>&nbsp;1) molecular biology of nuclear hormone receptors, 2) etiology of high blood pressure, 3) pathophysiology of diabetic nephropathy, 4) gene regulation of aldosterone synthase, and 5) epigenetics of hypertension and diabetes mellitus.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-17 22:56:31','2018-08-02 00:16:35',1),(156,15,20,'1531849067.jpeg','Giuseppina Lagana','giuseppinalagana@libero.it','(39) 0644232321','Department of Orthodontics','Editorial board member','Italy','University of Rome ','10','<p><u><strong><em>RESEARCH TOPICS</em></strong></u><strong><em>:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Malocclusions in growing subjects</li>\r\n	<li>Early treatment of dento-skeletal malocclusions</li>\r\n	<li>Epidemiology studies of oral conditions in Italian and Albanian population</li>\r\n	<li>Breathing disorders and malocclusions</li>\r\n	<li>Dental anomalies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,'2018-07-17 23:07:47','2018-07-17 23:21:50',1),(157,15,20,'1531849388.jpg','Riaud Xavier','xavier.riaud@wanadoo.fr','02.40.76.64.88','Associate professor of Dental Surgery','Editorial board member','France','National Academy of Dental Surgery','11','',1,'2018-07-17 23:13:08','2018-07-17 23:13:08',1),(158,15,20,'1531849670.jpg','Amer A. Taqa','amertaqa@hotmail.com','','College of Dentistry ','Editorial board member','Iraq','Dental Basic Science Mosul University','13','<p>Amer A. Taqa: Professor at Dental Basic Science, College dentistry, Mosul University, Iraq. Have PhD degree in Dental chemistry. He has published more 100 researches papers in national and international academic journals and authored 22 books. His research interests include dental chemistry, medical chemistry, and inorganic chemistry. He is editorial member in more than 140 international journals. He Nominated as a member of the organizing committees for a number of international &nbsp;and local conferences.</p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-17 23:17:50','2018-07-17 23:17:50',1),(159,35,20,'1531927373.png','Maia Akhalkatsi ','maia_akhalkatsi@iliauni.edu.ge','+995 99 193529 ','Head of the Department of Plant Genetic  Resources','Editorial board member','Georgia','Ilia State University','02','',1,'2018-07-18 20:52:52','2018-07-19 23:00:27',1),(160,28,20,'1531927819.jpg','May Ng','may.ng@nhs.net','','Consultant Paediatric Endocrinologistand Associate Medical Director ','Editorial board member','United Kingdom','Southport and Ormskirk NHS Trust ','08','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr NgisChair of the UK Association of Children&rsquo;s Diabetes Clinicians, Clinical GuidelinesOfficer for British Society of Paediatric Endocrinology and Diabetes and Training Advisor for Endocrinology and Diabetes College Specialty Advisory Committee for theRoyal College of Paediatrics and Child Health (RCPCH). Sheis an active researcherwith over 120 publications with60 peer reviewed research papers, including three Cochrane reviews and has presented at more than 100 scientific meetings. She serves on the editorial board for several international journals including as Editor-in-Chief and as Associate Editor and is a regular invited referee for many high impact journals. She has been an invited keynote speaker at many national and international meetings including Diabetes UK in 2018, Diabetes Ireland in 2017, Diabetes Professional Conference in 2016, National Network Forums and Royal College meetings.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><u>Research interest</u>: </strong>Diabetes, Thyroid Disorders, Adrenal insufficiency</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-18 21:00:19','2018-08-02 00:13:54',1),(161,28,20,'1531928100.jpg','Hamdy Ahmad Sliem','hamdy.sliem@yahoo.com','','Professor','Editorial board member','Egypt','Suez Canal University ','10','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Hamdy Ahmad Sliem, currently serving as full professor of internal medicine and endocrinology in the school of medicine, Suez Canal University. Received MD degree from the college of medicine in 1994. Have over three decades experience in the management of diabetes, endocrinal disorders and evaluation of health status of those patients with chronic complications. In the last decade, have over 50 scientific publications in peer reviewed national and international journals, given multiple poster and oral presentations at various national and international conferences. Most of the publications were in the areas endocrinal disorders, metabolic syndrome, obesity, prediabetes, and impact of diabetes on cardiovascular and immune systems. Editorial board member in about 60 peer review open access international journals. Referee and per reviewer in more than 40 medical journals, more than 140 articles were reviewed in the last 6 years. Supervised and judged several medical theses and shared in many national projects related to different health problems.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-18 21:05:00','2018-07-23 22:03:16',1),(162,21,20,'1531933979.jpg','Jose Maria Acostamadiedo','jacostam@uvm.edu',' (518) 562-7110','Hematology Oncology,Department of Medicine','Editorial board member','USA','Champlain Valley Physicians Hospital','02','',1,'2018-07-18 22:42:58','2018-07-18 22:54:31',1),(163,15,20,'1532017782.jpg','Vittorio Checchi','vchecchi@hotmail.com','','Department of Restorative Dentistry','Editorial board member','Italy','University of Bologna','13','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr Vittorio Checchi degreed from Dental School in 2006 with a thesis on two different types of bone graftin materials used in post extraction sockets. He finished his Phd in Biomedical technologies applied to dental sciences in 2010 with a thesis comparing short implants vs longer implants placed after bone augmentation, in posterior atrophic mandibles.in 2010<br />\r\nHe attended the Periodontology and Implantology Dept of The Medical School of Columbia University (New York City, NY) in 2009.<br />\r\nDr Checchi is Assistant Professor at the Dental School of the University of Trieste,Trieste (Italy).Since the beginning of 2016 he also became part of the Professors of the Master in Esthetic Restorative Dentistry at the Dental School of Bologna University, directed by<br />\r\nProf. Breschi.<br />\r\nDr Checchi wrote 54 scientific articles: 13 Italian language and 41 in English, with a total impact factor of 43.61 and an H-index of 10.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-19 21:59:42','2018-07-19 22:00:46',1),(164,28,20,'1532020434.jpg','Khue Vu Nguyen','kvn006@ucsd.edu','','Departments of Medicine and Pediatrics','Editorial board member','USA','University of California','01','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Khue Vu Nguyen (born in Ha Noi, Viet Nam) is currently Full Project Scientist in the Departments of Medicine and Pediatrics, University of California, San Diego, School of Medicine, San Diego, California, U.S.A. He has studied at University Louis Pasteur, Strasbourg, France: B.S. in Biochemistry, M.S. in Molecular Biology, Ph.D. in Macromolecular Physical Chemistry, Ph.D. in Physical Sciences (Doctorat d&rsquo;Etat es Sciences Physiques). </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He has worked as Scientist in different French and U.S. Research Institutions and Companies. He is author and co-author of numerous publications and holder of many patents. He is listed in Who&rsquo;s Who in the World, Who&rsquo;s Who in America, etc. He is member of different academic organizations such as American Society for Microbiology, American Chemical Society. He is invited reviewer of different scientific journals such as Molecular Genetics and Metabolism,<br />\r\nAGE: Journal of the American Aging Association. He is also editorial board member of different scientific journals such as International Journal of Medicine and Molecular Medicine, Open Journal of Endocrine and Metabolic Diseases. He is Scientist Reviewer for grant proposals of the Metabolic Disease Two (MB-2) of the Peer Review Medical Research Program (PRMRP) for the U.S. Department of Defense Congressionally Directed Medical Research Programs (CDMRP). Current research includes genetic diseases, neurodevelopmental and neurodegenerative disorders, and cancer.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-19 22:43:53','2018-07-19 22:43:53',1),(165,35,20,'1532021225.jpg','Alireza Heidari','scholar.researcher.scientist@gmail.com','','Director of the BioSpectroscopy Core Research ','Editorial board member','USA','California South University','01','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Prof. Dr. Alireza Heidari, Ph.D., D.Sc. is a Full Professor and Academic Tenure of Chemistry at California South University (CSU), Irvine, California, USA. He has got his Ph.D. and D.Sc. degrees from California South University (CSU), Irvine, California, USA. Furthermore, he has double postdocs in Project Management, Oncology, Human Cancer Tissues and Synchrotron Radiation from Monash University, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia and also in Nanochemistry and Modern Molecular Electronic&ndash;Structure Computations Theory from California South University (CSU), Irvine, California, USA.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">His research interests include Biophysical Chemistry, Biomolecular Spectroscopy, Quantum Chemistry, Nanochemistry, Modern Electronic Structure Computations, Theoretical Chemistry, Mathematical Chemistry, Computational Chemistry, Vibrational Spectroscopy, Molecular Modelling, Ab initio &amp; Density Functional Methods, Molecular Structure, Biochemistry, Molecular Simulation, Pharmaceutical Chemistry, Medicinal Chemistry, Oncology, Synchrotron Radiation, Synchrocyclotron Radiation, LASER, Anti&ndash;Cancer Nano Drugs, Nano Drugs Delivery, ATR&ndash;FTIR Spectroscopy, Raman Spectroscopy, Intelligent Molecules, Molecular Dynamics, Biosensors, Biomarkers, Molecular Diagnostics, Numerical Chemistry, Nucleic Acids, DNA/RNA Monitoring, DNA/RNA Hypermethylation &amp; Hypomethylation, Human Cancer Tissues, Human Cancer Cells, Tumors, Cancer Tissues, Cancer Cells, etc. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He has participated at more than three hundreds reputed international conferences, seminars, congresses, symposiums and forums around the world as yet. Also, he possesses many published articles in Science Citation Index (SCI)/International Scientific Indexing (ISI) Journals. It should be noted that he has visited many universities or scientific and academic research institutes in different countries such as United States, United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, Scotland, Ireland, Netherlands, Belgium, Denmark, Greece, Russia, Estonia, Ukraine, Turkey, France, Swiss, Germany, Sweden, Norway, Italy, Austria, Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland, South Africa, Egypt, Brazil, Spain, Portugal, Mexico, Japan, Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, Taiwan, Hong Kong, South Korea, China, India, Qatar, United Arab Emirates, etc. as research fellow, sabbatical and volunteer researcher or visitor and so on heretofore. He has a history of several years of teaching for college students and various disciplines and trends in different universities. Moreover, he has been a senior advisor in various industry and factories. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is expert in many computer programs and programming languages. Hitherto, he has authored more than twenty books and book chapters in different fields of Chemistry. Syne, he has been awarded more than nine hundreds reputed international awards, prizes, scholarships and honors. Heretofore, he has multiple editorial duties in many reputed international journals, books and publishers. Hitherward, he is a member of more than three hundreds reputed international academic&ndash;scientific&ndash;research institutes around the world. It should be noted that he is currently the President of American International Standards Institute (AISI), Irvine, California, USA and also Director of the BioSpectroscopy Core Research Laboratory at California South University (CSU), Irvine, California, USA.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-19 22:57:04','2018-07-19 23:04:03',1),(166,15,20,'1532110531.jpg','Charles P. Sia','charles.sia@hotmail.com','','Consultant in Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery & Implantology','Editorial board member','Philippines','University of the Visayas Philippines','14','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Sia is a graduate of both Dentistry and Medicine and holds the position as the Chairman of the Department of Oral &amp; Maxillofacial Surgery at Gullas Medical Center &ndash; University of the Visayas and a Consultant in Oral-Maxillofacial and Implant Surgery at St. Luke&rsquo;s Medical Center &ndash; Global City, University of Cebu Medical Center, Chong Hua Hospital Group and Cancer Center, and the Craniofacial Foundation of the Philippines. Currently, he holds the position as Vice President of the Philippine Association of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeons and is a Clinical Assistant Professor of the Department of Oral Surgery and Oral Medicine at Cebu Doctors&rsquo; University. He was appointed as the International Relations Officer for the Philippines of the Young Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon Group of Hong Kong and the editor-in-chief of the EMS Otolaryngology Journal; an honorary editorial board member of various journals in Otorhinolaryngology, Surgery, Dentistry &amp; Oral Health Journal, Oral Biology, Biomedical Research, and Integrated Medical and Clinical Case Reports.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Sia completed his dental degree at the Cebu Doctors&rsquo; University, medical degree at the University of the Visayas, Postgraduate Diploma in Oral Surgery, and Master&rsquo;s Degree in Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery at the University of Hong Kong. He was a recipient of the Clinical Fellowship grant by Arbeitsgemeinschaft fur Osteosynthesefragen (AO) Craniomaxillofacial Foundation at the Department of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery in Peking University School and Hospital of Stomatology. He is a Fellow of the International and Philippine Association of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeons, International Congress of Oral Implantology&rsquo;s, Philippine Academy of Head and Neck Surgery Inc., and International College of Continuing Dental Education.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Active member of the International College of Maxillofacial Surgery, International Academy of Oral Oncology, and International Cleft Lip and Palate Foundation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research interest includes Regenerative and Reconstruction techniques in Maxillofacial region, Bone Grafting, Biomaterials and Growth Factors, Orthognathic Surgery, Cleft Surgery, Pharmacology, and Quality of life in Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery patients.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-20 23:28:37','2018-08-15 10:33:32',1),(167,15,20,'1532110922.jpg','Jose Ricardo Kina','kinajr@hotmail.com','','Associate Professor','Editorial board member','Brazil','Universidade Estadual Paulista Jlio de Mesquita Filho','15','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Associate Professor at UNESP-Universidade Estadual Paulista J&uacute;lio de Mesquita Filho, Division of Periodontics, Department of Surgery and Integrated Clinic and Professor at UNDB Dom Bosco University Division of Periodontics S&atilde;o Luis MA. Graduated at Ara&ccedil;atuba Dental School-Universidade Estadual Paulista J&uacute;lio de Mesquita Filho (1981), master&#39;s at Periodontology from Universidade de S&atilde;o Paulo (1985) and Ph.d. at Periodontology from Universidade de S&atilde;o Paulo (1991), Postdoctoral research from Tokyo Medical and Dental University (1995) and Retired&nbsp;Associate Professor from Universidade Estadual Paulista J&uacute;lio de Mesquita Filho (1984-2017). Specialist in Periodontics, Endodontics, Dental Prosthesis and Operative Dentistry. Has experience in Odontology, acting on the following subjects: periodontology, operative dentistry, dental implant, oral rehabilitation, endodontics and laser.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-20 23:34:02','2018-07-20 23:52:02',1),(168,28,20,'1532114263.jpg',' Hooshang Lahooti','hooshang.lahooti@sydney.edu.au','','Principal Scientific Officer and Conjoint Lecturer','Editorial board member','Australia','Nepean Clinical School','05','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr Hooshang Lahooti is Principal Scientist and conjoint lecturer - Nepean Clinical School, University of Sydney - PhD in Molecular and Cellular Biology - Teaching Evidence-Based Medicine. Dr Lahooti primary research focus is on Molecular Genetics of Thyroid Eye Disease (Thyroid Ophthalmopathy) has published many articles on Autoimmune Thyroid Disorders and has developed a unique laboratory test which is found to be useful by ophthalmologists and endocrinologists to manage patients with various eye and thyroid disorders.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-21 00:47:42','2018-07-21 00:47:42',1),(169,35,20,'1532114683.jpg','Dario Stefanelli','dariostef@hotmail.com','+61 (0)417 124 831','Department of Economic Development, Jobs, Transport & Resources','Editorial board member','Australia','  Latrobe University','03','',1,'2018-07-21 00:54:42','2018-07-21 00:54:42',1),(170,35,20,'1532114997.jpg','Miklas Scholz','miklas.scholz@tvrl.lth.se','+44 (0)161 295 5921','Department of Building and Environmental Technology','Editorial board member','Sweden','LUND UNIVERSITY','04','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Miklas Scholz</strong>, cand ing, BEng (equiv), PgC, MSc, PhD, CWEM, CEnv, CSci, CEng, FHEA, FIEMA, FCIWEM, FICE, Fellow of IWA, is Prof. in Water Resources Engineering at Lund University, Sweden. He also holds the Chair in Civil Engineering at The University of Salford, UK. He is a Professor and the Head of the Civil Engineering Research Group in Salford. Moreover, Miklas is a Distinguished Professor at Johannesburg University. Prof. Scholz has shown individual excellence evidenced by world-leading publications, postgraduate supervision and research impact. He has published four books and 218 journal articles. Prof. Scholz has total citations of more than 4889 (above 3090 citations since 2013), resulting in an h-index of 35 and an i10-Index of 111 (19 June 2018).</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-21 00:59:56','2018-07-25 20:58:33',1),(171,35,20,'1532115585.png','Jin Seop Bak','jsbwvav21@kyonggi.ac.kr','+82 1031597789','Division of Bio-convergence','Editorial board member','South Korea','Kyonggi University','05','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Jin Seop Bak has a college degree in Yonsei Univ. (senior admissions), a PhD in Korea Univ. with top honors, and LittD/ScD/PhD in IBC (in King&#39;s College). He is/was in Faculty of Kyonggi Univ. and KAIST (as Project-Leader). He was appointed to the post of Secretary-General (in UCC), Professor, Director General (for Asia), and Adviser in IBC. He also worked as a researcher/scholar/judge especially in UC Berkeley (conditionally), MIT (conditionally), Korea Univ. (e.g., Institute of Life Science and Natural Resources), Seoul National Univ. (e.g., Center for Agricultural Biomaterials), KRIBB, IPET, and KIMST. In Korea Univ., Prof. Bak played a key role in teaching Physical Chemistry. He is a leading member of a large number of academies (as the recipient/nominate of numerous awards; e.g., BioMedLib&#39;s TOP 20 and B&amp;B Daniel I.C. Wang Award) and nonprofit/profit organizations (e.g., Mensa, IBA, MOIF, COEI, and WCOIM). His main area of investigation is Life/Natural/Applied Sciences. He has achieved many research publications , 2 patents, 14 grants and has made a big number of communications in scientific events. He is a reviewer of more than 55 international journals, and member of 29 editorial boards. He has been cited continuedly in Marquis Who&#39;s Who (with several awards) and IBC (with numerous awards).</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-21 01:09:45','2018-07-25 21:00:02',1),(172,35,20,'1532115841.jpg','Martin Svoboda','svobodama@vfu.cz','420 728 25 15 49','Ruminant and Swine Clinic','Editorial board member','Europe','University of Veterinary and Pharmaceutical Sciences','06','',1,'2018-07-21 01:14:01','2018-07-21 01:14:01',1),(173,35,20,'1532116161.jpg','Waleed Fouad Abobatta','wabobatta@yahoo.com','00201224296948','Agriculture Research Center','Editorial board member','Egypt','Horticulture Research Institute  Agriculture Research Center','07','<p style=\"margin-left:.25in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Abobatta working as a Dr at (Citrus research Department), Horticulture Research Institute, Agriculture Research Center, he&rsquo;s a member of Scientific Committee for Greenhouses Plantation (A R C) and a member of Scientific Team for National Campaign for Navel Orange improvement (HRI), Abobatta published more than 11 books and research papers. </span>Abobatta has been serving as an editorial board member <span style=\"color:black\">in many journals like </span>Acta Science Agriculture<span style=\"color:black\">,Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Science Publishing Group</span>,&nbsp;<span style=\"color:black\">International Journal of Research in Clinical Medicine and Pharmacy Practice.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:13.5pt; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dr. Abobatta has been identified as an influential speaker for seminar, symposium, workshop, training and classes. He&rsquo;s consultant of Nano application in the agricultural sector and Magnetizing treated water in agriculture in the Arabian region.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:13.5pt; text-align:justify\"><em><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Research Interest:</span></strong></span></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:13.5pt; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dr. Waleed Abobatta research interests are Nano application in the agricultural sector, application of hydrogel polymer in agriculture, Integrated Horticulture crops management, plant physiology, plant nutrition, Greenhouses Plantation, Jojoba production under marginal land conditions and the soilless culture of vegetables.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-21 01:19:21','2018-07-21 01:20:57',1),(174,35,20,'1532116530.jpg','Fatma Aykut Tonk','fatma.aykut@ege.edu.tr','',' Department of FieldCrops','Editorial board member','Turkey','Ege University','08','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Aykut Tonk is Associate Professor in the Department of Field Crops at the University of Ege. &nbsp;Dr. Aykut Tonk received her Ph.D in Plant Breeding and Genetic Sciences from Ege University in 2007, her M.S. in Plant Breeding and Genetic Sciences from Ege University in 2002 and her B.S. in the Department of Field Crops at the University of Ege in 1998. Dr. Aykut Tonk is editor board of Turkish Journal of Field Crops, <a href=\"https://www.google.com.tr/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=1&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0ahUKEwirtKCt7q7WAhVGYVAKHbJ-BLMQFggqMAA&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedomain.org%2Fjournal%2F32&amp;usg=AFQjCNHC4JMYjcaFVsVT-tmOh4GQkuL1Jw\">Annual Research &amp; Review in Biology</a>, Plant Cell Biotechnology and Molecular Biology.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Her research interests include <span style=\"color:black\">the development and breeding of new varieties in wheat, identification of plant genetic diversity in different plants, molecular markers, molecular mapping and QTL studies on disease and pest resistance in wheat. </span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-21 01:25:30','2018-07-21 01:25:30',1),(175,32,20,'1532117355.png','Nurullah Hamidi','Abcded@gmail.com','','Ankara Training and Research Hospital','Editorial board member','Turkey','Ankara Training and Research Hospital','05','',1,'2018-07-21 01:39:15','2018-07-21 01:39:15',1),(176,35,20,'1532185726.jpg','Teodor Rusu','rusuteodor23@yahoo.com','0040724719774','Department of Technical Sciences and Soil Sciences','Editorial board member','Europe','UNIVERSITY OF AGRICULTURAL SCIENCES  AND VETERINARY MEDICINE CLUJ-NAPOCA','09','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Prof. dr. Rusu Teodor from University of Agricultural Sciences and Veterinary Medicine Cluj-Napoca, Romania, teach Agrotechnics, Experimental Techniques and Rural Development. Director of the research center for Sustainable Agricultural Systems and Minimum Tillage Technologies (since 2011), has worked as a soil pedologist for the 3 years, and agrotechnics for the last 20 years, specializing in soil monitoring, soil tillage, soil quality, minimum tillage, no-tillage, sustainable agricultural technologies and climatic changes. PhD Supervisor on Agrotechnics (since 2009). Deputy Director of the Department of Technical and Soil Sciences (2009-present). Director, Office of Soil Survey and Agrochemical Cluj (2014-present). He was Vice-Dean of the Faculty of Agriculture (2008-2012), Master Program responsible Rural Development (2010-present) and judicial-technical expert in Agriculture specialization. Professional experience - through the publication of 25 books, courses and guidance published in national and international publishers; 315 scientific papers (from which 47 ISI) and consultancy; organizing symposia: soil compaction - processes and consequences (2007); soil tillage systems (ed. 5: 2008; ed. 6: 2011; ed. 7: 2013; ed. 8: 2015); ESSC Conference 2016. Hirsch factor: Web of Science 5; Scopus 6; Google Scholar 10.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#2f302b\">A</span>grotechnics, herbology and soil management; soil sciences &ndash; pedologic studies and land evaluation, pedoameliorations and soil erosion control studies; technique experimentally and analysis of variance; soil conservation systems for a sustainable agriculture, anti-erosion systems, minimum soil tillage, no-tillage, carbon sequestration; integrated control of weeds and correct use of herbicides; weed biology and ecology, weed assessment; crop rotation and differentiated agrotechnics; rural development and climatic changes<span style=\"color:#2f302b\">.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-21 20:38:46','2018-07-21 20:49:02',1),(177,35,20,'1532186280.jpg','Moraru Paula Ioana ','moraru_paulaioana@yahoo.com','0040741135593','Department of Technical Sciences and Soil sciences','Editorial board member','Bulgaria','UNIVERSITY OF AGRICULTURAL SCIENCES  AND VETERINARY MEDICINE CLUJ-NAPOCA','10','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#111111\">Dr. Engineer, Research assistant, Department of Soil Sciences, University of Agricultural Sciences and Veterinary Medicine Cluj-Napoca, Romania. Publication of 120 papers in BDI&amp;ISI journals and international symposiums, 28 of which as lead author. Specialized in soil tillage conservation and its effect on soil organic matter, water management and carbon sequestration.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#111111\">Research Interest:</span></span></strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#2f302b\">A</span>grotechnics, herbology and soil management; technique experimentally and analysis of variance; soil conservation systems for a sustainable agriculture, anti-erosion systems, minimum soil tillage, no-tillage, carbon sequestration; integrated control of weeds and correct use of herbicides; rural development and climatic changes<span style=\"color:#2f302b\">.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-21 20:47:59','2018-07-21 20:47:59',1),(178,28,20,'1532362751.jpg','Sangeeta Singg','Sangeeta.singg@angelo.edu','325-223-8606','Department of Psychology, Sociology','Editorial board member','USA','Angelo State University','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Sangeeta Singg, PhD is a licensed psychologist and a professor of psychology a<span style=\"color:black\">t the Angelo State University (ASU) where she started the graduate counseling psychology program and served as the Program Director for many years. She</span> is also a <span style=\"color:black\">certified Applied Clinical Nutritionist and a Purification and Weight Loss Coach. </span>&nbsp;Her publications are in the areas of health and counseling/clinical psychology. She is currently serving as the president of the Psychological Association of Greater West Texas (PAGWT).&nbsp; In November 2016, PAGWT&nbsp; recognized her with a prestigious award, &ldquo;Outstanding Leadership in Psychology Award.&rdquo; Serving o<span style=\"color:black\">n the Board of Directors of American Heart Association, Tom Green County Division for 32 years, four times as the Board President, she received recognition for her service and volunteerism for over 30 years and was named Go Red Ambassador in 2009. Dr. Singg was s</span>elected as a &ldquo;Top Psychologist in San Angelo, Texas&rdquo; by the International Association of HealthCare Professionals and listed in their publication, <em>Worldwide Leaders in Health Care</em>, 2016. Among several academic awards, three are ASU&rsquo;s Distinguished Faculty Achievement Award, ASU Faculty Excellence in Leadership/Service, Texas A&amp;M University-Commerce&rsquo;s Ambassador Award, and ASU 35-Years Service Award. Dr. Singg organized the first AIDS Awareness Program in West Texas in early 1980s and started the first support group for the AIDS patients, their families and friends. A group member and Dr. Singg founded the San Angelo AIDS Foundation which began serving a vast geographical area of West Texas.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research Interests:</strong></span></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Singg&rsquo;s research interests are diverse and interdisciplinary including post-traumatic stress disorder, depression, zoophilia, childhood sexual abuse, memory, cardiovascular disease, alternative methods of healing, grief, suicide, energy medicine, student personal responsibility, self-esteem, color preference and color therapy, and role of nutrition in physical and psychological wellness.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-23 21:49:11','2018-07-23 22:01:11',1),(179,28,20,'1532363174.jpg','Juei-Tang Cheng','jtcheng@mail.cjcu.edu.tw','','Chair Professor, Institute of Medical Research','Editorial board member','Taiwan, Province of China','Chang Jung Christian University','04','',1,'2018-07-23 21:56:13','2018-08-02 00:16:00',1),(180,28,20,'','Tatiana Mokhort','tat_mokh@mail.ru','','Depatment of Internal Medicine, Department of Endocrinology','Editorial board member','Russia',' Moscow Medical Institute','09','',1,'2018-07-23 21:59:59','2018-08-02 00:14:22',1),(181,31,20,'1532444959.jpg','Ronald Burke','rburke@schulich.yorku.ca','(416) 736-2100','Emeritus Professor of Organizational Studies and Senior Scholar','Editorial board member','Canada','Schulich School of Business York University','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">One of Canada&rsquo;s most prolific researchers, Professor Burke&rsquo;s work has focused on the relationship between the work environment and the individual&rsquo;s overall well being, and over the past forty years he has written articles for numerous academic and professional journals.&nbsp; In addition to his research and teaching activities, Professor Burke was the Founding Editor of the <u>Canadian Journal of Administrative Sciences</u>.&nbsp; Burke has served on the editorial board of two dozen journals and has reviewed manuscripts for a dozen more journals.&nbsp; He has served as a member of two grants committees for the Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council of Canada, as Director of the PhD program in the School of Business at York University, and as Associate Dean Research, with the Schulich &nbsp;School of Business at York University.&nbsp; He has participated in research conferences in North and South America, the UK, Europe, Asia and Australia.&nbsp; He is a Fellow of the Canadian Psychological Association.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Professor Burke previously held the Imperial Life Professorship in Organizational Behavior and was a Senior Research Fellow at the National Centre for Management Research and Development, &nbsp;Ivey School of Business Administration, The University of Western Ontario.&nbsp; As holder of this Professorship, he started the Women in Management Research Program at Ivey.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Professor Burke earned a BA from the University of Manitoba and an MA and a PhD, from the University of Michigan.&nbsp; After completing his PhD in 1966 Professor Burke taught for two years at the University of Minnesota, following which he joined the School of Business at York University in Toronto.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He has participated in over 300 management development programs as well as serving as a consultant on organizational effectiveness issues for private and public sector organizations.&nbsp; His views on management have also appeared in various media.&nbsp; An outstanding teacher, Professor Burke has been frequently nominated for MBA teaching awards, ranking first in 2001.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Burke has published over 500 journal articles and book chapters and presented over 500 papers at academic conferences around the world. He has also edited or co-edited55 &nbsp;books to date with McGraw-Hill, Kluwer, Blackwell, Routledge, the American Psychological Association, Sage, Edward Elgar, Cambridge University Press, Emerald, Gower &nbsp;and Elsevier. In addition, he serves as co-editor of the Gower Publishers series on the psychological and behavioral aspects&nbsp; of risk in organizations. &nbsp;Researchgate indicted that his work has received over 10,000 citations.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-24 20:39:19','2018-07-24 20:39:19',1),(182,25,20,'1532445893.jpg','Abdelaziz M Thabet','abdelazizt@hotmail.com','6472398092','President - Consultant Psychiatrist and Senior Researcher, President of the Child and Adolescent Section in Arab Federal Psychiatrists','Editorial board member','Canada','Gaza','04','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Professor Thabet is a Palestinian child and adolescent Psychiatrist, was educated in Palestine, Austria, and United Kingdom in child psychiatry. His main interest was in dealing with Palestinian children affected by First Intifada which was erupted in 1987. He was running the clinical setting in Gaza city and was seeing adults and children victims of trauma and political violence. Cases were varied from depression, psychosomatic problems, anxiety, PTSD in adults. Children were referred due problems such as fears, anxiety, bed wetting, acute stress disorder, PTSD, ADHD, and conversion disorder. In seeing such cases, Prof Thabet decided to study the impact of trauma on children in the Gaza Strip in 1993. On the last three decades professor Thabet had conducted very interesting research including the prevalence of mental health problems in Gaza and West Bank, coping strategies used by children and parents. He targeted different ages and preschool children were in the target group in which he carried out studies of the mental health of children in preschool age and their mothers. He also studied patients in different departments in the hospitals such as End Stage Renal Failure, Cancer patients both in children and adult departments.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">After a while he conducted evaluation of intervention studies including different intention programs such as writing therapy, school based intervention, psychoeducation, psychodrama. In the last years, he started to lock for risk and protective factors in children and adults victims of political violence, stress, and trauma. He had conducted studies to see the impact of trauma, stress on resilience and PTG of adolescents and adults. His research includes both qualitative and quantitative ways of data collection. Also, Prof Thabet had targeted marginalized population such as Labor, orphaned, children lost their fathers in war, children with special needs, children under dialysis.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Prof Thabet main interest is the impact of stress and trauma on children and adults and the coping as medication factor and resilience as the outcome.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-24 20:54:52','2018-07-24 20:54:52',1),(183,24,20,'1532446357.jpg','Khalid Al Aboud','amoa65@hotmail.com','','Consultant Dermatologist','Editorial board member','Saudi Arabia','King Faisal Hospital','04','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Khalid Al Aboud, holds Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery <strong>(MBBS)</strong> from King Abdulaziz University, Saudi Arabia.Recently he finished his fellowship in dermatopathology from Wake Forest University, Winston-Salem, North Carloina, USA.Khalid Al Aboud who is currently the head of public health department in King Faisal Hospital, Makkah, Saudi Arabia , has diverse medicals interests and has several publications in Sexually Transmitted Infections, dermatology , pathology and public health. In 2008 , he received Zakon prize from the Society of History of Dermatology.He Conducted national researches on several public health problems including leprosy, leishmania and skin cancers.He is on the Editorial and Advisory Boards of several peer-reviewed scientific journals. </span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-24 21:02:37','2018-07-24 21:02:37',1),(184,35,20,'1532446997.jpg','Zul Ariff Bin Abdul Latiff','zulariff@umk.edu.my','0192231584','Head of Department  Agriculture Science, Faculty of Agro Based Industry','Editorial board member','Malaysia','Universiti Malaysia Kelantan','11','',1,'2018-07-24 21:13:16','2018-07-24 21:13:16',1),(185,35,20,'1533319222.png','Abdalla A Satti','satisattisat@yahoo.com','','Department of Bio-pesticides and Bio-fertilizers','Editorial board member','Sudan','Natural Resources and Desertification Research Institute','12','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">A.A. Satti was graduated in the University of Gezira, and received his M.Sc. &amp; Ph.D. from Khartoum University, Sudan. He is a senior researcher of entomology and pest management at the Department of Bio-pesticides and Bio-fertilizers, Environment, Natural Resources and Desertification Research Institute (ENDRI), National Centre for Research (NCR). He became Assistant, Associate and Full Professor, 2004, 2009 and 2013, respectively. He was a head Dept., 2006&ndash;2013, then a director of ENDRI from 2016 up to date. Satti is the founder and editor-inchief of the &ldquo;Environment and Natural Resources International Journal-ENRIJ&rdquo;, and one of founders of &ldquo;Sudanese Pest Management Society-SPMS)&rdquo;- 2017, besides being member in some journals&rsquo; editorial boards and several professional societies and unions. He was managed to lead/participate in various research projects considering sustainable agriculture, published ?120 scientific papers in journals and conferences. Moreover, he contributes effectively in teaching, supervision, training and extension activities, and other community services via cooperation with relevant institutions, all add significantly to his career.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-24 21:18:48','2018-08-03 23:30:21',1),(186,15,20,'1532447903.jpg','Mehmet Kemal Tumer','Dr_kemaltumer@yahoo.com','7505- (+90) 5433199155','Department of Oral And Maxillofacial Surgery, Faculty Of Dentistry','Editorial board member','Turkey','Gaziosmanpasa University','16','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Mehmet Kemal TUMER received his DDs degree and graduated from Faculty of Dentistry, Ankara University (Turkey) in 2008. Dr. Tumer trained from 2009 to 2012 in Department of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery, Faculty of Dentistry, Gazi University, Ankara, Turkey; and received her specialization and PhD degree in OMFS in 2012. He has been working Gaziosmanpasa University as an Assistant Professor since 2013. Dr. Tumer has been head of department of Oral and maxillofacial Surgery, Faculty of Dentistry, Gaziosmanpasa University since 2016. He has been Dr. Tumer has been Vice Dean of Faculty of Dentistry, Gaziosmanpasa University since 2018. He is also a PhD student in the department of medical biology and genetics in the thesis stage.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Research interest:</span>&nbsp;</span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Animal science, aging, cell culture, molecular biology, PCR, Temporomandibular joint, salivary gland, oral cancer</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-24 21:28:23','2018-07-24 21:28:23',1),(187,15,20,'1532448318.jpg','Andrea Ballini','andrea.ballini@me.com','(+39)3492432155','Details: Department of Basic Medical Sciences, Neurosciences and Sense Organs, School of Medicine','Editorial board member','Italy','University of Bari ','17','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Doctor of Dental Surgery. Clinical and Research Investigator at Department of Basic Medical Sciences, Neurosciences and Sense Organs, School of Medicine - University of Bari ALDO MORO. Laboratory Head at Department of Dental Sciences and Surgery (2009-2012). Visiting Professor at &quot;City Unity College - Greece&quot; (and affiliated Institutions). Visiting Scientist at &quot;Tecnologica Research Institute&quot; in Crotone, Italy. Visiting Senior Clinical Lecturer at BPP University, Faculty of Dentistry, Birmingham-United Kingdom. Member of the &quot; World Academy of Growth Factors &amp; Stem Cells in Dentistry- WAGroFSCD&quot;.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Author of scientific papers and book chapters on National and International Journals (and Books) with Impact factor. Winner of &quot;Research Award&quot; from Medical and Dental Council of Bari (Italy) in year 2016. Winner of &ldquo;Sant&rsquo;Apollonia Award&rdquo; from ANDI (Italian Dental National Association) in year 2005 for the best clinical and scientific report in Dental Sciences.&nbsp; Invited reviewer, Lead Guest Editor,&nbsp; Past-Associate Editor and Editorial Board Member in International Journals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research Interests:</strong></em> Scientific research activity in Dentistry, Stem Cells, Sexual Transmitted Diseases, Medical Genetics, Clinical Biochemistry, Dermatology, Immunology, Microbiology, Public Health and Preventive Medicine, Maxillofacial Surgery, Biotechnology, Occupational Medicine, Sleep Medicine, Biochemistry and Dental Hygiene. Actually the research lines are focused on: stem cells from oral and extra-oral tissues, regenerative therapies in dentistry and maxillofacial surgery, biomimetic scaffolds, genetic disorders with and without oral and maxillofacial features, genetics of periodontal disease and its correlation with systemic diseases, genotoxicity, cytogenetic, biochemistry implant dentistry, orthodontics, and Laser Technology and Therapy. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><em>Keywords for research interests:</em></strong> <em>Dentistry, Stem Cells, Sexual Transmitted Diseases, Medical Genetics, Clinical Biochemistry, Dermatology, Immunology, Microbiology, Public Health and Preventive Medicine, Maxillofacial Surgery, Biotechnology, Occupational Medicine, Biochemistry and Dental Hygiene.</em></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-24 21:35:17','2018-07-24 21:35:53',1),(188,17,20,'1532448650.jpg','Kulanthayan KC Mani','kulan@upm.edu.my','','Executive Director Safe Kids Malaysia, Department of Community Health, Faculty of Medicine and Health Sciences','Editorial board member','Malaysia','University Putra Malaysia','12','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Kulanthayan KC Mani holds a Bachelor Degree in Resource Economics from Universiti Pertanian Malaysia, Master of Science Degree in Transportation Planning from Universiti Teknologi Malaysia, Doctoral degree in Transportation Engineering from Universiti Putra Malaysia in 2002 and a Diploma in Traffic Safety from Lund University in Sweden. He is an Associate Professor attached with the Department of Community Health. His main research area is on Traffic Safety and Children Safety. He heads Safe Kids Malaysia as its Executive Director since its inception in 2011and has been actively engaged in research and community engagement programs in promoting safety among children in the country. He works on preventing unintentional injuries mainly focussing on traffic, drowning, falls and burn injuries involving children.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-24 21:40:50','2018-07-24 21:40:50',1),(189,35,20,'1532707567.jpg','Alexander K Sayok','ksalexender@unimas.my','','Department of Biodiversity and Environmental Conservation','Editorial board member','Malaysia','Universiti Malaysia Sarawak','13','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Alexander K Sayok, a graduate in forestry (BS Forest management (1984) Louisiana State University, MS Watershed Management (1986)&nbsp; and Doctorate in Forest Hydrology and Soil Science (1991) Stephen F Austin State University, Texas).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Lecturing in Forestry at PNG University of Technology, Lae from 1992 to 1996 on subjects related to forest and agriculture production, management and conservation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Environmental Specialist at KTA Sdn Bhd (Consulting Engineers) from 1996 to 2002 ensuring all development projects especially on land development not just meeting state and national laws and regulation but must be environmental friendly </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">National Expert for the peat swamp forest project funded by United Nations Development Programme from 2002 to 2008.&nbsp; Main purpose is to understand more on the properties of peat swamp for sustainable use and integrated management </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research Fellow/Associate Professor at Institute of Biodiversity and Environmental Conservation, Universiti Malaysia Sarawak since September 2008 lecturing and doing researches as well as consultancies on biodiversity and environmental conservation and enhancement</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He had worked with communities while lecturing in Papua New Guinea and communities in Tinjar-Baram area, Sarawak when he served &nbsp;with UNDP. He continues to work with the communities while serving in UNIMAS. In UNIMAS, he lectures and undertake researches on plants and the environment including Water Resources Engineering. He also had led a project related to dissolved organic carbon in peat land areas in Selangor. Presently he is documenting resources in five&nbsp; community forests including plants in Sarawak towards effort for conservation and sustainable use, and traditional knowledge on food plants diet and health relationship of Bau District community, as well as active ingredients in selected medicinal plants in Singai Area, Kuching.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Had also been engaged in several hydrology-related consultancies since joining UNIMAS. Among them are as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In 2009, he was involved as a forester for the feasibility studies on the proposed Baram Dam by SEB. </span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In 2010, he led the team for Environment Sensitivity Index of the coastline of Sarawak and Western Sabah commissioned by Petronas and other oil companies. </span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">During September to December 2012, he was engaged as Peat Swamp Expert cum Team Leader for the midterm review on ASEAN Peatland Forest Project funded by the UNDP via International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD) based in Rome, Italy.&nbsp; </span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In 2015, he led two water/flood-related consulting projects entitled &ldquo;Rapid assessment of floods in peat swamp areas of Rajang delta&rdquo; under Wetlands International and &ldquo;Ecosystem-based adaptations to sea level rises in Sarawak River basin&rdquo; under NAHRIM.&nbsp; </span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In 2016, he led the team in drafting the Batang Ai Reservoir Management Plan commissioned by MNRE through NAHRIM.&nbsp; In 2017, he was engaged as the desktop evaluator for Agusan Marsh Mindanao, The Philippines, for nomination as the World Heritage Site. </span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In 2018, he was assigned as hydrologist for the Taman Perpaduan di Taman Budaya (aka Reservoir Park) Kuching renovation under DBKU through EMS Progress Sdn Bhd.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is a committee member for the Lakes and Reservoirs Malaysia,&nbsp; Academic Research on Oil Palm Sustainability (ARPOS), and a member of the Malaysian Palm Oil Certification Council Dispute Resolution Committee (DRC). He is a regular editor/reviewer of articles sent to Journal of Geography and Regional Planning, and reviewed some articles for Journal of Land Use as well as Journal of Environmental management</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-27 21:36:06','2018-07-27 21:36:06',1),(190,15,20,'1532708277.jpg','Douglas L. Risk','majorrisk@hotmail.com','(240) 682-1019','Department of General Dentistry','Editorial board member','USA','Fusion Dental','001','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dr Risk entered active duty through the Military Indoctrination of Medical Services Officers (MIMSO) Program at Sheppard AFB, TX in 1987 after graduating from Georgetown University School of Dentistry. As a direct accession dental officer, he had a variety of clinical and administrative duties and was accepted into the two-year general dentistry residency at Lackland AFB. After graduating the residency in 1997, Col Risk became the only dentist to successfully challenge the certifying board in Infection Control and Epidemiology in 1998 and is a Diplomate of the Federal Services Board of General Dentistry and the American Board of General Dentistry. He has been the Chief of Dental Services at Kunsan AB, Korea; RAF Croughton, UK; and Mountain Home AFB, ID. Col Risk also served as Dental Squadron Commander at Bolling AFB and Offutt AFB where he was also Deputy Group Commander for the 579<sup>th</sup> Medical Group and the 55th Medical Group. Col Risk served on the Air Force Surgeon General&rsquo;s Staff from 2005-2008, responsible for directly supporting the Dental Corp Director and for coordinating all Senior Leader Assignments for the Air Force Medical Service.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">In November 2003, Colonel Risk deployed to the 379th Air Expeditionary Medical Group, Southwest Asia, in support of OPERATION IRAQI FREEDOM and OPERATION ENDURING FREEDOM where he was individually responsible for the dental health of the Air Force&rsquo;s largest Air Expeditionary Wing including over 6000 coalition personnel.&nbsp; Col Risk also deployed with OPERATION NEW HORIZONS in support of nation building efforts in Central America in 2013.&nbsp;&nbsp; Col Risk is a Fellow of the International College of Dentists, served as the Military Consultant to the Air Force Surgeon General for Dental Materials, Devices and Investigations and interim Infection Prevention and Patient Safety Consultant.&nbsp; He was appointed as an Associate Professor of Comprehensive Dentistry for the Uniformed Services University of the Health Sciences.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dr Risk retired from Active Duty in November 2017.&nbsp; After retirement, Dr Risk joined Fusion Dental, an affiliate of American Dental Partners, Inc., where he entered private practice and provided preparation activities for accreditation by the Accreditation Association for Ambulatory Health Care (AAAHC).&nbsp; His current duties include quality assurance, regulatory compliance, risk management and accreditation preparation.&nbsp; Col Risk currently serves on the Executive Board of Directors for the Organization for Safety, Asepsis, and Prevention (OSAP) and on the Standards Committee for Dental Products for the American Dental Association (ADA).&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-27 21:47:56','2018-07-27 21:54:53',1),(191,28,20,'1532709095.jpg','Patricia Myriam Vuguin','pv2267@columbia.edu','','Associate Professor of Pediatrics ','Editorial board member','USA','Columbia University Medical ','03','<p style=\"margin-right:4.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Patricia Myriam Vuguin currently and associate professor at &nbsp;Columbia University Medical .<span style=\"color:black\">I have trained as Pediatric Endocrinologist with a record of achievement in both the clinical and the laboratory arenas.&nbsp; My Curriculum Vitae indicates my lifelong devotion to scientific and medical knowledge. I finished a Masters of Science Training Program in Clinical Research, a NIH-funded program offered by the Department of Epidemiology and Biostatistics at Albert Einstein College of Medicine. I also rounded out my education with a strong basic science program.&nbsp; I have almost 20 years&rsquo; experience researching the developmental origins of health and disease, diabetes and novel biochemical mechanisms by which glucagon affect pancreatic islet cell differentiation and maturation. I am currently the director of the Pediatric Thyroid Center and the Pediatric endocrine fellowship program at Columbia University. </span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-27 22:01:35','2018-08-02 00:15:41',1),(192,28,20,'1532709501.jpg','Emin Turkay Korgun','korgun@akdeniz.edu.tr','','Professor Doctor at the Department of Histology and Embryology','Editorial board member','Turkey','Akdeniz University','10','',1,'2018-07-27 22:08:20','2018-07-27 22:08:20',1),(193,28,20,'1533232507.jpg','Emmanuel Ifeanyi Obeagu','emmanuelobeagu@yahoo.com','','Department of University Health Services','Editorial board member','Nigeria','Michael Okpara University of Agriculture','11','',1,'2018-07-27 22:16:00','2018-08-02 23:25:06',1),(194,28,20,'1532710203.jpg','Valeria Calcaterra','v.calcaterra@smatteo.pv.it','00390382502930','Department of Internal Medicine','Editorial board member','Italy','University of Pavia','12','',1,'2018-07-27 22:20:03','2018-07-27 22:20:03',1),(195,26,20,'1532963756.jpg','Abyt Ibraimov ','ibraimov_abyt@mail.ru','','Head of Laboratory of Human Genetics','Editorial board member','Russia','National Center of Cardiology and Internal Medicine','03','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Abyt Ibraimov is a genetic researcher and get Grants from International Science Foundation, 1993. He is a member of Kyrgyz Parliament, 1990. He is a member of New York Academy of Sciences, Kyrghyz National Academy of Sciences, International Association Human Biologists.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-30 20:45:56','2018-07-30 20:45:56',1),(196,29,20,'1532964920.jpg','YanPing Yu','ypyu@pitt.edu','','Associate Professor of Pathology','Editorial board member','USA','University of Pittsburgh','01','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><u>Research interests</u></strong> focus on the cancer genome and epigenome abnormalities and in our studies we used the methods of genetics, molecular biology, tumor-cell biology, genome editing and animal models. For years we have analyzed hundreds of cancer specimens for the alterations of gene expressions and genome copy number variations (CNVs) and methylations in prostate cancers. We examined the correlations of abnormalities identified with the clinical aggression of cancers and evaluated the clinical diagnostic and therapeutic value of the promising targets in cancers. Currently, we are characterizing fusion genes identified in our transcriptome sequencing studies of human malignancies, and we envision these fusions as the transcriptional products of genome rearrangements, a driving gene event in cancer development and progression.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-30 21:05:19','2018-07-30 21:05:19',1),(197,28,20,'1532965649.jpg','Parijat De','p.de@nhs.net','01212491425','Consultant & Clinical Lead in Diabetes & Endocrinology','Editorial board member','United Kingdom','Sandwell & West Birmingham NHS Trust','06','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr Parijat De is a Consultant Physician in Diabetes, Endocrinology, and Lipid Metabolism at City Hospital (Sandwell &amp; West Birmingham NHS Trust), Birmingham.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He started as a Consultant Physician in January 2003 having trained as a Specialist Registrar in Wales. He has done his MD Medicine from India.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He has a wide interest and expertise in all aspects of Diabetes, especially in the field of Metabolic Medicine and Diabetes Renal disease. His special interest in Diabetes is Metabolic Syndrome as well as the growing problem of obesity including new oral and injectable therapies for weight loss. He has published widely in his field and persues an active research interest. He has published numerous papers in peer reviewed journals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He has set up a regular nurse-led diabetic renal review clinic and is involved in research and projects involving diabetic nephropathy and renal disease. He has also set up community based diabetes clinics in Birmingham, which are amongst the first in the country. He has received national acclaim for the Diabetes in Community Extension (DiCE) work.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He has an active interest in all aspects of Endocrinology and has regular out-patient clinics as well as managing in-hospital referrals. His special interest is in the adrenal gland, endocrine hypertension, Thyroid and Vitamin D deficiency.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is involved in both undergraduate and postgraduate MRCP teaching and is an MRCP examiner and host. He has previously been the trust Clinical Governance Lead, College Tutor and is currently the Clinical Lead. He has set up local protocols and guidelines in most aspects of metabolic medicine including emergencies in diabetes as well as endocrinology.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-07-30 21:17:28','2018-07-30 21:18:13',1),(198,28,20,'1532966203.jpg','Nikolaos Papanas','papanasnikos@yahoo.gr','','Diabetes mellitus Diabetic complications Diabetic foot Diabetic neuropathy Medical writing Vascular disease Metabolic syndrome in OSAS and obesity','Editorial board member','Greece','University of Thrace Greece','14','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Nikolaos Papanas is Professor in Internal Medicine-Diabetes Mellitus at Democritus University of Thrace, Greece. He has been specialized in diabetes and its complications in the Diabetes Center and the Diabetic Foot Clinic at King&rsquo;s College Hospital, London, UK, as well as in the German Diabetes Center at the Heinrich Heine University, D&uuml;sseldorf, Germany. He has established an ongoing collaboration with the neuropathy study group of the German Diabetes Center in D&uuml;sseldorf. He has published <strong>more than 270 papers</strong> in peer-reviewed journals<strong>.</strong> He serves in the editorial board of more than 70 international journals. He has also participated with numerous presentations in Greek and European medical congresses and repeatedly served as invited reviewer in medical journals. He has served in the Executive Committee of the Hellenic Society for Angiology. He is currently a member in the Executive Committee of the Study Group on Diabetes and Nervous System of the German Diabetes Association (DDG). He is also Vice President of the Greek Society for the Study of the Diabetic Foot. He has served as Secretary General and, until very recently, as President of the Hellenic Diabetes Association. He is now the President of the ethics and administrative committee of the Hellenic Diabetes Association. He is also Vice President of the Diabetic Foot Study Group (DFSG, www.dfsg.org) of the European Association for the Study of Diabetes (EASD). He has recently become Visiting Professor in the German Diabetes Center, D&uuml;sseldorf. Moreover, he is an honorary member of the Cypriot Diabetes Association and the Hungarian Diabetes Association.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><em><strong>Research Interest</strong></em></u><em><strong>:</strong></em></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Diabetes mellitus</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Diabetic complications</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Diabetic foot</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Diabetic neuropathy</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Medical writing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Vascular disease</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Metabolic syndrome in OSAS and obesity</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,'2018-07-30 21:26:42','2018-07-30 21:27:17',1),(199,28,20,'1532966518.jpg','Teresa Arora','teresaarora8@gmail.com','971544 497 305','Assistant Professor ','Editorial board member','United Arab Emirates','Zayed University','15','',1,'2018-07-30 21:31:58','2018-07-30 21:31:58',1),(200,35,20,'1532966901.jpg','Shady El-Ghaish','shady2002nabil@yahoo.com','','Department of Dairy Science, Faculty of Agriculture','Editorial board member','Egypt','Kafrelsheikh University','14','',1,'2018-07-30 21:38:20','2018-07-30 21:38:20',1),(201,35,20,'1532967120.jpg','Ahmed Abd El-Aziz Kheder','ahmedkheder@hotmail.com','201003392108','Department of Virus and Phytoplasma Plant Pathology Research Institute','Editorial board member','Egypt','Agricultural Research Centre (ARC)','15','',1,'2018-07-30 21:42:00','2018-08-01 21:24:21',1),(202,15,20,'1533115641.jpg','Mohammad Hosein Kalantar Motamedi','Motamedical@yahoo.com','','Professor, Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon','Editorial board member','Iran','Azad University of Medical Sciences','19','',1,'2018-08-01 14:57:20','2018-08-01 14:57:20',1),(203,15,20,'1533116152.jpg','Nagy Abdul Samee','nagyabdulsamee@gmail.com','201022065499','Professor and Head of Dental Biomaterials, Faculty of Dentistry','Editorial board member','Egypt','Modern University for Technology & Information ','20','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Bachelor Degree of Dental Sciences from Faculty of Dentistry, Cairo University 1975, Master Degree in Prosthodontics from Faculty of Dentistry, Alexandria University, December 1980, and PhD in Dental Biomaterials has been finished at faculty of dentistry, Alexandria University 1985.Worked as demonstrator 5/7/1976 &ndash; 21/4/1981, Assistant lecturer 22/4/1981 &ndash; 16/9/1985, Lecturer 17/9/1985- 29/12/1991, and Assistant professor 30/12/1991 &ndash; 6/7/1994 at Dental Biomaterials Department, Faculty of Dentistry, Mansura University.<br />\r\nWorked as consultant Prosthodontics, Dental Center, King Fahad Hospital, Al-Madinah Al Menawarah, Kingdom of Saudia Arabia 1988 &ndash;2000.Worked as Assistant Professor, Dental Biomaterials, College of Oral and Dental Medicine, Misr University for Science &amp; Technology (MUST), Egypt 2000 &ndash;2004. At the same university i became a full professor &amp; head of Dental Biomaterials, 12/9/2004 &ndash; 1/6/2014. I worked as a Vice Dean of Graduate Studies and Researches, in this college, 2/6/2014 till 31/1/2016.<br />\r\n<em><strong>Currently:</strong></em> <strong>Consultant Prosthodontics</strong>, Professor and Head of Dental Biomaterials, Faculty of Dentistry, Modern University for Technology &amp; Information (MTI), Egypt 1/9/2016 till now.<br />\r\n&nbsp;An editor in many international dental journals, a speaker at many national and international dental conferences, and published seventeen researches in international dental journals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em> Removable and Fixed prosthodontics, Implant dentistry, Dental Biomaterials, and Laser applications in dentistry.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 15:05:52','2018-08-01 15:05:52',1),(204,26,20,'1533117314.jpg','Shehab Mahmoud Abd El-Kader','profshehab@LIVE.COM','','Professor,Department of Cardio-Pulmonary Disorders and Geriatrics, Faculty of Physical Therapy','Editorial board member','Egypt','Cairo University','04','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><sub>Prof. Shehab Mahmoud Abd El-kader, PT, MPT, PhD in physical therapy for cardiopulmonary, metabolic, women health, and geriatrics, Faculty of Physical Therapy, Cairo University, Egypt, since 2000 . Recent research interests include the areas of Cardiothoracic Surgery, Respiratory Disorders, Metabolic Disorders&nbsp;, women health, caring for older people, cardiopulmonary disorders, geriatrics, hepatology and wound care. Prof. Shehab is interested in teaching Physical therapy for patients with respiratory disorders, geriatrics, hepatology and metabolic disorders. In addition, he has published several original researches in refereed pioneer journals, published ten online textbooks with LAMBERT Academic Publishing in Germany that are available in Amazon and participated in many international conferences all over the world. Prof. Shehab is a designer and reviewer for several teaching curriculum for bachelor and master degrees in physical therapy for many universities in the middle east. Also he is a reviewer for many medical and scientific journals in addition to be a supervisor and referee for several post-graduate scientific thesis, he is an editorial board member for many international Journals. Finally, Prof. Shehab has a long history in teaching for students in the bachelor, master and doctorate degrees in physical therapy.</sub></span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 15:25:13','2018-08-01 15:26:43',1),(205,27,20,'1533117825.png','Andrzej Prystupa','aprystup@wp.pl','480815327717','Department of Internal Medicine','Editorial board member','Poland','Medical University of Lublin','13','',1,'2018-08-01 15:33:45','2018-08-01 15:33:45',1),(206,35,20,'1533118192.png','Carmen Georgeta Nicolae ','carmennicolae19@yahoo.com','+4021.318.25.61','Associate Professor PhD','Editorial board member','Romania','University of Agronomic Sciences and Veterinary Medicine of Bucharest','16','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Carmen Georgeta NICOLAE is Associate Professor at the Faculty of Animal Products Engineering and Administration, University of Agronomic Sciences and Veterinary Medicine of Bucharest, Romania. She is PhD and PhD Coordinator in animal science field. Area of expertise refers to aquaculture and fishery, animal husbandry, food products processing, quality of food products, public health, environmental sustainability, management, organization of specific activities of research and the livestock production. The experience in his field of expertise is reflected in the publication of 11 books or chapter in book, over 200 scientific articles in representative journals and conferences, 2 patents and 20 research projects. She is member of the editorial staff and reviewer of scientific journals and national and international events such as International Conference &ldquo;Agriculture for life, life for agriculture&rdquo;; &nbsp;International Virtual Conference on&nbsp; Advanced Research in Scientific Areas (ARSA 2016), Scientific Papers. Series D. Animal Science Journal; Prudent Journals; BioPublisher; Science Domain International Journals; Science Publishing Group Journals; Uttar Pradesh Journal of Zoology.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 15:39:52','2018-08-03 23:29:15',1),(207,35,20,'1533118659.jpg','Christopher Teh Boon Sung','christeh@yahoo.com','+603-89474858','Dept. Land Management, Fac. of Agriculture','Editorial board member','Malaysia','Universiti Putra Malaysia','17','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Christopher Teh Boon Sung has a Ph.D. in Agriculture from The University of Reading, UK. His field of specialties are in soil and water conservation and crop modeling. He is attached to the Department of Land Management, Faculty of Agriculture, Universiti Putra Malaysia since 2001. He has numerous publications: 5 books, 7 book chapters, 41 journal articles, and nearly 100 proceedings. He is active in promoting urban gardening and has written several newspaper articles and conducted several workshops in urban gardening. He has also won several teaching awards for teaching excellence from his university.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 15:47:39','2018-08-01 15:47:39',1),(208,35,20,'1533119163.jpg','M. Cuneyt Bagdatli','cuneytbagdatli@gmail.com','','Asst. Prof. Dr','Editorial board member','Turkey','Nevsehir Haci Bektas Veli University','18','<p>M. Cuneyt Bagdatli&nbsp;is working in Nevsehir Haci Bektas Veli University Faculty of Engineering and Architecture, Department of Biosystem Engineering in Turkey since 2014.<strong> </strong>He completed Ph.D. level in Biosystem Engineering area of Nam?k Kemal University and M.S. Level in Sel&ccedil;uk University, Department of Agricultural Structures and Irrigation in Turkey. He worked as a research assistant in Nam?k Kemal University, Faculty of Agriculture, Department of Biosystem Engineering (2008-2013). He served as project head and researcher in 18 projects supported by Universities. He is having 70 articles in Journals and Syposium, Conference on Irrigation, Hdrology, Climate Change, Hydrology, Watershed Management, Water quality, Remote sensing and GIS mapping, The system management in automatic irrigation, fertilization, pesticide and greenhouse. Heavy metal pollution in water and soil.</p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 15:56:02','2018-08-02 23:38:56',1),(209,28,20,'','Jianping Liu','liujpnfm@163.com','','Chief Doctor/Professor','Editorial board member','China','The Second Affiliated Hospital to Nanchang University','16','',1,'2018-08-01 16:08:11','2018-08-01 16:08:11',1),(210,28,20,'1533232413.png','Alexander E. Berezin','dr_berezin@mail.ru','+3806061006','Professor Chief of Cardiology Unit of Internal Medicine','Editorial board member','Ukraine','State Medical University','17','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Alexander E. Berezin received the MD degree from State Medical University, Zaporozhye, Ukraine, in 1992. PhD degree in field of Heart Failure was earned in State Medical University, Zaporozhye, Ukraine in 1994. He is currently Professor of Medicine, Chief of Cardiology Unit of Internal Medicine Department at State Medical University, Zaporozhye, Ukraine. He became a Member (M) the Ukrainian Cardiology Association in 1997; M of the Ukrainian Heart Failure Association in 2000; M of Heart Failure Association of the ESC in 2004; M of European Acute Cardiovascular Care Association in 2010; M of W.G. on Atherosclerosis and Vascular Biology of the ESC in 2010; M of European Association of Percutaneous Cardiovascular Interventions in 2012; M of European Association for Cardiovascular Prevention and Rehabilitation in 2012, M of W.G. on Hypertension &amp; the Heart of the ESC in 2012. From 2002 to 2012, he was Associate Professor at the Internal Medicine Department at State Medical University, Ukraine. His research interest includes the fundamental study of biological markers of cardiovascular diseases, the implementation of visualization procedures and percutaneous cardiovascular interventions, the development of cardiovascular prevention and rehabilitation, especially in the field affected heart failure and coronary artery disease, as well as regenerative medicine. Based on this research and fellowship training he has received several awards and honors, such as: Award of The Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine (2002), Honor of The Ukrainian Cardiology Association (2004). His previous publications are: 1. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA. Circulating osteopontin as a marker of early coronary vascular calcification in type two diabetes mellitus patients with known asymptomatic coronary artery disease. Atherosclerosis. 2013; 229: 475-481. 2. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA. Analysis of Various Subsets of Circulating Mononuclear Cells in Asymptomatic Coronary Artery Disease. J. Clin. Med. 2013, 2, 32-44. 3. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA. Bone-Related Circulating Proteins as Early Predictors of Coronary Atherosclerosis in Asymptomatic Patients with Known Coronary Artery Disease. Advanced Studies in Medical Sciences. 2013; 1 (4): 157 &ndash; 172 4. Berezin AE, Samura TA. Prognostic value of biological markers in myocardial infarction patients. Asian Cardiovascular and Thoracic Annals; 2013, 21(2): 142 &ndash; 150. 5. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA. Serum uric acid as a marker of coronary calcification in patients with asymptomatic coronary artery disease with preserved left ventricular pump function. Cardiology Research and Practice. 2013, Article ID 129369, 7 pages, http://dx.doi.org/10.1155/2013/129369. 6. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA, Samura T.A., Martovitskaya Yu.V. Association between Circulating Galectin-3 and Proangiogenic Mononuclear Progenitor Cells in Chronic Heart Failure Patients. JCvD. &ndash; 2014 [in press] 7. Berezin AE, Lisovaya OA. C-reactive protein in arterial hypertension after stroke. Asian Cardiovascular and Thoracic Annals; 2013 [in press]. October 29, 2013, doi: 10.1177/0218492313501163 8. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA, Samura T.A., Martovitskaya Yu.V. Circulating Endothelial-Derived Apoptotic Microparticles in the Patients with Ischemic Symptomatic Chronic Heart Failure: Relevance of Pro-Inflammatory Activation and Outcomes. Int Cardiovasc Res J.2014;8(3): [before print] 9. Berezin AE, Lisovaya OA. Predictive Value of Circulating Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor-1 in Arterial Hypertension Patients. Intern Med S. 2014; 11: 2-10. 10. Berezin AE. The Concept of Cell Therapy in Advanced Heart Failure: New Reality, Hope or Hype. Journal of Cardiology and Therapy. 2014; 1(3): 52-57. He is current Editor-in-Chief of Biological Markers and Guided Therapy. He is serving as an editorial member of several reputed journals like Ukranian Medical J, J Cardiology and Therapy (since 2013), Case Reports in Internal Medicine and expert Reviewers for journals like J Genetic Disorders and Genetic Reports; Obesity; Eur. J Clinical Investigations; J Food Science and Engineering; Case Reports in Internal Medicine; Diabetes, Metabolic Syndrome and Obesity: Targets and Therapy; British Journal of Medicine and Medical Research; Biomarkers in Medicine; Pediatrics &amp; Therapeutics; Journal of Vascular Medicine &amp; Surgery; Journal of Pain &amp; Relief; Cardiology and Angiology: An International Journal; Journal of Multiple Sclerosis; Journal of Clinical Case Reports; Journal of Haematology &amp; Thromboembolic Diseases, Acta Biochimica et Biophysica Sinica; Journal of Gerontology &amp; Geriatrics Research; Cloning &amp; Transgenesis.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Coronary artery disease, Heart Failure, Atherosclerosis Hypertension, Prognosis, Biological Markers, Comorbidities, Metabolic disorders, Visualization procedures, Cardiovascular Prevention and Rehabilitation, and Vascular Biology</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 16:13:35','2018-08-15 09:43:32',1),(211,28,20,'1533232597.jpg','Majid  Alabbood','dr_majid79@yahoo.com','','Specialist Endocrinologist','Editorial board member','Iran','AlZahraa Medical College','18','',1,'2018-08-01 16:18:15','2018-08-02 23:26:37',1),(212,15,20,'1533138701.jpg','Dr.Mohamed Elarbi','mselarbi@hotmail.com','+218913163322','Professor and Senior Consultant Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon','Editorial board member','Libya','Sbea Neursurgery Center University Hospital','21','',1,'2018-08-01 21:21:41','2018-08-02 23:48:18',1),(213,35,20,'1533146590.jpg',' Antar El-Banna','antar.elbana@agr.kfs.edu.eg','+2 01061157294','Department of Genetics, Faculty of Agriculture','Editorial board member','Egypt','Kafrelsheikh University','19','<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research interests:</span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Improvement resistant and/or tolerant of plants for biotic and abiotic stresses using Tissue genetic engineering technologies</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Gene function analysis using Next generation sequencing and gene silencing approaches.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Molecular genetics, genetic diversity and phylogenetic analysis.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Molecular characterization and exploitation of rhizosphere microorganisms for crop yield improvement.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research experience:</span></strong></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">1- Extensive scientific and technical knowledge of genetics/genomics, Proteomics, transcriptomics,plant biotechnology, and molecular biology.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">2- Outstanding communication skills: verbal, written and presentation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">3- Excellent negotiation and rhetorical skills with demonstrated ability to influence others and work towards consensus.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">4- A good potential and cooperative behavior with the working team members</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">5-Well conversant with computer applications like Microsoft Word, Word Perfect, Slide Write and PowerPoint, Internet Skills, Blast search analysis.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 23:33:10','2018-08-01 23:46:56',1),(214,35,20,'1533147308.png','Idress Attitalla','idressattitalla2004@yahoo.com','','Botany Department (Head of Department of Microbiology)','Editorial board member','Libya','University of Omar Al-Mukhtar','20','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Idress Hamad Attitalla, (Professor, 2015) has completed his PhD at the age of 31 years from Uppsala University (Sweden) and postdoctoral studies from USM University Sains Malaysia. He is the director of Research and Study at Agriculture Research Center (ARC) up to 2014, and Scientific Consultant, Libya and director of departments of microbiology at (Omar Al-Mukhtar University, Al-Bayda, Libya&Ugrave;?up to now). He published more than 80 papers in reputed journals and serving as an editorial board member of repute, and 1 book in Arabic about Algae and 1 translated book about proteomic.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 23:42:37','2018-08-01 23:45:08',1),(215,35,20,'1533147940.png','Entessar Al Jbawi','dr.entessara@gcsar.gov.sy','00-963-988-699884','Head of Sugar Beet Department,Co editor in chief in Syrian Journal of Agricultural Research (SJAR)','Editorial board member','Syrian Arab Republic','General Commission for Scientific Agricultural Research','21','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Publications: </strong></em>Publications: <span style=\"color:#00b050\">15 </span>International papers, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">37 </span>Regional and local papers, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">11 </span>articles, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">3 </span>booklets, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">12 </span>scientific reports, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">14 </span>national conferences, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">1 </span>book, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">12 </span>Master students, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">4 </span>Ph. D students, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">3 </span>international and national projects, <span style=\"color:#00b050\">2 </span>international work shops and <span style=\"color:#00b050\">4 </span>international training courses. <span style=\"color:#00b050\">8 </span>international conferences.Editorial board member in <span style=\"color:#00b050\">7 </span>international journals</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Achievements:</strong></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Reproduction sugar beet seeds locally for the first time in Syria (2017).</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">New planting date of sugar beet crop in Syria for the Northern and Eastern area in Al Raqqa and Der Al Zur governorates (Summer time, 15th July to 15th August). 2013.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Recommendation of 14, and 22 monogerm and multigerm sugar beet varieties to be grown in largescale in autumn time, also 25 monogerm and 25 multigerm sugar beet varieties to be grown in largescale in winter time, in Syria.</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Reviewed more than 50 international manuscripts in different international refereed journals.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,'2018-08-01 23:55:40','2018-08-02 00:01:29',1),(216,35,20,'1533148500.jpg','Bed Mani Dahal','bedmani@ku.edu.np','+977 9851216191','Associate Professor, Department of Environmental Science and Engineering','Editorial board member','Nepal','Kathmandu University','22','',1,'2018-08-02 00:05:00','2018-08-02 00:05:00',1),(217,28,20,'1533148916.jpg','Kevin Peter Shotliff','Kevin.Shotliff@chelwest.nhs.uk','','Department of Diabetes and Endocrinology Chelsea and Westminster Hospital; Honorary Senior Lecturer','Editorial board member','United Kingdom','Imperial College London','07','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Having undertaken a General Medical Registrar rotation in South West Thames I studied for my Master Degree at the Hammersmith Hospital prior to joining the South West Thames Diabetes and Endocrinology Senior Registrar Rotation. In June 1998 I was appointed Consultant Physician with an interest in Diabetes and Endocrinology at Kingston Hospital, Surrey where I ran a district general hospital diabetes and endocrinology service, with out-reach diabetes and endocrinology clinics and was Chairman of the Department of Medicine and Trust Information Technology Lead for my last 4 years there.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In March 2003 I moved to the Chelsea and Westminster Hospital and also hold Honorary Consultant Endocrinologist Contracts with the Royal Brompton Hospital, London (where I undertake a Cystic Fibrosis Related Diabetes Clinic) and The Royal Marsden Hospital. On the Chelsea and Westminster Hospital site I have a General Medicine responsibility as well as providing a Diabetes and Endocrine outpatient service with 4 colleagues. I was also the Clinical Lead for the Obesity Service for Central London Community Healthcare Trust (2009-2014), where I helped set up a Tier 3 service for the Kensignton and Chelsea CCG.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I was the Clinical Tutor for Chelsea and Westminster Hospital from 2003 to 2013 and then became the Director of Multi-professional Education for the trust in 2013 to date. I am involved in teaching an MSc module in Diabetic Retinopathy for the University of Roehampton Diabetes MSc program, as well as teaching and examining on the Middlesex University / Rila Publications Postgraduate Diploma in Diabetes and Endocrinology course from 1998 to date.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I chaired the London Deanery Clinical Tutors group from 2007 to 2009, being deputy from 2005 to 2007. I am an Honorary Senior Lecturer at Imperial College, London and was Chairman of the Year 3 Examination Board for the Imperial College MB BS course (2008 &ndash; 2015). I was President of the British Association of Retinal Screening (BARS) from 2010 to 2013, having been a council member for BARS from 2006 to 2010, and represented the UK on the International Diabetes Federations Diabetic Retinopathy Education Group from 2011-2013.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I am currently on the Department of Health&rsquo;s Endocrinology Clinical Reference Group, representing London and the South East, and an on the Departments of Health&rsquo;s Improving Value Group, representing the Endocrinology CGR, as well as serving on the NICE Adult Diabetes Guidelines group. I have written several diabetes and endocrinology text book chapters including the diabetes and lipid sections in the first two editions of the Oxford Handbook of Diabetes and Endocrinology, chapters on diabetes in the Oxford Textbook of Diagnosis and Treatment and on diabetes and hypoglycaemia in the Oxford Textbook of Acute Medicine, as well as the adrenal crisis section for the Oxford Textbook of Acute Medicine. My research interests include diabetic retinopathy and screening, methods for the delivery of postgraduate and undergraduate education and I have supervised both BSc and PhD research degees, through Imperial college.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-02 00:11:55','2018-08-02 00:13:16',1),(218,31,20,'1533149616.jpg','Domenico Antonio Restivo','darestivo@libero.it','+393397534652','Department of Internal Medicine','Editorial board member','Italy','Nuovo Garibaldi Hospital','05','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Restivo was born in Catania on 1969. He graduated from the University of Catania in 1994 He completed his residence in Neurology at the University of Catania in 1999 and his residence in Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation at the same university in 2007. He received a PhD in &quot;Applied Biomedical Sciences&quot; at the Institute of Human Physiology, University of Catania in 2002. He is Consultant Neurologist at the Neurologic Unit of the &quot;Garibaldi&quot; Hospital of Catania, where in addition to clinical work is also chief of the laboratory of clinical neurophysiology. His main scientific interests are: neurogenic dysphagia, pathophysiology of swallowing control, neurogenic dysphagia rehabilitation, electromyography, neuropathic pain, and peripheral neuropathies. Dr. Restivo has participated in important international clinical trials on diabetic neuropathic pain, and he has received grants as principal investigator for research projects on neurogenic dysphagia by the Italian Multiple Sclerosis Foundation (FISM). Dr Restivo is reviewer of submitted reasearch project for the Italian Multiple Sclerosis Foundation (FISM). He has participated as an author / co-author of a major book series. He is author/coauthor of about 100 scientific publications in journals of national and international importance. He partecipated as speaker to a number of international neurological meetings and is reviewer of numerous prestigious international scientific journals, including &ldquo;The New England Journal of Medicine&rdquo;,&rdquo;The&nbsp; Lancet&rdquo;, &ldquo;Lancet Neurology&rdquo;, &ldquo;Gastroenterology&rdquo;, &ldquo;European Journal of Neurological Sciences, Neurological Sciences &ldquo;. </span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-02 00:23:35','2018-08-02 00:23:35',1),(219,35,20,'1533234181.jpg','Shoji Ohga','ohga@forest.kyushu-u.ac.jp','81929483116','Department of Agro-environmental Sciences Faculty of Agriculture','Editorial board member','Japan','Kyushu University','23','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#222222\">Fungi Mushrooms is specialized in research on environmental restoration and health foods.</span> <span style=\"color:#222222\">In particular, there are many achievements of purification of soil contamination by fungi and restoration of natural environment preservation power. Studies on medicinal mushrooms and traditional Chinese medicine are advancing advanced research on the maintenance of scarce natural resources such as caterpillar fungi, <em>Ophiocordyceps sinensis</em>.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-02 23:53:01','2018-08-02 23:53:01',1),(220,35,20,'1533234517.jpg','Luis F. Garcia del Moral ','lfgm@ugr.es','(34) 958 24 32 53','Department of Plant Physiology, Faculty of Sciences','Editorial board member','Spain','University of Granada','24','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Luis F. Garcia del Moral is a Full Professor of Plant Physiology and Biotechnology at the Faculty of Sciences in the University of Granada (Spain). Senior Principal Scientific is the head of a research group on Crop Physiology. His research efforts are dedicated to the understanding of yield determination and quality of cereal crops under different management and environmental conditions, with emphasis on water and high temperature stresses in the Mediterranean area, as well as in the use of physiological and molecular markers as tools for breeding in dry environments. Author of 69 scientific articles cited in Web of Science (WOS) and 14 book chapters, his h index in WOS is 24 and 33 in Google Scholar. Director of more than 17 research projects and 13 doctoral theses on crop physiology, he has been commissioned by the Rector of the University of Granada for scientific and academic relations with Morocco and has served as an adviser and evaluator for various agencies of the Spanish Government. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research of Interest:</strong> Crop physiology, abiotic stress, plant growth analysis, crop phenology, ecophysiological and molecular approaches in plant breeding.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-02 23:58:36','2018-08-02 23:58:36',1),(221,35,20,'1533235048.jpg','Gamal Abdel-Nasser Mohamed Khalil','nasserga@alexu.edu.eg','(+2) 01112632489','Professor of Soil Physics & Water Management Faculty of Agriculture','Editorial board member','Egypt','Alexandria University','25','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Professor Gamal Khalil is working as full professor of soil physics and water management, Soil and Agricultural Chemistry Dept., Faculty of Agriculture (Saba Basha)- Alexandria University- Alexandria &ndash; EGYPT. Prof. Gamal Khalil was born in Alexandria, Egypt on March 09, 1953. He attended the Alexandria University and graduated in 1975 with B.Sc. degree in Soil and Water Sciences. He obtained M.Sc. degree in Soil Physics from Assiut University, Egypt in 1984. In 1991 he was awarded a Ph.D. degree in Soil Physics from Alexandria University, Egypt. He joined the Department of Soils and Agricultural Chemistry, Alexandria University, Egypt as Lecturer in 1991, Assistant Professor in 1996 and full Professor in 2002. He is specialized in soil physics &amp; water management and is involved in teaching both undergraduate and graduate level courses in soil physics program (Soil physics, Advanced soil physics, Applied soil physics, Environmental soil physics, Solid Waste Management, Soil Hydrology, Soil, water and plant relations and Transport processes in soil environment). His research interests are focused on fate and transport of pollutants in soil and groundwater, water and solute transport in soil, soil and wastewater remediation with organic wastes. He has authored and co-authored for about 107 scientific publications in refereed journals. He is Editor and Associate Editor of many international journals. He was a supervisor and co-supervisor of 33 M.Sc. and Ph.D. students and contributed for 15 scientific projects. He regularly reviews papers for scientific journals as well as research proposals and projects for governmental agencies.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research Interest:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"LTR\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Soil physical properties in relation to water management; Water in relation to soil and plant; Plant-water consumptive use; Water-use efficiency; Water movement in relation to pollution sources; Irrigation scheduling in desert regions; Fertilization in relation to water-use efficiency; Water saving through using plant antitranspirants; Clay-jar subsurface irrigation system; Simulation models of transport processes for water and pollutants; Water conservation through soil surface treatments; Studies on infiltration function in relation to irrigation methods; Computer simulation of soil-water relations, Agro-meteorological studies of plant evapotranspiration; Application of statistical methods in soil physics studies; Modeling of solute transport in soil system; Management of soil physical properties; Fertigation management in desert regions; Organic farming; Soil conditioners; Using organic residues in remediation of contaminated soils with heavy metals; Using organic residues in remediation of industrial wastewaters; Using nanotechnology in wastewater treatment.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-03 00:07:27','2018-08-03 00:09:41',1),(222,19,20,'1533235672.jpg','David Cheneler','d.cheneler@lancaster.ac.uk','07792414402','Lecturer in Engineering','Editorial board member','England','Lancaster University','17','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I am a lecturer in engineering at Lancaster University, a chartered engineer and a fellow of the HEA. I am the Deputy Admissions Director and Internationalisation Coordinator for the Engineering Department. In this latter role, I coordinate International Teaching Partnerships (in China, India and Pakistan), Strategic Research Partnerships and international collaborations in Asia, Africa and the Middle East and elsewhere globally. I am also the Director of the international partnerships within Engineering for COMSATS in Pakistan (Lahore campus) and GDGWI in India and am primarily responsible for quality assurance of the programmes delivered there. I am also the programme director for the MSc in International Innovation (engineering pathway) which is part of the Lancaster China Catalyst Programme, which aims to develop partnerships between UK companies with commercial partners in China. I am course convenor on a first year module, ENGR119: Design, Innovation and 3D Thinking, and a fourth year/MSc module, ENGR411/511: Advanced CAD/CAM, and co-teach another module: ENGR404/504: Mechanics and Actuators. I am also on the Operations team for the Materials Science Institute at Lancaster University.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Specialties:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Material characterisation, numerical modelling including FEA, CFD and FDM, advanced manufacturing including additive manufacturing and laser processing, development of biomedical technologies.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-03 00:17:52','2018-08-03 00:17:52',1),(223,26,20,'1533236080.jpg','FSalah Altarabsheh','salah936@gmail.com','962- 777181844','Department of Cardiovascular Surgery','Editorial board member','Jordan','Queen Alia Military Hospital','05','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr Salah Altarabsheh is a Jordanian born, board certified in cardiac surgery, who is currently working as a consultant cardiac surgeon in Queen Alia Heart Institute, Jordan</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Salah had his advanced cardiac surgery training for two years in full time at the Mayo Clinic Foundation, Rochester, MN as well as one full year time at Texas Heart Institute, Houston, TX.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Scientifically he is being interested in new advances in mitral valve repair as well as coronary arterial revascularization.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Salah has outstanding records of scientific and academic accomplishments that include numerous publications in highly prestigious journals and various presentations in both national and international conferences and had been awarded for his research achievements.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He also serves as an editorial board member as well as reviewer in couple of scientific journals</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-03 00:24:39','2018-08-03 00:24:39',1),(225,22,20,'','Jianying Zhang','jianying@pitt.edu','1-412-648-9294 ','Research Associate Professor  Department of Orthopaedic Surgery','Editorial board member','USA','University of Pittsburgh','01','',1,'2018-08-03 00:49:35','2018-08-03 00:49:35',1),(226,35,20,'1533319631.jpg','Said Elshahat Abdallah ','saidelshahat@agr.kfs.edu.eg','+201008407294','Faculty of Agriculture, Department of Agricultural Engineering','Editorial board member','Egypt','Kafrelsheikh University','26','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Prof. Dr. Said Elshahat Abdallah is working as Professor of Agricultural Process Engineering, Department of Agricultural Engineering, Faculty of Agriculture, Kafrelsheikh University, Egypt. He was born on January 6, 1972. He obtained his Ph. D. degree in Technical Sciences in November 2005 from the Faculty of Design, Don State Technical University, Russia. He prepared many scientific literatures such as Engineering of Food Factories and Dairy Plants, Engineering Thermodynamics and Heat Transfer, introduction to agricultural process engineering, Instrumentation, Properties and Testing of Engineering Materials,Fitting of Curves and Differential Equations and Differentiation &amp; Integration, etc&hellip; He published more than thirty research articles in international peerreviewed journals. He supervised, has done and examined about twenty M. Sc. and Ph. D. dissertations. He participated in several either local or international conferences on the topics of Agricultural Process Engineering. He contributed in the attendance of many meetings, workshops and training courses. He was awarded: Food Engineer of the Year Award &ndash; 2010; Excellence Award in<br />\r\nInternational Scientific Publication &ndash; 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017 and 2018; Arab Papers Published on Agriculture &ndash; 2012; Egypt 25 Foundation Award &ndash; 2012; Who&#39;s Who in the World &ndash; 2013, 2014 and 2015; 2000 Outstanding Intellectuals of the 21st Century &ndash; 2013; Top 100 Engineers&ndash; 2013; International Biographical Center Man of The Year&ndash; 2013; Cambridge Certificate for Outstanding Engineering Achievement &ndash; 2013 and Cambridge Certificate for Outstanding Educational Achievement &ndash; 2013. He served as: Editor-in-Chief; Associate Editor; Editorial Board Member; Food Expert; Reviewer, etc&hellip; in more than five hundred international peer-reviewed journals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research Interest:</strong><br />\r\nAgricultural Process Engineering; Postharvest Technology; Bioengineering; Food &amp; Dairy Engineering; Agro-Industrial Waste Management; Process and Bioprocess Engineering; Thermal &amp; Non-Thermal Process Engineering; Agricultural Production Engineering; Postharvest operations Engineering; Composting and Vermicomposting Process; Non-Conventional Forages Processing; Farm Wastes Bioconversion; By-Products Recycling Engineering.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-03 23:37:11','2018-08-03 23:37:11',1),(227,35,20,'1533320230.jpg','Muhammed Yuceer','myyuceer@gmail.com','+90.536.457.28.77','Assistant Professor ','Editorial board member','Turkey','Canakkale Onsekiz Mart University','27','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Muhammed Yuceer is a food scientist and an academician (Assistant Professor in the Department of Food Processing, Canakkale Onsekiz Mart University (Comu), Canakkale, Turkey). Yuceer received Bsc from Yuzuncu Yil University (2002), and MSc from Istanbul Technical University, department of food engineering (2007). Yuceer obtained PhD in food engineering department of Comu (2013). His career began in R&amp;D department of largest egg processing plant in Turkey. Before joining the University, he was a Deputy Director of Factory Manager, as an egg-processing expert for 10 years. His current research interests on egg science and application of novel techniques.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research Interest:</strong><br />\r\nEgg Science and Technology (Egg and Egg Products, Egg Processing), Thermal and Non-Thermal Emerging Food Preservation Techniques (active packaging, coating application, antimicrobial coating, ozone, ultrasound, electrolyzed water etc.), Food Defense, Food Safety, Quality Control and Quality Management Systems, Functional Food, Rheology and filtration, Industrial Food Production, Protein Separation and Purification Process for Bioactive Substances of foods and eggs. Control and System Engineering for Food Industry.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-03 23:47:10','2018-08-03 23:47:10',1),(228,35,20,'1533320680.jpg','Sevil Saglam Yilmaz','saglamsevil@gmail.com','+9003862804818','Assoc. Prof, Department of Agricultural Biotechnology ','Editorial board member','Turkey','University of Kirsehir Ahi Evran ','28','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Sevil Saglam Yilmaz is Assoc.<strong> </strong>Professor of Agricultural Biotechnology at University of Kirsehir Ahi Evran, Kirsehir, Turkey. She is also the chair of that Department. Dr Sevil Saglam Yilmaz received master&rsquo;s level &nbsp;and doctoral training in Agricultural Biotechnology at the University of Ankara in Ankara, Turkey. In addition to research, Dr. Sevil Saglam Yilmaz teaches plant tissue culture and plant gene transformation methods to postgraduate students. Dr Sevil Saglam Yilmaz&rsquo;s professional interests are in the area of gene transformation via <em>Agribacterium</em>, mainly in plant biotechnology.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-03 23:54:40','2018-08-03 23:56:08',1),(229,28,20,'1533321165.jpg','Xiaoping Luo','xpluo@tjh.tjmu.edu.cn','+86-27-83663712','Professor and Chairman, Department of Pediatrics','Editorial board member','China','Tongji Hospital','20','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Xiaoping Luo is the Professor and Chairman of the Department of Pediatrics, Director, Division of Pediatric Endocrinology and Metabolism, Tongji Hospital, Director of the Center for the Diagnosis of Genetic Metabolic Diseases, Tongji Medical College, Huazhong University of Science and Technology, Wuhan, China. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Luo obtained his medical degree from Tongji Medical University in 1985. After graduate study, he stayed in the Department of Pediatrics of the affiliated Tongji Hospital and specialized in neonatology, and was appointed as an associate professor of pediatrics in 1992. From January 1994, he worked as a visiting scientist in the Division of Genetic Metabolic Diseases in the Department of Pediatric Laboratory Medicine in the Hospital for Sick Children in Toronto. In July 1997, he joined the CIHR group in Lung Development and Neonatal Research, and the Lung Biology Programme in the Research Institute of the Hospital for Sick Children, as a research associate/scientist. He was appointed as an adjunct professor in the Department of Paediatrics, Faculty of Medicine, University of Toronto since 2000, before he moved back to China where he subsequently became a full professor and vice chairman of the Department of Pediatrics, Tongji Hospital. He assumed his current positions as Chairman of the Department of Pediatrics in Tongji Hospital in Wuhan since 2003.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Luo is now the Vice President of the Chinese Pediatric Society (CPS), President of the Chinese Society of Pediatric Endocrinology and Metabolism (CSPEM). He is also the past president for the Asia Pacific Paediatric Endocrine Society (APPES), Executive Committee member of the Global Pediatric Endocrinology and Diabetes (GPED), Board of Directors for the Asian Society for Inherited Metabolic Diseases (ASIMD), Council member of the Growth Hormone Research Society (GRS). His main interests are pediatric endocrinology and metabolism, and neonatal/perinatal medicine. Dr. Luo&rsquo;s research was funded by the National Natural Science Foundation of China, the Ministry of Health, the Ministry of Education, and the Ministry of Science and Technology of China, and the World Diabetes Foundation, etc. He has published 48 book chapters and over 380peer reviewed articles, and served as editor or reviewer for 45 domestic and international medical journals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>Research Interest:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Neonatology/Perinatology</strong>: Oxygen Toxocity; Oxidant/Antioxidant; Lung Development; Hypoxic Ischemic Encephalopathy; Cardiomyopathy (doxorubicin toxicity, iron overload, reperfusion injury); Free Radical Injury and Lipid Peroxidation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Genetic Metabolic Disease:&nbsp;</strong>Inborn Errors of Metabolism; Clinical Biochemistry; Mass Spectrometry; Animal Models; QA/QC; etc.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Pediatric Endocrinology and diabetes</strong>: Growth; Puberty;&nbsp; DSD; Adrenal and thyrioid disorders; &nbsp;Obesity and diabetes.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-04 00:02:44','2018-08-04 00:02:44',1),(230,26,20,'1533321553.jpg','Shih-Tai Chang','cst1234567@yahoo.com.tw','','Department of Cardiology ','Editorial board member','Taiwan, Province of China','Chang Gung Memorial  Hospital','06','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I had been a clinical cardiologist for 20 years. My expert fields are metabolic syndrome, coronary arterial disease (including myocardial infarction and acute coronary syndrome), peripheral arterial disease. Now, I am at the position of visiting staff of Chia-Yi Chang Gung Memorial Hospital and with the degree of Associated Professor of cardiology.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">My research projects including peripheral arterial disease, erectile dysfunction and coronary disease, and myocardial infarction animal model setting.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In the past years, I had published more than 20 more first author articles in the cardiology field. And, I was of the editorial board of World Journal of Cardiology.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-04 00:09:12','2018-08-04 00:09:12',1),(231,19,20,'1533322153.jpg','Dazhi Fan','fandazhigw@163.com','','Professor','Editorial board member','China','Maternal & Child Health Hospital of Foshan - Southern Medical University','18','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dazhi Fan completed his Bachelor in Preventive Medicine from Anhui Medical University in 2012.He completed his MPH from Anhui Medical University in 2015.</span></span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Currently, he is a Public Health Physician in Foshan Institute of Fetal Medicine, Southern Medical University Affiliated Maternal &amp; Child Health Hospital of Foshan</span>. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Research Interests</span></strong><span style=\"color:black\">:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:black\">Clinical Trials, Evidence-Based Medicine, Clinical Epidemiology and Public Health, Medical Statistics, Big Data Analytics</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-04 00:19:12','2018-08-04 00:19:12',1),(232,22,20,'1533374229.jpg','Jessica Cottrell','cottreje@shu.edu','732-948-6936 ','Assistant Professor, Department of Biological Sciences','Editorial board member','USA','Seton Hall University','02','',1,'2018-08-04 14:46:19','2018-08-04 14:47:09',1),(233,20,20,'1533374765.jpg','Alireza Heidari','Alireza.Heidari@calsu.us','','Director of the BioSpectroscopy Core Research ','Editorial board member','USA','California South University','05','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Prof. Dr. Alireza Heidari, Ph.D., D.Sc. is a Full Professor and Academic Tenure of Chemistry at California South University (CSU), Irvine, California, USA. He has got his Ph.D. and D.Sc. degrees from California South University (CSU), Irvine, California, USA. Furthermore, he has double postdocs in Project Management, Oncology, Human Cancer Tissues and Synchrotron Radiation from Monash University, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia and also in Nanochemistry and Modern Molecular Electronic&ndash;Structure Computations Theory from California South University (CSU), Irvine, California, USA.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">His research interests include Biophysical Chemistry, Biomolecular Spectroscopy, Quantum Chemistry, Nanochemistry, Modern Electronic Structure Computations, Theoretical Chemistry, Mathematical Chemistry, Computational Chemistry, Vibrational Spectroscopy, Molecular Modelling, Ab initio &amp; Density Functional Methods, Molecular Structure, Biochemistry, Molecular Simulation, Pharmaceutical Chemistry, Medicinal Chemistry, Oncology, Synchrotron Radiation, Synchrocyclotron Radiation, LASER, Anti&ndash;Cancer Nano Drugs, Nano Drugs Delivery, ATR&ndash;FTIR Spectroscopy, Raman Spectroscopy, Intelligent Molecules, Molecular Dynamics, Biosensors, Biomarkers, Molecular Diagnostics, Numerical Chemistry, Nucleic Acids, DNA/RNA Monitoring, DNA/RNA Hypermethylation &amp; Hypomethylation, Human Cancer Tissues, Human Cancer Cells, Tumors, Cancer Tissues, Cancer Cells, etc.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He has participated at more than three hundreds reputed international conferences, seminars, congresses, symposiums and forums around the world as yet. Also, he possesses many published articles in Science Citation Index (SCI)/International Scientific Indexing (ISI) Journals. It should be noted that he has visited many universities or scientific and academic research institutes in different countries such as United States, United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, Scotland, Ireland, Netherlands, Belgium, Denmark, Greece, Russia, Estonia, Ukraine, Turkey, France, Swiss, Germany, Sweden, Norway, Italy, Austria, Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland, South Africa, Egypt, Brazil, Spain, Portugal, Mexico, Japan, Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, Taiwan, Hong Kong, South Korea, China, India, Qatar, United Arab Emirates, etc. as research fellow, sabbatical and volunteer researcher or visitor and so on heretofore. He has a history of several years of teaching for college students and various disciplines and trends in different universities. Moreover, he has been a senior advisor in various industry and factories.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is expert in many computer programs and programming languages. Hitherto, he has authored more than twenty books and book chapters in different fields of Chemistry. Syne, he has been awarded more than nine hundreds reputed international awards, prizes, scholarships and honors. Heretofore, he has multiple editorial duties in many reputed international journals, books and publishers. Hitherward, he is a member of more than three hundreds reputed international academic&ndash;scientific&ndash;research institutes around the world. It should be noted that he is currently the President of American International Standards Institute (AISI), Irvine, California, USA and also Director of the BioSpectroscopy Core Research Laboratory at California South University (CSU), Irvine, California, USA.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-04 14:56:04','2018-08-04 14:59:14',1),(234,31,20,'1533627859.png','Imene Ksibi Ben Salem','imeneksibibs@yahoo.fr','00216 54428016','Department of physical and rehabilitation Medicine','Editorial board member','Tunisia','Military Tunis Hospital','03','',1,'2018-08-07 13:14:19','2018-08-07 13:14:19',1),(235,24,20,'1533628279.jpg','Medhat Abdelmalek','malek_clinic@yahoo.com','+9626- 4648317 ','Director ','Editorial board member','Jordan','Dr. Malek Cosmetic, Laser and Skin Clinic','05','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Medhat Abdel Malek received his specialty degree from the University of London, Saint John&rsquo;s hospital institute of dermatology, UK. He is the founder of laser associate group&nbsp; in Jordan , Reviewer at &lsquo;Dermatologic Therapy&rsquo;, Allergan Local Country and Middle-East Mentor, Annual &nbsp;Professor of dermatology at Marconi University, Italy and author of&nbsp; few book chapters. He is a Member of several American and European dermatological societies. Additionally Dr Medhat is a reputable late lecturer at the department of dermatology, university of Jordan and a late board examiner at the Jordan Medical Council, late vice President of the Pan Arab League of Dermatology and Venereology&nbsp; and the Late Chairman of the Jordanian Society of Dermatology and Venereology.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-07 13:21:18','2018-08-07 13:21:18',1),(236,25,20,'1533628575.jpg','Jie Zhou','jiezhou198208@126.com','+8613880750750','Doctor degree in management science ','Editorial board member','China','Sichuan Normal University','05','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Jie Zhou, received the Doctor degree in management science from Southwest Jiaotong University and received the Master degree in applied mathematics from Sichuan Normal University, Chengdu, China. He is currently a associate professor of Sichuan Normal university. He also is the author or coauthor of more than 10 journal papers. He currently presides over the Youth Fund of the National Natural Science Foundation of P.R.China.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><em>Research interests</em></strong>?Healthcare operations management (using revenue management and queueing theory).</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-07 13:26:14','2018-08-07 13:26:14',1),(237,25,20,'1533628831.jpg','Francisco Epelde','fepelde@gmail.com','652508832','Medical Coordinator. Short Stay Unit','Editorial board member','Spain','Hospital de Sabadell. Consorci Hospitalari i Universitari Parc Taul','06','',1,'2018-08-07 13:30:30','2018-08-07 13:30:30',1),(238,32,20,'1533790999.jpg','Bruno Jorge Pereira','brunoalexpereira@gmail.com','','Faculty of Health Sciences','Editorial board member','Portugal','Universidade da Beira Interior','05','',1,'2018-08-09 10:33:21','2018-08-09 10:33:21',1),(239,32,20,'1533791811.jpg','Sabah Mohamed Alharazy','sabah_alharazy@yahoo.co.uk','','Department of Medicine','Editorial board member','Malaysia','Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia Medical Centre','06','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Sabah received her M.Med.Sc and Ph.D degrees in medicine from the National University of Malaysia. She has good records in research and publication with a good number of first authored, peer reviewed publications. She has also reviewed several scientific papers for more than 15 peer-reviewed medical journals. Currently, she is serving on the editorial boards for several medical journals. Her research interests include acute kidney injury, chronic kidney disease, lupus nephritis and novel biomarkers of renal function.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr.Sabah has presented a number of abstracts and posters at local and national meetings.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">She has also received awards including 3rd and 1st Prizes for presenting a prize winning paper at Malaysian Society of Nephrology in 2010 and 2013 respectively. She has also received sponsored Travel fellowship from International Society of Nephrology-Hong Kong Society of Nephrology-Asian-Pacific Society of Nephrology to attend the World Congress of Nephrology in 2013.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-09 10:46:51','2018-08-09 10:50:33',1),(240,32,20,'1533792477.jpg','Serena Maruccia','serena.maruccia.urologia@gmail.com','(+39) 3478450365','Deputy Chief at the Urology Division','Editorial board member','Italy','Istituti Clinici Zucchi','08','',1,'2018-08-09 10:57:56','2018-08-09 10:57:56',1),(241,32,20,'1533792908.gif','Flavia Cristina Morone Pinto','fcmorone@gmail.com','','Bachelor of Science in Nursing ','Editorial board member','Brazil','Federal University of Pernambuco','08','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Bachelor of Science in Nursing (RN-BSN) from Federal University of the State of Rio de Janeiro. Master of Science (M.Sc.), National School of Public Health/Oswaldo Cruz Foundation (FIOCRUZ).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Doctoral Urogenital Research (Ph.D.), Postgraduate Program in Physiopathology and Surgical Sciences, Urogenital Research Unit /UERJ, emphasis on studies of radioprotective substances.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Postdoctoral degree in Surgery, Postgraduate Program in Surgery, Federal University of Pernambuco.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Adjunct Professor, Academic Center of Vitoria, Nutrition Center, Public Health course at the Federal University of Pernambuco, UFPE/PE, Brazil. Researcher collaborator, Nucleus of Experimental Surgery, Department of Surgery and National School of Public Health, Oswaldo Cruz Foundation, ENSP/FIOCRUZ.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Experience in development of model experimental designs and clinical trials in surgery.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-09 11:05:08','2018-08-09 11:05:08',1),(242,35,20,'1533793862.jpg','Farhood  Golmohammadi','FARHOOD.GOL@GMAIL.COM','00983145245914','Assistant Professor, Department of   Agricultural Extension and Education','Editorial board member','Iran','Islamic Azad University','29','',1,'2018-08-09 11:21:03','2018-08-09 11:21:03',1),(243,23,20,'1533794081.png','Alfio Ferlito','alfio.ferlito@uniud.it','','Department of Otolaryngology','Editorial board member','Italy','University of Udine School of Medicine','05','<p>Formerly Director of the Department of Surgical Sciences at the University of Udine School of Medicine from 2003 to 2009 and Professor and Chairman of the ENT Clinic at the same University from 1997 to 2013. He graduated in medicine at the University of Bologna in 1968. He completed his residence programme in otolaryngology and subsequently in pathology. He worked at the ENT Department of&nbsp;&nbsp; Padua University from 1970 to 1997. Since 2009 he is the Coordinator of the International Head Neck Scientific Group (www.IHNSG.com).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Professor Ferlito has collaborated in writing articles, editorials, commentaries, Consensus statement Consensus statementconsensus statements, letters to the editor, special issues, book chapters and books with 669 international experts. He has edited a three-volume book entitled <em>Cancer of the Larynx</em> (CRC Press, Boca Raton, 1985) and three other books entitled <em>Neoplasms of the Larynx</em> (Churchill Livingstone, Edinburgh, 1993), <em>Surgical Pathology of Laryngeal Neoplasms</em> (Chapman and Hall, London, 1996) and <em>Diseases of the Larynx</em> (Arnold, London, 2000), and co-authored two books entitled <em>Granulomas and Neoplasms of the Larynx</em> together with Professor Imrich Friedmann (Churchill Livingstone, Edinburgh, 1988) and <em>Surgery for Cancer of the Larynx and Related Structures</em> together with Dr. Carl E. Silver (Saunders, Philadelphia, 1996). He is editor with Dr. Marvin P. Fried of the third edition of a two-volume book entitled <em>The Larynx </em>(Plural Publishing, San Diego, 2009) and with Drs. K. Thomas Robbins and Carl E. Silver of the book entitled <em>Neck Dissection - Management of Regional Disease in Head and Neck Cancer</em> (Plural Publishing, San Diego, 2010). He is Editor of four issues of <em>ORL Journal for Oto-Rhino-Laryngology, Head and Neck Surgery.</em> Professor Ferlito has been author or co-author of 660 referred publications in 70 medical journals and 54 chapters in various books.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He serves/served as editor, co-editor, assistant editor or reviewer for the following 742 journals: <em>The Lancet; The Lancet Oncology; Advanced Drug Delivery Reviews; </em><em>Nature Communications; </em><em>Nature Clinical Practice Oncology;</em> <em>Human Molecular Genetics;&nbsp; Clinical Cancer Research; BMC Medicine; Cancer; Acta Biomaterialia; </em><em>Clinical Epidemiology; </em><em>European Journal of Cancer; </em><em>International Journal of Cancer; </em><em>Expert Review of Molecular Diagnostics; </em><em>Biomarkers in Medicine; </em><em>Modern Pathology; Molecular Carcinogenesis; Oncotarget; Annals of Surgical Oncology;</em><em> Surgical Endoscopy; Cellular Physiology and Biochemistry; British Journal of Cancer; </em><em>FEBS Journal;</em><em> Radiotherapy and Oncology; Investigational New Drugs; </em><em>Thyroid; Cancers; </em><em>Journal of Pathology Research; Epigenomics; </em><em>Journal of the American College of Surgeons; Oral Oncology; European Journal of Surgical Oncology -The Journal of Cancer Surgery; European Journal of Endocrinology; Histopathology; Journal of the European Academy of Dermatology and Venereology; Head and Neck; Expert Opinion on Pharmacotherapy; PLOS ONE; </em><em>Future Oncology; </em><em>Pediatric Infectious Disease Journal; </em><em>Journal of Cancer Research and Clinical Oncology;</em> <em>International Journal of Molecular Sciences;</em> <em>Cancer Chemotherapy and Pharmacology; Biotechnic &amp; Histochemistry; Journal of Surgical Oncology; Histology and Histopathology; Respiratory Medicine; Experimental and Molecular Pathology;</em> <em>Immunotherapy;</em><em> Translational Oncology; Oral Diseases; </em><em>Cancer Medicine