 and Primary Care; Clinical Oncology Research Journal; Journal of Biomarker Research and Studies; Cases Med Research Journal; Journal of Neurology and Epidemiology; Neurology and Neurorehabilitation Research; Global Scientific Research Journal of Surgery, </em><em>International Journal of Tropical Medicine and Health;</em> <em>Annals Journal &amp; Bulletin Journal;</em> <em>Enliven: Clinical Case Reports; Archives of Community and Family Medicine;</em> <em>Advances in Pharmacology &amp; Clinical Trials; Chemotherapy Research Journal; Journal of Natural Products Research Updates; Open Journal for Surgery Case Reports; Archives of Surgery; Journal of Emergency, Critical Care and Diagnostic Management; Chemotherapy Research Journal; Preventive Medicine Research;&nbsp; International Journal of Clinical Pathology and Diagnosis; Global Scientific Research Journal of Public Health; Journal of surgery and advanced surgical techniques; Journal of Recent Advancement in Food Science and Nutrition Research; Journal of Regional Anesthesia and Intensive Care; Current Analysis on Oncology; Global Journal of Human Anatomy and Physiology Research; Signal and Information Processing; Spinal Diseases and Research; Journal of Clinical and Medical Imaging; International Technology and Science Publications; International Journal of Thyroid Disorders and Therapy; Postgraduate Medicine; Journal of Infectious Diseases and Therapeutics; Medical Frontiers; Journal of Rheumatology &amp; Arthritis Research; Journal of Human Anatomy; American Journal of Microbiology &amp; Biochemistry; Journal of Autoimmune Diseases and Rheumatology; Journal of Clinical and Laboratory Investigation Updates; Journal of Family Medicine &amp; Public Health;&nbsp; Journal of Palliative Medical Care &amp; Research; Management Science and Engineering; LOJ Medical Sciences; Journal of Surgical Science and Operative Care; European Journal of Rheumatology; CPQ Medicine; Online Journal of Otolaryngology and Rhinology; Innovations in Rehabilitation Research.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Professor Ferlito has been awarded <em>ad hominem</em> fellowship from the Royal College of Surgeons of Edinburgh and <em>ad eundem</em> fellowship from the Royal College of Surgeons of England, Glasgow, Ireland and Dental Surgery of the Royal College of Surgeons of England. He is a fellow or a member of the American College of Surgeons, the Royal College of Pathologists, the Royal Society of Medicine of London, the American Otological Society, the American Laryngological Association, the Collegium Oto-Rhino-Laryngologicum Amicitiae Sacrum, the American Laryngological Rhinological and Otological Association, the American Society for Head and Neck Surgery, the Society of Head and Neck Surgeons, the American Broncho-Esophagological Association, the American Rhinologic Society, the Association for Research in Otolaryngology, the American Academy of Otolaryngology-Head and Neck Surgery, the International Broncho-Esophagological Society, the Oto-Rhino-Laryngological Society of Japan, the Japan Laryngological Association, the American Association for the Advancement of Science, the Hungarian Association of Otorhinolaryngologists (Honorary), the Slovenian Association of Otorhinolaryngologists, the Slovak Society of Otolaryngology-Head and Neck Surgery (Honorary), the Spanish Society of Otorhinolaryngology-Head and Neck Surgery (Honorary), the Israeli Society of Head and Neck Surgery and Oncology, the Hong Kong College of Otolaryngologists, the New York Academy of Sciences, the Laryngeal Cancer Association, Deutsche Gesellschaft f&uuml;r Hals-Nasen-Ohren-Heilkunde, Kopf- und Hals-Chirurgie, the American Society for Clinical Pathology, the College of American Pathologists, the International Academy of Pathology, the International Academy of Oral Oncology and the Interventional Oncology Society.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Professor Ferlito has been honored with several distinctions from professional ENT Societies including two Presidential Citations from the American Laryngological Association for his contributions made to the field of laryngology and the association. He has been appointed as the International Liaison for Corresponding Fellows of the American Laryngological Association. He is also a Fellowship External Examiner in Otorhinolaryngology at the Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has been invited as visiting professor at the Departments of Otolaryngology of the Universities of Ljubljiana, Valencia, Zagreb, Yale, Pittsburgh, Amsterdam, San Francisco, Hong Kong, Seoul and Tokyo, at the House Ear Institute of Los Angeles, at the Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center and Montefiore Medical Center of New York. He collaborated as a member of the World Health Organization&rsquo;s Committee on Histological Typing of Tumours of the Upper Respiratory Tract and Ear. He is also a member of the Laryngeal Cancer Association&rsquo;s Committee on the Classification of Laryngeal Cancer. He was consultant to Yale University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Professor Ferlito has delivered prestigious lectures all over the world. In 2006 he gave the 2<sup>nd</sup> Morrison Lecture in San Francisco and the 19<sup>th</sup> Som Lecture in New York. He has divided his professional life between clinical practice, teaching and research. One of his chief interests is the promotion of international cooperation in head and neck surgery, oncology and cancer research.</p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-09 11:24:41','2019-02-13 17:16:54',1),(244,24,20,'1533795189.jpg','Mahaveer Mehta','drmmehta@emirates.net.ae','97150-4561999','Chairman','Editorial board member','United Arab Emirates','Dr.Mahaveer Mehta Medical Center Dubai ','06','<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Mahaveer Mehta is working as Dermatologist and Medical director in his own medical Center in Dubai since May 1990. Prior to this he was Chairman of the Dept. of Dermatology at Qatar armed Forces medical unit and Chairman of Dermatology at International Hospital Bahrain. He has also worked as Faculty member in Al Fateh University, Tripoli, Libya and SMS medical college, Jaipur. Dr. Mehta is internationally well known in the field of Dermatology and Lasers. He is a pioneer in introducing Lasers to the Middle East. He is successfully practicing in Dubai since 1990.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">His clean reputation is not limited to just UAE but spread across seven seas. He is one of the strongest promoters of Health Tourism in Dubai.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Mehta is a Chair and Speaker at several international dermatological and laser conferences. He is a member of Several Dermatology and Laser societies in the world.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is Board of Director, The Dermatologic &amp; Aesthetic Surgery International League (DASIL) 2013, 2014, 2015 and 2016.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is Congress President for forth coming USA based nonprofit organization annual conference DASIL Dermatology Aesthetic surgery International league held in Dubai in Oct 2016 with support from Dubai Tourism department, Government of Dubai.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&nbsp;Dr. Mehta is Chair, Scientific committee ICAAM 2013, 2014, 2015 and 2016 (International Congress in Aesthetic and anti-ageing Medicine)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is former Member advisory committee Gender Aesthetic Congress Asia 2014 organized by American Academy of Aesthetic Medicine International (AAAM)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is Mentor/Host, International Travelling Mentorship Program (ITMP), American Society of Dermatologic Surgery (ASDS). He is a recipient of prestigious awards such as Physician Recognition Award from American Medical Association and Continuing Medical Education Award from American Academy of Dermatology. He is member Editorial Board of Journal of Clinical and Cosmetic Dermatology USA, Member Editorial Board Journal of Procedural Dermatology and Former Member of the editorial board of Gulf medical college health journal</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">received outstanding contribution Medal 2016 at international Dermatology conference DASIL held in October 2016 in the field of Dermatology from (ASDS) American Society of Dermatology by Prof Lawrence field Chief of International Mentorship program ASDS USA. I am invited Chair and Faculty for World congress of Cosmetic Dermatology to be held in Bengaluru, India in May 2017.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Recipient of outstanding contribution Medal By president of Dermatology Aesthetic international league Dr. Michael Gold at annual conference.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He received most prestigious Congress Ambassador Award from Dubai Tourism department for organizing ICAAM and DASIL conferences in Dubai. He is of Member Editorial Board few International Dermatology Journals.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-09 11:43:08','2018-08-09 11:43:08',1),(245,31,20,'1533795673.jpg','Mohd Hasnun Arif Hassan','mhasnun@ump.edu.my','','Senior Lecturer','Editorial board member','Malaysia','Universiti Malaysia Pahang','07','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Hassan earned his first degree in Mechanical Engineering from the Technische Hochschule Bingen in Germany in 2010. He then pursued a Master&rsquo;s degree in Mechanical Engineering at the University of Malaya in Kuala Lumpur, graduating with distinction in 2012. After that, he embarked on his PhD at the Universiti Malaysia Pahang (UMP), where he studied the head injuries sustained by soccer players due to heading. He completed his PhD study in 2016, then continued to serve UMP as a senior lecturer. He is currently the director of the Innovative Manufacturing, Mechatronics and Sports Laboratory (iMAMS), which was founded by Professor Zahari Taha, who was his supervisor for his doctoral study. His research interests include finite element modelling of the interaction between human and sports equipment, instrumentation of sports equipment, and injury prevention particularly with regard to sport. His work aims to apply engineering principles in sports to not only enhance the performance of an athlete, but also to prevent injuries.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research Interests:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Sports Engineering</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Finite Element Analysis of Sports Equipment</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Head Injury Prevention</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,'2018-08-09 11:51:13','2018-08-09 11:51:13',1),(246,35,20,'','Sukhvinder Singh','sukhvinder.singh@pioneer.com','','Project Manager - Agronomy','Editorial board member','USA','DuPont Pioneer','02','',1,'2018-08-09 23:40:34','2018-08-09 23:40:34',1),(247,35,20,'1533931177.jpg','Parmodh Sharma','sparmodh1@gmail.com','575-571-7589','Ph.D','Editorial board member','USA','New Mexico State University','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Parmodh Sharma is a Senior Statistician/Statistical Programmer working with PVR Technologies, Inc., USA. He received his B.S. (Agriculture) and M.S. (Soil Science) from Punjab Agricultural University, India. He received another M.S. (Applied Statistics) and Ph.D. (Plant and Environmental Sciences) from New Mexico State University, USA. He has more than 15 year&rsquo;s research experience in Soils and Agronomy. He is serving as a reviewer for several prominent agriculture journals. He is a member of Soil Science Society of America, Crop Science Society of America, American Society of Agronomy, and Sigma Xi Society. Currently he is working on statistical modeling in Plant and Life Sciences field.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research interest:</span></strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#1b1b1b\">Parmodh Sharma is interested in continuing his research efforts in soil and water resources management in water-limited and irrigated agricultural production systems, as well as other natural and managed ecosystems. His research interests particularly focus on applied soil physics, soil-water-plant-atmosphere relationships, spatial and temporal variability of soil properties, nitrogen leaching, irrigation systems, Water use efficiency, Nutrient use efficiency, under different land use and management systems at multiple scales. </span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-11 01:29:36','2018-08-11 01:32:25',1),(248,29,20,'1534080112.png','Wa Xian','wa.xian@uth.tmc.edu','','Assistant Professor ','Editorial board member','USA','McGovern Medical School, University of Texas Health Science Center','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Wa Xian received her Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Biochemistry from Nankai University in China and Ph.D. degree in Molecular Genetics at the University of Texas Graduate School of Biomedical Sciences in Houston, focusing on master regulator genes of cell proliferation and lineage specification during early neural development. The support of a DOD breast cancer fellowship enabled Dr. Xian&rsquo;s postdoctoral studies with Prof. Jeffrey Rosen at the Baylor College of Medicine. There she used a combination of ligand-induced dimerization strategies and a mammary epithelial 3D culture system to address the role of fibroblast receptor tyrosine kinase signaling in the evolution of breast cancer. In 2008, Dr. Xian moved to Harvard Medical School under the direction of Prof. Christopher Crum, Director of Women&rsquo;s and Perinatal Pathology at the Brigham and Women&rsquo;s Hospital to study the origin and evolution of ovarian cancer. Dr. Xian continues to work very closely with Prof. Crum on the origins and chemotherapy resistance problem in high-grade ovarian cancer. In 2009, Dr. Xian was appointed Principal Investigator at the Institute of Medical Biology of the Agency for Science, Technology, and Research in Singapore, where she jointly oversaw a highly interactive group of postdoctoral fellows, graduate students, and research assistants with Prof Frank McKeon of the Genome Institute of Singapore devoted to the cloning of stem cells of regenerative tissues and using advanced technologies to understand the genetics of their self-renewal, commitment, and differentiation. In 2013, Dr. Xian returned to the US and initiated multiple projects related to inflammatory diseases and cancer with colleagues at the University of Connecticut Health Center. In 2015, Dr. Xian received the Rising Stars Award from the Cancer Prevention &amp; Research Institute of Texas (CPRIT) and was recruited to the Institute of Molecular Medicine at the University of Texas Health Science Center in Houston.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-12 18:52:08','2018-08-12 18:52:08',1),(249,24,20,'1534082528.jpg','Sergio A Cuevas-Covarrubias','sergiocuevasunam@gmail.com','','Head of Department of the Genetic Depart