5-2009, Dean of Faculty of Agriculture UNRI 2009-2013 and 2013-2017. Member of Indonesian Food Technologist Association (PATPI) since 2000-present, Chairman of PATPI Branch of Riau (2012-present) and Professor in Food Microbiology at Faculty of Agriculture UNRI since July 1, 2005. Usman was recorded as an editor and reviewer in several national and international scientific journals. He also often attended national and international seminars held in Indonesia and abroad. To date, Usman and the research team have published more than 100 articles in national journals in Indonesia and reputable international journals indexed by Scopus, Google Scholar and others.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-12 19:50:02','2018-08-12 19:50:02',1),(252,35,20,'1534657393.jpg','Jose Luis da Silva Nunes','silva.nunes@ufrgs.br','','Department of Plant Science','Editorial board member','Brazil','BADESUL Development','33','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I am a graduate in Agronomy from the Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul (1998), a master&#39;s degree (completed in February 2003) and a Doctor (completed in February 2007) in Plant Sciences by the Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul. I participated in the research groups &quot;Plant Propagation Systems&quot;, coordinated by Professors Paulo Vitor Dutra de Souza and Otto Carlos Koller and certified by the Federal University of Rio Grande do Sul, &quot;Integrated Production of Fruit of Caro&ccedil;o&quot;, coordinated by Professors Jos&eacute; Carlos Fachinello and Gilmar Arduino Bettio Marodin and certified by the Federal University of Pelotas, and &quot;Fruticultura de Clima Temperado - Rootstock and certified seedlings&quot;, coordinated by Professor Jos&eacute; Carlos Fachinello and certified by the Federal University of Pelotas. I have experience in the field of Agronomy, with emphasis on Fruticulture of Perennial and Deciduous, working mainly on the following topics: integrated and conventional fruit production, soil management, plant management, pest and phytopathogen management, plant propagation and production of quality fruit seedlings through the use of arbuscular mycorrhizal fungi, identification and classification of arbuscular mycorrhizal fungi, classification and post-harvest of fruits. He served as a supervisory agent for the Cooperativa de Professionais do Agroneg&oacute;cios (PROCOOP), for the Cooperativa de Profissionais de Neg&oacute;cios (CAMP TEC) and as technical responsible for the Portal Agrolink, the company JOVAL and the company FORTESUL. He acts as technical consultant for the Portal Agrolink and is an employee of BADESUL Development, a development agency, acting as Development Technician - Agronomist - at the Agribusiness Superintendency.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-14 10:03:57','2018-08-19 11:13:12',1),(253,26,20,'1534306003.jpg','Thiago Andrade de Macedo','thiago.macedo@incor.usp.br','11 26615084','Doctorate in Cardiology from Faculty of Medicine','Editorial board member','Brazil','University of Sao Paulo','06','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Graduation in Medicine by the Federal University of Piau&iacute; (2002). Residency in Clinical Medicine.&nbsp; Institute of Assistance to the Public Servant of the State of S&atilde;o Paulo (2004-2006). Residency in Cardiology at the Heart Institute of the School of Medicine of the University of S&atilde;o Paulo - (FMUSP) - (2006-2008). Specialist in Cardiology by the Brazilian Society of Cardiology (2008). Specialist in Echocardiography&nbsp; by the Heart Institute - FMUSP (2011-2013) and by the Brazilian Society of Cardiology (2014). PhD in Cardiology, Faculty of Medicine, University of S&atilde;o Paulo (2012). Medical Coordinator of the Hospital TotalCor Emergency Service (2013-2014). American College of Cardiology Member (2014). Member of the Editorial Board of Scientific Periodicals: Clinical Updates of Cardiology&nbsp; and Medical and Clinical Research.&nbsp; Assistant&nbsp; Physician&nbsp; at the Hypertension Clinic Unit (InCor - HCFMUSP) and Collaborator at the Clinical Research Institute of the TotalCor&nbsp; Hospital,&nbsp; working&nbsp; in Secondary&nbsp; Hypertension,&nbsp; Echocardiography&nbsp; and Cardiac Emergencies.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-15 09:36:43','2018-08-15 09:36:43',1),(254,26,20,'1534306401.png','Alexander E. Berezin','aeberezin@gmail.com','+3806061006','Professor Chief of Cardiology Unit of Internal Medicine','Editorial board member','Ukraine','State Medical University','07','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Alexander E. Berezin received the MD degree from State Medical University, Zaporozhye, Ukraine, in 1992. PhD degree in field of Heart Failure was earned in State Medical University, Zaporozhye, Ukraine in 1994. He is currently Professor of Medicine, Chief of Cardiology Unit of Internal Medicine Department at State Medical University, Zaporozhye, Ukraine. He became a Member (M) the Ukrainian Cardiology Association in 1997; M of the Ukrainian Heart Failure Association in 2000; M of Heart Failure Association of the ESC in 2004; M of European Acute Cardiovascular Care Association in 2010; M of W.G. on Atherosclerosis and Vascular Biology of the ESC in 2010; M of European Association of Percutaneous Cardiovascular Interventions in 2012; M of European Association for Cardiovascular Prevention and Rehabilitation in 2012, M of W.G. on Hypertension &amp; the Heart of the ESC in 2012. From 2002 to 2012, he was Associate Professor at the Internal Medicine Department at State Medical University, Ukraine. His research interest includes the fundamental study of biological markers of cardiovascular diseases, the implementation of visualization procedures and percutaneous cardiovascular interventions, the development of cardiovascular prevention and rehabilitation, especially in the field affected heart failure and coronary artery disease, as well as regenerative medicine. Based on this research and fellowship training he has received several awards and honors, such as: Award of The Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine (2002), Honor of The Ukrainian Cardiology Association (2004). His previous publications are: 1. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA. Circulating osteopontin as a marker of early coronary vascular calcification in type two diabetes mellitus patients with known asymptomatic coronary artery disease. Atherosclerosis. 2013; 229: 475-481. 2. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA. Analysis of Various Subsets of Circulating Mononuclear Cells in Asymptomatic Coronary Artery Disease. J. Clin. Med. 2013, 2, 32-44. 3. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA. Bone-Related Circulating Proteins as Early Predictors of Coronary Atherosclerosis in Asymptomatic Patients with Known Coronary Artery Disease. Advanced Studies in Medical Sciences. 2013; 1 (4): 157 &ndash; 172 4. Berezin AE, Samura TA. Prognostic value of biological markers in myocardial infarction patients. Asian Cardiovascular and Thoracic Annals; 2013, 21(2): 142 &ndash; 150. 5. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA. Serum uric acid as a marker of coronary calcification in patients with asymptomatic coronary artery disease with preserved left ventricular pump function. Cardiology Research and Practice. 2013, Article ID 129369, 7 pages, http://dx.doi.org/10.1155/2013/129369. 6. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA, Samura T.A., Martovitskaya Yu.V. Association between Circulating Galectin-3 and Proangiogenic Mononuclear Progenitor Cells in Chronic Heart Failure Patients. JCvD. &ndash; 2014 [in press] 7. Berezin AE, Lisovaya OA. C-reactive protein in arterial hypertension after stroke. Asian Cardiovascular and Thoracic Annals; 2013 [in press]. October 29, 2013, doi: 10.1177/0218492313501163 8. Berezin AE, Kremzer AA, Samura T.A., Martovitskaya Yu.V. Circulating Endothelial-Derived Apoptotic Microparticles in the Patients with Ischemic Symptomatic Chronic Heart Failure: Relevance of Pro-Inflammatory Activation and Outcomes. Int Cardiovasc Res J.2014;8(3): [before print] 9. Berezin AE, Lisovaya OA. Predictive Value of Circulating Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor-1 in Arterial Hypertension Patients. Intern Med S. 2014; 11: 2-10. 10. Berezin AE. The Concept of Cell Therapy in Advanced Heart Failure: New Reality, Hope or Hype. Journal of Cardiology and Therapy. 2014; 1(3): 52-57. He is current Editor-in-Chief of Biological Markers and Guided Therapy. He is serving as an editorial member of several reputed journals like Ukranian Medical J, J Cardiology and Therapy (since 2013), Case Reports in Internal Medicine and expert Reviewers for journals like J Genetic Disorders and Genetic Reports; Obesity; Eur. J Clinical Investigations; J Food Science and Engineering; Case Reports in Internal Medicine; Diabetes, Metabolic Syndrome and Obesity: Targets and Therapy; British Journal of Medicine and Medical Research; Biomarkers in Medicine; Pediatrics &amp; Therapeutics; Journal of Vascular Medicine &amp; Surgery; Journal of Pain &amp; Relief; Cardiology and Angiology: An International Journal; Journal of Multiple Sclerosis; Journal of Clinical Case Reports; Journal of Haematology &amp; Thromboembolic Diseases, Acta Biochimica et Biophysica Sinica; Journal of Gerontology &amp; Geriatrics Research; Cloning &amp; Transgenesis.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Coronary artery disease, Heart Failure, Atherosclerosis Hypertension, Prognosis, Biological Markers, Comorbidities, Metabolic disorders, Visualization procedures, Cardiovascular Prevention and Rehabilitation, and Vascular Biology</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-15 09:43:21','2018-08-15 09:43:21',1),(255,24,20,'1534306897.jpg','Hong Wan','h.wan@qmul.ac.uk','0044 207 882 7139',' Immunobiology and Regenerative Medicine, Institute of Dentistry','Editorial board member','United Kingdom','Barts and The London School of Medicine and Dentistry','04','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr Hong Wan is a non-clinical senior lecturer in the Centre for Immunobiology and Regenerative Medicine, Institute of Dentistry, Barts and The London School of Medicine and Dentistry (SMD). Dr Wan&rsquo;s interest is focused on intercellular junctions of epithelia in health and disease. She initially worked on tight junction in pulmonary epithelial cells and its inhibitory role in the antigen presentation of house dust mite in asthma, and then she joined a dermatological team at St John&rsquo;s Institute of Dermatology, St Thomas&rsquo; Hospital working on hereditary skin disorders caused by defects in the desmosome genes. Finally, she moves to current centre focusing on cadherin signalling, in particular the desmosomal cadherin desmoglein-3 and its associated skin diseases, pemphigus and cancer.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-15 09:51:36','2018-08-21 21:02:39',1),(256,24,20,'1534307240.jpg','Farid Menaa','dr.fmenaa@gmail.com','','Professor, Director and Independent Consultant,Departments of Internal Medicine and Nanomedicine','Editorial board member','USA','California Innovations Corporation','001','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Farid Menaa is an inter- and multi-disciplinary professional with worldwide reputation. He has three international post-doctoral terms in Oncology, Dermatology, and Hematology; MBA Entrepreneurship and MD candidate. During his ongoing career, he has mainly contributed to the identification and functions of new human disease-causing genes and variants, formulated natural products for anti-aging and developed innovative theranostic strategies against cancers, cardiovascular diseases, diabetes, obesity and infectious diseases. He has more than 10 years&rsquo; experiences either in the academic, hospitals or industrial sectors. As Chief Scientific Officer and Vice-President R&amp;D at Fluorotronics, Inc. he actively participated in the development of the disruptive &ldquo;Carbon-Fluorine Spectroscopy&rdquo;. Dr. Menaa collaborates with various organizations worldwide. He is a member of several prestigious medical and scientific organizations and editorial boards in the field of medicine, science, technology and business, including in the nano-segment. He has authored more than 100 articles including research and review articles, books, book chapters, textbooks, proceedings, and has participated to over 200 scientific international events including as co-organizer, keynote speaker, chairman. Dr. Menaa&rsquo;s worldwide collaborations, holistic point of view and strong expertise in various fields led him to prevent, implement early diagnosis, and develop efficient and safer therapy.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Farid Menaa&rsquo;s research interest includes Preventive Medicine, Personalized Medicine, Translational Medicine, Integrative Medicine, Green Medicine, Nanomedicine, Biotechnology, and Nanotechnology. </span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-15 09:57:19','2018-08-19 09:13:25',1),(257,23,20,'1534307730.jpg','Michal Bartoszcze','mabarto@mx.within.pl','48 601215106','Professor','Editorial board member','Poland','Biological Threats Identification and Countermeasure Center of MIHE','07','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Education and Degrees: Graduated from Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, University School of Agriculture, Lublin, (Vet.Surg., 1966); doctor of veterinary sciences at the Agricultural-Technical University, Olsztyn ( Ph. D , 1974); doctor habilitatus (Assist. Prof., 1982); Assoc. Prof of MIHE (1997), Professor 2007.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Carrier: assistant at the Dept. of Virology, Veterinary Institute, Pu?awy (1966-1970); sr. assistant and adjunct at the Military Research Centre of Veterinary Services, Pu?awy ( ONBSW, 1970-1975); head of the Sanitary Epidemiological Laboratory, UNEF, Egypt (1975); head of Dept. of Microbiology and Epizootiology at ONBSW, Pu?awy (1976-1985); commandant of the Military Research Centre of Veterinary Service, Pu?awy (1985-89); deputy commandant of MIHE and head of ONBSW (1989-2002); deputy director of MIHE and head of Biological Threat Identification and Countermeasure Centre, Pu?awy (from 2002 &ndash; 2011, 2012 - professor of MIHE, invited lecturer at the University of Lublin.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Professional activity: initiator of research collaboration of MIHE and the US Army institutions (since 1996 technical project officer for the US-Poland Master Information Exchange Agreement); principal designer of the Army defence system against biological weapons; co-organizer of the first in Poland BSL-3 laboratory; co-director of the NATO Workshop of Advanced Technologies ( organised for the first time in Poland in 1997 ); co-organizer of the meeting of the FHTV COMEDS NATO panel and a number of local and international scientific conferences.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Publications (research interest): over 200 original and review papers on rapid methods of detection of biological agents, epidemiology, molecular biology, microbial genetics, bacterial resistance, virology, zoonoses, immunology, eradication of infectious diseases, ecology of microorganisms, new vaccines,&nbsp; modern treatment of infectious diseases and on countering biothreats.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-15 10:05:30','2018-08-15 10:05:30',1),(258,15,20,'1534309145.jpg','Fabio Antonio Piola Rizzante','fap17@case.edu','','Assistant Professor; Department of Restorative Dentistry','Editorial board member','USA','Case Western Reserve University - School of Dental Medicine','22','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Fabio Rizzante received his DDS in 2012 from Bauru School of Dentistry&ndash;University of Sao Paulo, Brazil. At the same school, he completed his Master&rsquo;s Degree in Operative Dentistry (2015) and PhD in Restorative Dentistry (2018). After dental school, Dr. Rizzante got advanced training in Periodontics and Implant Dentistry and start to lecture in undergraduate and advanced education programs focusing in Operative/Restorative Dentistry and Dental Materials. In 2016, Dr. Rizzante went to the University of Michigan as a Research Scholar in the BMS department and started to teach part-time in the same department in 2017. In August of 2017, Dr. Rizzante joined the department of Comprehensive Care at the School of Dental Medicine-Case Western Reserve University as a full-time Assistant Professor.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research interests:</span></strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Rizzante&rsquo;s current research interests include the evaluation of direct and indirect restorations, as well as the application of new digital technologies to improve quality and workflow of dental procedures.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-15 10:29:04','2018-09-04 22:39:47',1),(259,29,20,'1534309711.jpeg','Nihar Nikhilesh Shah','shahniharn@gmail.com','(973)204-4773','Assistant Professor of Medicine; Section of Gastroenterology and Hepatology','Editorial board member','USA','Joan C. Edwards School of Medicine at Marshall University','001','',1,'2018-08-15 10:38:31','2018-08-15 10:38:31',1),(260,25,20,'1534430278.gif','Helene Santos Barbosa','helenes.bar@gmail.com','','Senior researcher ','Editorial board member','Brazil','Oswaldo Cruz Foundation','09','',1,'2018-08-16 20:07:57','2018-08-16 20:07:57',1),(261,25,20,'1534430873.jpg','Daniela R. Recchia','daniela_recchia@yahoo.com.br','','Faculty of Health Sciences','Editorial board member','Germany','(University of Witten/Herdecke','10','',1,'2018-08-16 20:17:56','2018-08-16 20:17:56',1),(262,29,20,'1534431333.jpg','Kexin Liu','kexinliu@dlmedu.edu.cn','86-411-86110407','Department of Clinical Pharmacology','Editorial board member','China','Dalian Medical University','06','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Kexin Liu received his B.S. degree in Clinical Medicine and M.S. degree in Pharmacology from Dalian medical University in China and Ph. D. degree in Pharmacy in The University of Tokyo (Laboratory of Yuichi Sugiyama, Department of Pharmaceutics, Faculty of Pharmaceutical Sciences) in Japan. The focus of his research is on the molecular pharmacokinetics of transport in liver, intestine, kidney as well as transporter-mediated DDI and MDR.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&nbsp;Prof. Kexin Liu is a co-author of more than 250 publications in international journals and a first or corresponding author in the famous journals such as Hepatology, Biochem Pharmacol, Drug Metab Dispos, J Pharmacol Exp Ther, Am J Physiol, Pharm Res, Toxical Appl Pharm, Eur J Pharm Sci and 50 book chapters as well as 30 review articles. He serves as a vice president of CSSX from 2005 and a dean in College of Pharmacy in Dalian Medical University from 2004.2-2015</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-16 20:25:32','2018-08-16 20:25:32',1),(263,29,20,'1534431645.jpg','Chia-tung shun','ctshun@ntu.edu.tw','011-886-223123456(65497)','Department and Institute of Forensic Medicine','Editorial board member','Taiwan','National Taiwan University','07','<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Chia-Tung Shun is professor in Department and Institute of Forensic Medicine in National Taiwan University in Taiwan. He has attended for many conferences and he has submitted many presentations in different backgrounds like Intragenic homozygous deletions of MTS1 gene in gastric cancer in Taiwan. Overexpression of MUC5 genes is associated with early post-operative metastasis in non-small-cell lung cancer.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Forensic Parthology, Pathology, Gastric cancer</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-16 20:30:44','2018-08-16 20:30:44',1),(264,33,20,'1534435306.jpg','Ahmed Ragab Gaber Ahmed','ragabb900@yahoo.com','','Associate Prof. Dr. of developmental and experimental biology, Division of Anatomy and Embryology, Zoology department, Faculty of Science','Editorial board member','Egypt','Beni-Suef University','09','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Ahmed RG received his Ph.D. in Developmental Biology from Beni-Suef University, Egypt. He received his research training as a visiting scholar at the Katholic University,Belgium.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is working as Associate Professor of developmental and experimental biology, Division of Anatomy and Embryology, Zoology department, Faculty of Science, Beni-Suef University, Egypt.He is specialist in of developmental neuroscience neurotoxicology, developmental neuroendocrinology, developmental biology and biochemical development. He has outstanding record of scientific and academic accomplishments with multiple research funding, numerous publications in highly prestigious journals and various presentations in both national and international conferences.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is a member of number of eminent societies, organizations and schools. He served as a scientific editors and reviewer for the national and international research institutions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">His publication: - Interna