national conference at Budapest, Hungary. The prestigious and rarest award from Research Society for Study of Diabetes in India also given me a cash prize travel award for presenting research paper at RSSDI Hyderabad. I have published 34 research papers in peer reviewed journals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research Interest: Diabetes mellitus, Immunology, Tissue engineering, pancreatic cells</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-16 21:39:49','2018-08-21 18:13:51',1),(266,33,20,'1534436145.jpg','Rohit  Sharma','dhanvantari86@gmail.com','9816724054','Research officer','Editorial board member','India','Central Ayurveda Research Institute for Drug Development,CCRAS','11','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Dr. Rohit Sharma (MD, Ph.D)</strong>, is Research officer (Ayu.), Central Ayurveda Research Institute for Drug Development, CCRAS, Ministry of AYUSH, Government of India, Kolkata. He did his post-graduation and doctorate from the Institute for Post Graduate Teaching &amp; Research in Ayurveda, Gujarat Ayurved University, Jamnagar. He has been the recipient of several academic awards and honors and has more than 100 International research publications, one book and few chapters in books to his credit. He is also the editorial board member and reviewer of 26 International Research Journals. He was the recipient of &ldquo;Gold medal&rdquo; awarded by Governor of Gujarat for achievements; and National level Awards &ldquo;INSA Young Historian of Science Award, 2015&rdquo; awarded by INDIAN NATIONAL SCIENCE ACADEMY and &ldquo;Young Scientist Award&rdquo; by Education Expo TV (EET) CRS. Dr. Sharma is working on various aspects of herbal/herbo-mineral drug research, drug development, pharmacovigilance and engaged in various clinical research trials.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-16 21:45:45','2018-08-16 21:45:45',1),(267,24,20,'1534650502.jpg','Alireza Heidari','Alireza.Heidari@ca