e achievement award; from 2016 was awarded the health care &amp; biotechnology merit award.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:#00b050\">Research Interest:</span></em></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Pharmacognosy,<a href=\"https://www.omicsonline.org/scholarly/cell-therapy-products-journals-articles-ppts-list.php\">&nbsp;Natural Product Research</a>, Chinese Medicine, Pharmacy</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-23 10:22:23','2018-08-23 10:26:17',1),(278,29,20,'1535000526.png','Dimitrios Filippou','d_filippou@hotmail.com','30.6944287125','Chief of Laparoscopi Surgery and Surgical Oncology','Editorial board member','Greece','Neo Athinaio Hospital','11','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Dimitrios K. Filippou studied medicine in Athens University Medical School and then surgery in various Athens Oncological and General Hospitals and in Hospital Cantonal de Fribourg in Switzerland. He was appointed as Chief of the Department of Laparoscopic Surgery, Surgical Oncology in Neo-Athinaio MD Hospital in Athens, Greece and also Responsible for the Department for Laser Applications. He worked as doctoral researcher in the Dept. of Physiology in Athens University Medical School. In his doctoral thesis studied the oxidants and antioxidant status and alterations in burned patients. His educational experience in pre- and postgraduate level includes teaching and laboratory exercises in various educational objects including anatomy, physiology, sport medicine, hygiene, surgical anatomy etc. He owns more than 90 publications in International Journal and he has written, translated or contributed in more than 30 medical books. He translated many Medical Books for Greek Medical Schools. He has contributed in a large number of congresses and symposiums with lectures, presentations and round tables. He also serves as Editor or Reviewer in many International Journals.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-23 10:32:06','2018-08-23 10:35:53',1),(279,26,20,'1535437005.jpg','Indranil Dasgupta','indranildasgupta@aol.com','(215) 955-5050','Assistant Professor','Editorial board member','USA','Jefferson University','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Dasgupta has been Clinical Assistant Professor of Medicine at Jefferson Medical College and a member of the Thomas Jefferson University Hospital Heart Institute in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania since 2002. He specializes in Clinical Cardiovascular Disease and is part of the Adjunct Faculty Vascular Biology Working Group at the University of Florida School of Medicine. He graduated from the St. George&#39;s University School of Medicine in 1994, after receiving his MPH-International Health from Loma Linda University in 1987 and his MBA-Finance from George Washington University in 1989. In addition to completing his Cardiology Fellowship at Robert Wood Johnson Medical School of the University of Medicine and Dentistry of New Jersey, serving as Chief in his final year, Dr. Dasgupta completed a Fellowship in Geriatric Medicine, MCP-Hahnemann University.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Dasgupta&rsquo;s research interests include: Heart disease in older women and management of mitral valve disease in older adults.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-28 11:46:44','2018-08-28 11:46:44',1),(280,18,20,'1535438030.jpg','Helena Isabel da Silva Reis','helenaisabelsilvareis@gmail.com','','lecturer in Occupational Therapy','Editorial board member','Portugal','The Polytechnic Institute of Leiria, School of Health Sciences','13','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Helena Isabel da Silva Reis is a lecturer in Occupational Therapy at the Polytechnic Institute of Leiria, at the School of Health Sciences.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Helena has completed her PhD in Child Studies at the Institute of Education of the University of Minho, in July 2014; she is also a Clinical Specialist in Therapy and Rehabilitation - Occupational Therapy since December 2014 and completed an MSc in Early Intervention, focusing in Special Education by the Institute of Child Studies at the University of Minho since January 2009.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Helena has also completed a Postgraduate degree course in &quot;Sensory Integration - 1st edition&quot; by the Cooperative of Higher Education and University Polytechnic (CESPU) in February 2015. Specialised in the area of &quot;Sensory Integration&quot; by USC / WPS including administration and interpretation of the Sensory Integration and Praxis Test (SIPT) from January to October 2009.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Helena has started teaching in 2010 at CESPU and in 2011 she was invited to teach modules of the 3rd year of the Degree of Occupational Therapy at the Higher Health Institute of Alto Ave (ISAVE).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Most of her clinical practice was based in an early intervention team specialised in Developmental and Autism Spectrum disorders, from September 2003 to February 2017. She also worked in private pediatric clinics alongside of her work in the Association for Developmental Disorders and Autism (APPDA). Helena has scientific publications in international journals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">She is currently involved in the project for the validation of the Sensory Processing Measure -Pre-school, Sensory Processing Measure - Preschool (SPM-P), in the School and Home versions by the CiTechCare Research Unit. Helena is also involved in the international project by the University of Minho: &quot;Intervention with children with Autism Spectrum Disorder: a Luso-Brazilian proposal&quot; under the bilateral agreement FCT-CAPES.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Helena has reviewed a variety of peer reviewed publications including the Journal of Early Intervention and Autism and Developmental Language Impairments. She has undertaken a range of specialisation courses in Autism Spectrum Disorders and attended conferences as a guest speaker in this field.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-08-28 12:00:58','2018-08-28 12:03:50',1),(281,31,20,'1535444454.jpg','Guillermo F. Lopez Sanchez','gfls@um.es','868 888 671','Assistant Professor,Physical Activity and Sport','Editorial board member','Spain','University of Murcia','08','',1,'2018-08-28 13:50:53','2018-08-28 13:50:53',1),(282,31,20,'1535449861.jpg','Arturo Diaz Suarez','ardiaz@um.es','','Professor, Faculty of Sport Sciences','Editorial board member','Spain','University of Murcia','09','',1,'2018-08-28 15:21:01','2018-08-28 15:21:01',1),(283,30,20,'1535450152.jpg','Teodora Daneva ','danevadoki@abv.bg','','Faculty of Biology of Sofia University','Editorial board member','Bulgaria','Institute of Biology and Immunology of Reproduction','13','',1,'2018-08-28 15:25:51','2018-08-28 15:25:51',1),(284,25,20,'1535997623.jpg','Alisan Kahraman','alisan.kahraman@uk-essen.de','+49-201-72384797','Department of Gastroenterology & Hepatology','Editorial board member','Germany','University Hospital of Essen','09','',1,'2018-09-03 23:30:26','2018-09-04 00:14:13',1),(285,29,20,'1536000141.jpeg','Tsvetelina Velikova','tsvelikova@medfac.mu-sofia.bg','','Assistant professor Department of Clinical Laboratory and Clinical Immunology','Editorial board member','Bulgaria','Medical University of Sofia','12','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Tsvetelina Velikova is an Assistant professor at Department of Clinical Laboratory and Clinical Immunology, Medical University of Sofia and Medica