omalies ,from 2012 till now.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is reviewer for International Arab Journal of Dentistry (IAJD), Advisory Board Member for Annals of International Medical and Dental Research and Associate editor in Journal of Dental Health, Oral Disorders and Therapy and member of the Editorial Board&nbsp; for Advances in dentistry and Oral Health Journal.(Juniper Publishers.com)and Editorial board Member for EC Dental Science Journal,(www.ecronicon.com).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&nbsp;He is member of European association of Cranio-Maxillo-Facial Surgeons, Egyptian Cancer Society, Egyptian Association of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery, Pan-Arab Association of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeons, International Cleft Lip and Palate Foundation etc. He is Chairman of the Alexandria Club of Cranio-Maxillofacial, Oral and Plastic Surgery. He is member of Egyptian Dental Association, Alexandria Oral Implantology Association (AOIA). He has published several scientific papers in International peer reviewed journals. He attended so many conferences in Egypt and in Saudi Arabia. All fields of Craniomaxillofacial, Oral, and Plastic Surgery especially: Cleft Lip and Palate; Craniofacial Anomalies; Craniomaxillofacial and mandbular trauma; Temporomandibular joint; trauma, ankylosis, and Disorders; Distraction osteogenesis; Mandibular, craniofacial,and midface, including transport distraction osteogenesis; Oral surgical procedures, under local and general anesthesia; Craionmaxillofacial, oral, and mandibular tumor; resection and reconstruction; Head and neck tumors.Web and Maxillofacial Surgeons, International Cleft Lip and Palate Foundation etc. He is Chairman of the Alexandria Club of Cranio-Maxillofacial, Oral and Plastic Surgery. He is member of Egyptian Dental Association, Alexandria Oral Implantology Association (AOIA). He has published several scientific papers in International peer reviewed journals. He attended so many conferences in Egypt ,in Saudi Arabia and in Europe.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-09-18 14:19:09','2018-09-18 14:21:31',1),(305,26,20,'1537857763.jpg','Maria Luz Gunturiz','mgunturiz@ins.gov.co','','Scientific researcher','Editorial board member','USA',' National Institute of Health, Bogota, Colombia','03','',1,'2018-09-25 12:11:19','2018-09-25 12:13:11',1),(306,23,20,'1537858312.jpg','A. C. Matin','amatin@stanford.edu','(650) 725-4745','Professor of Microbiology & Immunology','Editorial board member','USA','Stanford University School of Medicine','01','<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. A.C. Matin got his Ph.D from University of California in Microbiology (1969). He is serving as the Chair of MS senate task force on posdoctoral affairs (2009- present), Member of MS senate steering committee (2008-present) &amp; Senator of Medical School senate (2006-present). He is a Fellow of the American Academy of Microbiology. He got 16 Honors and Awards which are Star Award in Environmental Protection Agency (1991-1997), Review Committee Member in Accreditation Board for Engineering and Technology (1992) and Foundation for Microbiology Lecturer in American Society for Microbiology (1991-1993). He has authored about 37 Publications that include review articles. His Community &amp; International Work involved in Bacterial antibiotic resistance in space flight, Stanford University; NASA Ames and Nuclear waste remediation.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research Interest:</strong></em></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Cancer research,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.omicsonline.org/scholarly/bioprocess-engineering-journals-articles-ppts-list.php\">biomolecualr engineering</a>, biofilms, cellular resistance and virulence, biology of low shear/microgravity, bioremediation, stress promoters, stress sensing,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.omicsonline.org/scholarly/bioprocess-and-systems-engineering-journals-articles-ppts-list.php\">systems biology</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.omicsonline.org/scholarly/pharmaceutical-bioprocessing-journals-articles-ppts-list.php\">biotechnology</a>.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-09-25 12:21:52','2018-09-25 12:21:52',1),(307,22,20,'1538021036.jpg','Evija Stumbra Stumberga','evijastumbra@inbox.lv','','Consultant in rheumatology','Editorial board member','Europe','Riga Stradins University','03','<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Evija Stumbra Stumberga is a consultant rheumatologist, neurosonologist and internal medicine specialist. She has completed her postdoctoral studies in the Riga Stradin&rsquo;s University. She has graduated the residency of internal medicine and rheumatology. She participated in the &acute;Erasmus Exchange Program&acute; in the Whytenshaw Hospital, Rheumatology Department, Manchester, United Kingdom in 2011.She has got the AAS degree and had courses in Internal Medicine in Salzburg. She has been specialized in neurosonology, worked as a neurosonologist. She has got the DAAD degree in 2013 and has been worked in the Stroke Unit, Neurosonology department in the Neurologisches Zentrum der Segeberger Kliniken Gruppe in Bad Segeberg, Germany. She has published clinical and research works concerning rheumatoid arthritis and atherosclerosis in reputed journals and has been served as an editorial board member of repute.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-09-27 09:33:56','2018-09-27 09:33:56',1),(308,31,20,'1538021554.jpg','Robert C Cantu','RCantu@emersonhosp.org','978-369-1386','Director, Service of Sports Medicine','Editorial board member','USA','Dr. Robert C. Cantu Concussion Center','00','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Robert Cantu is a Clinical Professor in the Department of Neurology and Neurosurgery, Clinical Diagnostics and Therapeutics Leader AD and CTE Center, at the Boston University School of Medicine, and Medical Director and Director of Clinical Research, Dr. Robert C. Cantu Concussion Center, Emerson Hospital.&nbsp; He has authored over 436 scientific publications, including 33 books on neurology and sports medicine, in addition to numerous book chapters, peer-reviewed papers, abstracts and free communications, and educational videos. He is section editor for World Neurosurgery and he has served as associate editor of Medicine and Science in Sports and Exercise and Exercise and Sports Science Review, and on the editorial board of The Physician and Sports Medicine, Clinical Journal of Sports Medicine, and Journal of Athletic Training.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr, Cantu serves as Senior Advisor to the NFL Head, Neck and Spine Committee; Section Co-Chair Mackey-White National Football League Players Association Traumatic Brain Injury Committee;&nbsp; Founding member and Medical Director Concussion Legacy Foundation (previously SLI); International Rugby Board Concussion Advisory Group; Adjunct Professor Exercise and Sport Science and Medical Director National Center for Catastrophic Sports Injury Research, University of North Carolina, Chapel Hill, NC; Senior Advisor Brain Injury Center and Adjunct Staff, Children&rsquo;s Hospital, Boston,&nbsp; Vice President Chair Scientific Advisory Committee National Operating Committee on Standards for Athletic Equipment (NOCSAE), Chief of Neurosurgery Service, and Director of Sports Medicine at Emerson Hospital in Concord, Massachusetts.&nbsp;&nbsp; He also consults with numerous NFL, NHL and NBA teams.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-09-27 09:42:34','2018-09-27 09:42:57',1),(309,23,20,'1538022127.jpg','Ashraf Abdelsalam Mohamedei Metwally','ashraf.elmetwally@gmail.com','966594800755','ASSOCIATE PROFESSOR AND CONSULTANT OF EPIDEMIOLOGY AND BIOSTATISTICS','Editorial board member','United Arab Emirates','King Saud Bin Abdulaziz University for Health Sciences','08','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Ashraf El-Metwally is an internationally recognized medical doctor and scientist with a PhD in Epidemiology and Biostatistics (from University of Tampere, Finland). He is best known as a docent of Epidemiology in the University of Tampere (Finland). After completion of his degree, he was appointed as an epidemiologist at the Rheumatism Foundation Hospital in Finland from 2003-2005. In 2006, Dr. Ashraf El-Metwally joined as a Lecturer in the Department of Epidemiology and Bio-statistics at University of Aberdeen, UK. He also served as a Faculty in Health Sciences, Higher Colleges of Technology, Sharjah, UAE from 2008-2011.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He was then appointed as an assistant professor in the Department of Epidemiology and Biostatistics in 2011, while holding an honorary lecturer position at the department of Public Health-University of Aberdeen in the UK.&nbsp; Dr. Ashraf El-Metwally has supervised more than 20 MPH projects. He now serves as an Associate Professor and Director of MPH Epidemiology Program at the College of Public Health and Health Informatics, King Saud Bin Abdulaziz University for Health Sciences, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. Dr. Ashraf is also a renowned qualified instructor in Public health sciences, at the University of Roehampton, UK.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">His research experience focuses on clinical trials, systematic reviews, meta-analysis, cross sectional studies, with scientific interest in wide range of topics such as pain, musculoskeletal disorders, rheumatic diseases, dental disorders, digital health research, communicable &amp; non-communicable diseases and Alternative medicine. Dr Ashraf has published more than 60 research articles in prominent peer reviewed international journals, presented papers in many national and international conferences, and has co-authored two books, five book chapters, and commenced several grant funded research projects.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Currently, Dr. Ashraf El-Metwally is an active member of Editorial Board and review committees of several international medical journals including European Journal of Pain, Primary Care Epidemiology and Global Health &amp; Annuals of Rheumatic Diseases. He is also an &ldquo;Editor in chief&rdquo; of the Journal of Health Informatics in Developing Countries.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Ashraf El-Metwally&rsquo;s research contribution and proficient research publications are all testaments of his extraordinary talents that can be evidenced by more than 1000 google scholars citation, the quality of the published articles; that has earned him multiple and&nbsp; pioneering awards (most notably from British pain society - Young Investigator Award (2006) and First Prize for The Best Submitted Paper and Presentation (2007) from British society of rheumatology), as well as membership with reputable research and public health organizations, which named him one of the &ldquo;Most Influential People in the World&rdquo; in Marquis Who&rsquo;s Who -2009.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-09-27 09:52:06','2018-09-27 09:52:06',1),(310,20,20,'1538378786.jpg','Jiulin Wang','WangJ@macewan.ca','780-497-4747','Assistant Professor','Editorial board member','Canada','Grant MacEwan University','11','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Jiulin Wang has both MD. and MSc. Degrees in TCM from Nanjing University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, where he was also a faculty member. He has taught TCM/Acupuncture in many famous TCM universities from China, US, and Canada. Currently, Dr. Jiulin Wang is an assistant professor of the Acupuncture Program at Grant MacEwan University. He is also a founding member of Bethune Oriental Medicine Center, where he provides private TCM/Acupuncture service to the public. Dr. Jiulin Wang is dedicated to biomedical research. He finished two terms of post-doctoral fellowship training in the Neuroscience Department of Louisiana State University and Oregon Health Science University, USA. He has partnered with the Pulmonary Research Centre, University of Alberta, to finish an Acupuncture research project on COPD. He has published more than 30 professional papers and books.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Since 2001, Jiulin has been an active member of the Acupuncture and TCM profession in Alberta. In the Acupuncture-TCM Society of Alberta (ASA), he was an executive and also secretary. Since 2007, he has served as the CAAA interim council. In 2010, 2012 and 2014, he was elected as a CAAA council member, serving as secretary and treasurer separately. He works closely with other council members to promote TCM/Acupuncture profession in Alberta.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-01 12:56:25','2018-10-01 12:57:43',1),(311,20,20,'1538379224.jpg','Soren Ventegodt','ventegodt@livskvalitet.org','45 20 66 67 66','Director ','Editorial board member','Denmark','Quality of Life Research Center','12','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Soren Ventegodt was born in 1961. His father was a historian specialised in maritime history and co-editor of the large Gyldendal Danish Encyclopaedia, his mother a nurse with a master degree in French. When S&oslash;ren was 10 years old his younger brother Jesper died in a terrible drowning accident, which awakened S&oslash;ren&rsquo;s spiritually and he soon became interested in philosophy, science, sport and arts. At age 11 years, he started to write poetry, play music and read books on chemistry and at age 13 years he had his own chemistry lab in the family basement, which he continued to develop though his teenage years.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Gifted with a special talent for science he entered the University of Copenhagen at age 18 years and after studying chemistry, philosophy and finally medicine, he entered the research field of theoretical biology. During his last years at the university he developed a highly controversial theory of quality of life (QOL) and the state of consciousness as the primal factors causing disease including cancer. His research in quality of life soon became popular with the general public and in 1992 the Pharmacist Foundation of 1991 awarded him, while still a medical student, a grant of 600,000 Euro for his research in quality of life and health. The University Hospital in Copenhagen (Rigshospitalet) and the late pediatric professor Bengt Zachau-Christiansen helped him to establish the Quality of Life Survey using the Copenhagen Perinatal Birth Cohort 1959-61 as the sample for the research. This way the Quality of Life Research Center (QOLRC) was established in 1993 at the University Hospital. In 1994 this institution became one of the first independent QOL Research Centers in Northern Europe and moved to its present location in the center of old Copenhagen with S&oslash;ren as its director.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In 1997 the Research Clinic for Holistic Medicine was established. More than 200 peer reviewed scientific papers have now been published, making the QOLRC one of the worlds most productive centres of new medical knowledge in the field of clinical holistic medicine &ndash; &ldquo;quality of life as medicine&rdquo;. In 2003 the Scandinavian Research Institute for Working Life Quality (NFA) was established in Oslo, Norway based on the ideas, books and materials produced by Soren Ventegodt. In 2004 the Nordic School of Holistic Medicine was established at the QOLRC. He also participated in establishing the International Society for Holistic Health (ISHH) in 2004. In 2006 he became director of Nordic Campus, Interuniversity College, Graz.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Soren Ventegodt is today the author of more than 10 popular books (some of them best sellers) and hundreds of papers and articles in magazines and scientific journals. He is often used as a speaker on QOL and holistic health throughout the Nordic countries. Through more than 1,000 presentations and lectures at most of the universities and large companies in Denmark he has made 100,000 Danes understand the fundamental quality of life concepts. After more than 1,000 presentations in the national medias, from the nine a clock news to national TV- and radio programs and the front pages of the leading news papers during the past 14 years, the Danish society at large now seems to have assimilated the key message: that you can improve your QOL and thus prevent disease and even improve your health and ability if you are sick, unhappy or poorly functioning.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-01 13:03:43','2018-10-01 13:03:43',1),(312,35,20,'1541854643.jpg','Zhao Zhang','zhangzhao@bnu.edu.cn','86-10-58800409','Professor,Department of Life and Environment Sciences','Editorial board member','China','Beijing Normal University','38','',1,'2018-10-02 20:15:12','2018-11-10 18:27:22',1),(313,25,20,'1538492019.png','John McManus','JMCMANUS@augusta.edu','(210) 240-6995','Professor & EMS Fellowship Director','Editorial board member','USA','Augusta University','04','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">COL (ret) John G. McManus retired in 2012 from the United States Army with a combined Federal service record of over 24 years as a Medical Corps Officer and decorated combat veteran. After graduating from North Georgia Senior Military College in 1988 with a B.S. in chemistry on a full National Guard Scholarship, Dr. McManus attended his M.D. training at the Medical College of Georgia, (Augusta University) serving as student government president his final year in 1992. He then completed a 4 year emergency medicine residency in 1999 at Madigan Army Medical Center and University of Washington, an EMS fellowship at Oregon Health and Sciences University and a Master Degree in Clinical Research. Furthermore, he received his MBA in July 2012 from Brenau University. Dr. McManus served on active duty in numerous leadership assignments and deployments (Bosnia, Kuwait, Iraq) throughout the world. He had the honor to serve as the Chief Medical Officer of the last Combat Support Hospital (47th CSH) in Baghdad Iraq in 2011. His other prior leadership assignments include: Director for the U.S. Army&rsquo;s EMS Department and also the Director for the Center of Pre-deployment Medicine, at the U.S. Army Medical Department Center and School, Fort Sam Houston, Texas (equivalent to Associate Deans). Dr. McManus also founded and served as the inaugural program director for three EMS fellowship programs: the U.S. Army&#39;s first emergency medicine subspecialty fellowship, at the San Antonio Military Medical Center (2007-11), the University of Texas Health Science Center San Antonio (2010-11) and currently at Augusta University (2013-present). He also currently serves as a professor and EMS Fellowship Director in the Department of emergency medicine at Augusta University and the Region 6 EMS Medical Director. Dr. McManus serves as medical director for Southstar EMS and Georgia Bureau of Investigation. He is also the the current Speaker for the national emergency medical society ACEP (American College of Emergency Physicians).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">COL (ret) McManus is a physician executive that possesses extensive and progressively responsible experience that provided clinical leadership and medical management in both the Department of Defense and civilian medical community. He possesses a thorough understanding of academic and research development practices, clinical training as well as deployment logistics for medical devices and products. His research focus included trauma and combat casualty care research at the U.S. Army Institute of Surgical Research and in Iraq and Afghanistan focusing on pre-hospital, disaster and critical care medicine. He is an internationally recognized researcher and speaker with over 500 presentations and accomplished author of over 100 (50 peer) scientific publications to include editor of 5 medical textbooks. He has developed medical educational experiences for 1000&rsquo;s of medical personnel for the military and ACGME. Just a few of his numerous awards include: the Legion of Merit, the National Emergency Medicine teaching award and the outstanding Army Medical Department LTC of the year by the U.S. Army Surgeon General in 2006.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is the father of 7 year-old twins Aedan and Aoife (pronounced &ldquo;eefa&rdquo; &ndash; it&rsquo;s Gaelic)</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-02 20:23:42','2018-10-02 20:23:42',1),(314,31,20,'1538637652.jpg','David N. Taylor','dtaylor@txchiro.edu','281-998-5718','Associate Professor of Clinical Science','Editorial board member','USA','Texas Chiropractic College','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. David Taylor obtained his DC degree from National University of Health Sciences. Neurology Residency at Logan College of Chiropractic, &amp; Diplomate from the American Board of Chiropractic Neurology. Awarded a Fellow from the International Academy of Chiropractic Neurology and the International College of Chiropractic Neurology, he currently is on the executive board.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He is the founder and president of Multimed Center, Inc, for 30 years.&nbsp; a multidisciplinary practice that employed chiropractors, anesthesiologist/pain specialists, physiatrist, osteopath, physical therapist, physical therapy assistants, massage therapists, acupuncturists, and psychologists. Dr. Taylor was also the president of Healthcare Review &amp; Consulting, Inc., a medicolegal consulting company, and the owner of Pioneer Neurodiagnostics, a neurological testing and consulting company. He was appointed by two governors to serve on the Massachusetts Board of Chiropractic Examiners. He has served on the board of directors of the Mass. Chiropractic Society, and as examiner and test evaluator for the National Board of Chiropractic Examiners. A fellow of the Federation of Chiropractic Licensing Boards, he also served Spine Managed Care as chairman of credentialing and quality improvement &amp; as consultant to many insurers. He has published numerous research papers in various peer reviewed journals and co-authored the text &ldquo;Chiropractic Hospital Privileges&rdquo; and lectured internationally. Past clinic director at Texas Chiropractic College, he currently is an associate professor of clinical sciences and continues to serve as adjunct professor of many other chiropractic colleges.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-04 12:50:52','2018-10-04 12:50:52',1),(315,26,20,'1538721334.jpg','Eirini Apostolidou','Eirini_Apostolidou@brown.edu','646-725-6835','Department of Medicine and Cardiovascular Disease','Editorial board member','USA','Lifespan Cardiovascular Institute','03','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I was born and raised in a small town in Greece, Kozani. I received my medical degree from the School of Medicine- Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, in Greece and graduated as a valedictorian. After moving to the United States in 2008, I worked as a research associate at the Center of Interventional Vascular Therapy at Columbia University Medical Center in New York. I completed my residency in internal medicine at Drexel College of Medicine/ Hahnemann University Hospital in Philadelphia and my cardiovascular fellowship at the Warren Alpert Medical School of Brown University. During my fellowship, I completed advanced training in echocardiography and concurrently enrolled in the Master of Science in Clinical and Translational Research at the School of Public Health, Brown University. I am board-certified in internal medicine, cardiovascular disease, echocardiography, nuclear cardiology and peripheral vascular imaging. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I joined the Cardiovascular Institute at Rhode Island and Miriam Hospitals on August 2016 as a noninvasive cardiologist and contribute to both inpatient and outpatient cardiac services. I am an Assistant Professor of medicine at the Warren Alpert Medical School of Brown University and I am actively involved in the teaching of fellows, residents and medical students. I received the Dean&rsquo;s Excellence in Teaching Award in 2017. My research focuses on cardiac imaging and novel techniques for treatment of valvular heart disease (transcatheter aortic valve replacement and mitral clip). My scientific work has been published in highly respected cardiology journals.&nbsp; I am a Fellow of the American College of Cardiology and I have been invited as an author in textbook chapters and educational material.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-05 12:05:33','2018-10-05 12:05:33',1),(316,24,20,'1538721699.jpg','Kexin Liu','kexinliu@dlmedu.edu.cn','86-411-86110407','Department of Clinical Pharmacology','Editorial board member','Japan','Dalian Medical University','06','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Kexin Liu received his B.S. degree in Clinical Medicine and M.S. degree in Pharmacology from Dalian medical University in China and Ph. D. degree in Pharmacy in The University of Tokyo (Laboratory of Yuichi Sugiyama, Department of Pharmaceutics, Faculty of Pharmaceutical Sciences) in Japan. The focus of his research is on the molecular pharmacokinetics of transport in liver, intestine, kidney as well as transporter-mediated DDI and MDR.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">&nbsp;Prof. Kexin Liu is a co-author of more than 250 publications in international journals and a first or corresponding author in the famous journals such as Hepatology, Biochem Pharmacol, Drug Metab Dispos, J Pharmacol Exp Ther, Am J Physiol, Pharm Res, Toxical Appl Pharm, Eur J Pharm Sci and 50 book chapters as well as 30 review articles. He serves as a vice president of CSSX from 2005 and a dean in College of Pharmacy in Dalian Medical University from 2004.2-2015</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-05 12:11:39','2018-10-05 12:11:39',1),(317,31,20,'1539009393.jpg','Michael Naafs','naafs.healthconsultancy@gmail.com','31681589079','Endocrinologist','Editorial board member','Netherlands','Naafs Health Consultancy','12','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Michael A.B. Naafs is a Dutch internist-endocrinologist with a long clinical career in internal medicine and endocrinology .</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">His Ph.D Endocrinology was obtained at Leiden University (1988) and focused on the renal end-organ resistance to PTH (Parathormone) infusion in normo-and hypercalcaemic patients with solid tumors secreting a PTH-like factor.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Other area&rsquo;s of interest are clinical&nbsp; pharmacology where he was in the front of clinical research&nbsp; of transdermal nitroglycerin patches.(1984) Recently he participated in the standard book project&nbsp; &ldquo;Drug Discovery and Evaluation: Methods in Clinical Pharmacolgy &ldquo;Eds Hock.F.J,Gralinski M.R&nbsp; 2nd Edition,,2017,Springer Verlag, providing the section &ldquo;Pharmacodynamic Evaluation: Endocrinology &ldquo;.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">In infectious medicine he was one of the first to report about HIV-2 infection (1990) Experience in HIV,MDRTB and&nbsp; tropical Infectious medicine was acquired during a one year stay at Nelson Mandela Academic Hospital,Umthata,South Africa.( 2008).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">At present he works as an independent health consultant (Naafs International Health Consultancy ) and as a Medical &nbsp;Writer. Michael is an editorial board member of a number open access journals and the author of tenfolds of publications.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-08 20:06:33','2018-10-08 20:06:33',1),(318,24,20,'1539631309.jpg','Luigi Laino','luigilaino@yahoo.it','','Professor','Editorial board member','Italy','LUMSA University','13','',1,'2018-10-16 00:51:49','2018-10-16 00:51:49',1),(319,31,20,'1539631634.jpg','Henry Heard','heard_hh@mercer.edu','770-886-8903','Clinical Assistant Professor, Physician Assistant Department','Editorial board member','Georgia','Mercer University','13','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">My name is Henry Heard, I am an Clinical Assistant Professor at the Mercer University Physician Assistant Program with five plus years in academia and 40 plus years as a clinician.&nbsp; I hold a doctor of health science degree, a master of physician assistant studies, a master of military study, a baccalaureate in physician assistant, and an associate in nursing degree.&nbsp; I practiced medicine as a physician assistant in orthopedic surgery for 15 years, primarily in sports medicine, total joint replacement, and general orthopedics.&nbsp; I have published several articles on orthopedic/sports medicine topics, have collaborated with colleagues in physical therapy to write ongoing continuing medical education products, and have recently presented at the Physician Assistants in Orthopedic Surgery annual meeting.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">My research interests lie not just in clinical orthopedic and physical therapy medicine but in finding ways to deliver better orthopedic care, increasing utilization of physician assistants in orthopedic care, and developing methods to allow patients better access to medical care.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-16 00:57:17','2018-10-16 00:57:17',1),(320,22,20,'1539757914.jpg','Kai Fu','kafu7690@uni.sydney.edu.au','61 0468476117','Department of Orthopaedics','Editorial board member','Australia','University of Sydney','03','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Kai Fu graduated from West China Medical School, Sichuan University in China and got MBBS degree in 2013. In 2016, he got the Master of Surgery in the Department of Orthopedics in Shanghai Jiao Tong University.&nbsp; Kai is now pursuing his PhD degree in The University of Sydney. His research is now focused on clinical research of osteoarthritis especially hip osteoarthritis pain; and also translational research in orthopaedic surgery area including hand surgery, joint replacement and spinal cord injury. Besides, Dr. Kai Fu is learning and doing many big data analysis using machine learning methods.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-17 12:01:29','2018-10-17 12:01:53',1),(321,31,20,'1539758128.jpg','Hironobu Ihn','ihn-der@kumamoto-u.ac.jp','','Vice President, Kumamoto University Hospital,Professor & Chairman, Department of Dermatology & PlasticSurgery, Faculty Life Sciences','Editorial board member','Japan','Kumamoto University','08','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Prof. Hironobu Ihn was born in 1964 at Kobe, Japan and graduated from University of Tokyo in 1990. He became assistant professor, Department of Dermatology, Faculty of Medicine, University of Tokyo in 1990, and worked as the research fellow in Division of Rheumatology &amp; Immunology, Medical University of South Carolina, SC, USA between 1994 and 1997. He worked as the lecturer, Department of Dermatology, Faculty of Medicine between 2001 and 2005 and became the associate Professor, Department of Dermatology, Faculty of Medicine, University of Tokyo. He was elected as the professor &amp; Chairman, Department of Dermatology &amp; Plastic Surgery, Faculty Life Sciences, Kumamoto University in 2005 and became the Vice President, Kumamoto University Hospital in 2013.<br />\r\nHe obtained Japanese Society of Connective Tissue Research Award in 2001, Japanese Society of Investigative Dermatology Award in 2005, and Japan Rheumatism Foundation Award in 2006.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research Interest:</strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Hair transplantion, Hair Loss in Women, Scarring Alopecia, Alopecia Areata.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-17 12:05:27','2018-10-17 12:08:20',1),(322,31,20,'1539758634.jpg','Sarwat Sultan','sarwatsultan@hotmail.com','','Chairperson,Department of Applied Psychology','Editorial board member','Pakistan','Bahauddin Zakariya University Multan','15','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Sarwat Sultan Chairperson, Department of Applied Psychology, Bahauddin Zakariya University Multan-Pakistan completed post doctorate from Curtin University, Australia in 2013. She has 85 research publications; 80 oral presentations in conferences, one book published in Germany to her credit and has supervised more than 300 dissertations. She is a distinguished teacher having experience of 15 years. She is also the HEC approved supervisor for the Ph.D scholars in the subject of Psychology. She is a regular member of APA. At present she is also working as the Vice President of Pakistan Psychological Association. </span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-10-17 12:13:53','2018-10-17 12:13:53',1),(323,22,20,'1541442748.jpg','Varun Gupta','drvarun1234@gmail.com','919654450789','orthopaedics Department','Editorial board member','India','Dr. Baba saheb ambedkar hospital','05','',1,'2018-11-06 00:02:28','2018-11-06 00:02:28',1),(324,31,20,'1541443522.jpg','George K. Paraskevas ','g_paraskevas@yahoo.gr','6974011290','Department of Anatomy, Faculty of Medicine','Editorial board member','Greece','Aristotle University of Thessaloniki','14','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dr George K. Paraskevas born in Greece and works as Associate Professor of Anatomy at Department of Anatomy, Medical School, Aristotle University of Thessaloniki (AUTH), Thessaloniki, Greece. He received the Medical degree from Medical School, Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, attained the Ph.D. degree in 2000 (degree: excellent) and gained full qualification as specialist in orthopaedic surgery in 2005. In 2005 was appointed as Postdoctoral Lecturer at Department of Anatomy, AUTH and in 2010, G.K.Paraskevas served as Assistant Professor at the Department of Anatomy in Medical School of Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Greece and since 2014 serves as Associate Professor.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><u><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Research and Scientific Fields of Interest:</span></strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"color:black\">Surgical anatomy and embryology of gastrointestinal tract, Congenital anomalies of bones and muscles, Entrapment syndromes of nerves and neuropathies, Variational anatomy of vascular system, Trauma and surgery, History of Anatomy, Anatomical nomenclature, Anthropometric studies</span></span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-06 00:15:21','2018-11-06 00:17:05',1),(325,35,20,'1541444723.png','Yasin Ozdemir','yasin.ozdemir@tarim.gov.tr','','Department of Food Technologies','Editorial board member','Turkey','Ataturk Central Horticultural Research Institute','39','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Dr. Yasin Ozdemir&nbsp;has been the research scientist 2007&minus;present in the Department of Food Technologies, Ataturk Central Horticultural Research Institute. He was also an auditor of &#39;Food Safety and Standards&rsquo; 2004&minus;2007 in the Yalova Agriculture Ministry Office, Turkey. He has 1.st Natinal Olive Oscar Award for his innovative olive technology research project at 2015.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><u><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:#333333\">Research Interest:</span></strong></span></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">His research program involves: Eco-friendly food technology, tble olive technology, new fruit and vegetable selectin works for final step of breeding project, new food technologies, oive oil, food safety and functional foods, probiotic foods</span></span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-06 00:35:22','2018-11-06 00:35:22',1),(326,35,20,'','Rasmia Sayed Sayed Darwesh','darweshssrasmia@gmail.com','01004243215','Horticulture department, Ornamental department','Editorial board member','Egypt','Cairo University','40','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Rasmia Sayed Sayed Darwesh&nbsp;&nbsp; has completed Ph.D at the age of 40 years from Cairo University and postdoctoral studies from Agriculture Research Center. She has published more than 25 papers in reputed journals and serving as an editorial board member of repute. </span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-06 00:39:49','2018-11-06 00:39:49',1),(327,35,20,'1541611344.jpg','Bijan Abadi','abadi@maragheh.ac.ir','9837252319','Department of Biosystem Engineering, Agricultural College','Editorial board member','Iran','University of Maragheh','41','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Bijan Abadi is an assistant Prof. at the University of Maragheh. Iran. He received his PHD in agricultural Extension and education from the University of Shiraz, Iran, 2008-2013. His research interests are agricultural development, agricultural sustainability, the optimal use of agricultural inputs, soft systems in agriculture, and medicinal plants cultivation. After his graduation, he involved in research and teaching. He authored the book &ldquo;Cognition and Thinking of Sustainable Agricultural Extension and rural Development&rdquo;. Moreover, he published articles in the <em>Azarian Journal of Agriculture</em> and <em>Iranian Agricultural Extension and Education Journal</em>, and <em>Rangeland Ecology and Management</em>. He was a chief executive of the research project, aiming at investigating how environmental NGOs play a role in changing farmers&rsquo; water use behavior to revive the ecosystem of the Urmia Lake. So far, he is a chief executive of the research project to examine how to extend the cultivation of medicinal plants in agricultural systems.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-07 22:50:20','2018-11-07 22:52:23',1),(328,35,20,'1541611721.jpg','Ahmed Abdel-Wahab Enab','drahmed_enab@yahoo.com','20 (100) 5355282','Professor of poultry breeding and genetics','Editorial board member','Egypt','Minufiya University','42','',1,'2018-11-07 22:58:41','2018-11-07 22:58:41',1),(329,35,20,'1541611947.jpg',' Zakaria Fouad Fawzy Hassan','zakaria6eg@gmail.com','201000213127','Professor in Agriculture and Biological Division','Editorial board member','Egypt','National Research Centre','43','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Zakaria Fouad Fawzy - Professor - National Research Centre and Assessor &nbsp;in Egyptian Accreditation Council &nbsp;He is the first Egyptian researcher attended of the talented young scientist program in China. He got an opportunity for more than two international projects in Egypt as a principal investigator about Climate Changes Issues in China and Egypt. Dr Zakaria is professor in the Agriculture and Biological Division, National Research centre since 2013. Also, he is Assessor in the Egyptian Accreditation Council. Dr Zakaria is Former President of the Youth Scientific Research Association. He was attended many scholarships and fellowships such as , scholarship &ldquo; PostDoctor &ldquo; in china from 2011 to 2012 and fellowship &ldquo; Talented Young Scientists Program&rdquo; in China from 2014 to 2015. He created about four Memorandum of Understanding &ldquo;MoU&rdquo; and Memorandum of Agreement &ldquo;MoA&rdquo; between National Research Centre and other international scientific organization such as &ndash; Institute of Geographic Sciences and Natural Resources Research- Chinese Academy of Sciences and Beijing Institute of Technology- Ministry of Science and Technology &ndash; China.&nbsp; He is a member in many scientific organizations and acts as reviewer and referee as well as board member in the field of organic agriculture and climate changes issues for different national and international journals and organizations. Also, Dr. Zakaria won many awards and he was attend a huge number of conferences, training and workshops in Egypt and other many countries in worldwide as well as he was published five scientific books and more than 45 scientific research paper. Dr. Zakaria contributed significantly to the expansion of knowledge of organic agriculture and climate changes issues through public lectures on scientific research centers and various Egyptian and Chinese universities, and because he is principal investigator of some international and national projects he contributed significantly in helping to learn organic agriculture and climate changes and using smart climate agriculture as a new trend in the field of agriculture. He work a Progress Patent invention entitled &ldquo;A new natural compound to increase productivity and immunity of horticultural and field crops &quot; - Application No. 2077/2015 - Advanced side - Academy of Scientific Research and Technology - Patent office.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-07 23:02:26','2018-11-07 23:02:26',1),(330,35,20,'1541612184.jpg','Antonio Elia','antonio.elia@unifg.it','0039 0881589237','Dept. Science of Agriculture, Food and Environment','Editorial board member','Italy','University of Foggia','44','',1,'2018-11-07 23:06:24','2018-11-07 23:06:24',1),(331,35,20,'1541612860.jpg','Moustafa Mohamed Sabry Bakry','md.md_sabry@yahoo.com','01112383122','Plant Protection','Editorial board member','Egypt','Plant Protection Research Institute Agricultural Research Center','45','<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Moustafa Mohamed Sabry Bakry,works as a Dr. of Economic Entomology&nbsp;at the Institute of Plant Protection Research&nbsp;and Head of Plant Protection at the Station of Agricultural Research El-Matanaa, Esna district, Luxor governorate, Egypt. Dr. Moustafa got his Ph.D. in Plant Protection Department (Economic Entomology) from Faculty of Agriculture, Sohag, Univ., Egypt 2014. His research interest is ecological studies of pests, biological studies, population density, and its control as well as, the results of these researches can be used to optimize monitoring methods for establishing IPM strategies against these pest. Dr. Moustafa published 32 papers most of them in international journals. Dr. Moustafa is editorial board and reviewer for 15 journals in the economic entomology and pest control. Dr. Moustafa published four scientific books in the field of ecological studies of pests.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-07 23:17:40','2018-11-07 23:20:56',1),(332,35,20,'1541613417.jpg','V. K. Khanna','khannavk@rediff.com','','Senior Professor, Plant Biotechnology , School of Crop Improvement, College of Post Graduate Studies','Editorial board member','India',' Central Agricultural University','46','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. V. K. Khanna graduated from Delhi University and did his M.Sc and PhD from Haryana Agricultural University in Genetics, followed by Post Doctorate, CSIR. He joined as an Assistant Professor at G. B. Pant University of Agriculture &amp; Technology, Pantnagar and worked there for nearly 30 years. He has more than 39 years of experience of teaching and conducting research on Wide-hybridization, Genetics and Biotechnology. He has guided 76 M.Sc and Ph.D theses and published 164 research papers in Indian and Foreign Journals of repute. He has also presented 193 research papers in Conferences/Symposia/Workshops in India and abroad, a few of them being Lead Papers including a Key-note address in an International Conference. He has been the Chairman/Co-chairman in many National and International conferences. He Chaired a session at the 7th International Congress of SABRAO and International Symposium of WSAA at Taipei, Taiwan, Republic of China from Nov. 16-20, 1993. His group reported the mechanism of crossability between wheat and rye for the first time.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He has also published 57 Popular Articles and written 12 Books. He has visited various Universities and Research Stations abroad and presented his research work in conferences in Australia, USA, Germany, UK, Taiwan, Netherlands, Singapore, Russia, Thailand and Philippines. He was a Fellow of Food and Agricultural Organization (FAO) of UN and worked on Molecular Markers and Genetic Transformation at the University of Queensland, in Australia. He is a member of the Editorial Board of Agrotechnology (Omics group), J. of Horticulture (Omics group) and some Indian journals and Reviewer of some Indian and Foreign Journals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">He was a member of the National Review Committee on Genetic Manipulation in the Department of Biotechnology, Government of India. He has also filed a Patent with the National Research Development Corporation, N. Delhi. He has taught 24 P.G. and U.G. courses and is currently teaching &lsquo;Molecular Cell Biology&rsquo;, &lsquo;Pr. of Cytogenetics&rsquo; and &lsquo;Molecular and Chromosomal Manipulations for Crop Breeding&rsquo; to the P.G. students and &lsquo;Principles of Genetics&rsquo; to the undergraduate students He has been the PI of 15 research projects.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. V. K. Khanna is the recipient of many awards including the Best Paper awards in various conferences and the Best Teacher Award at India&rsquo;s first agricultural university i.e. G. B. Pant University of Agriculture &amp; Technology, Pantnagar. He was felicitated with &lsquo;Vijay Rattan Award&rsquo; and Certificate of Excellence for Meritorious Services, Outstanding Performance and Remarkable Role by Dr. Bhisham Narain Singh, former Governor of Tamil Nadu &amp; Assam at a seminar on Economic Growth &amp; National Integration at New Delhi on 25th November 2005, by India International Friendship Society. He was awarded with &lsquo;Bharat Vikas Award&rsquo; and Certificate of Excellence for Excellence in the Chosen Field by Hon&rsquo;ble Smt. Mohsina Kidwai, Member of Parliament (Rajya Sabha) on the occasion of the significant seminar on Economic Growth &amp; National Integration at New Delhi on 31st August 2006, by International Institute of Success Awareness. He got &lsquo;Rajiv Gandhi Excellence Award&rsquo; and Certificate of Excellence for Meritorious Services, Outstanding Performance and Remarkable Role by Hon&rsquo;ble Lt. Gen. (Retd.) T. P. S. Rawat, P. V. S. M., V. S. M., Minister for Tourism, Excise &amp; Sainik Kalyan (Govt. of Uttaranchal) at a seminar on Economic Growth &amp; National Integration at New Delhi on 31st August 2006, by India International Friendship Society. He was given &lsquo;Gem of India Award&rsquo; and Certificate of Excellence for Meritorious Services, Outstanding Performance and Remarkable Role by Shri M. V. Rajasekharan, Hon&rsquo;ble Minister of State for Planning, Govt. of India at a seminar on Global Participation in India&rsquo;s Economic Development at New Delhi on 8th January, 2007 by India International Friendship Society. He has worked as Joint Director Research, In charge Govt. notified Seed Testing Laboratory, In charge Pantnagar Centre of Plant Genetic Resources, Acting Registrar, Acting Director Research, Acting Dean of College of Agri- Business Management, Acting Coordinator (Admissions) at G. B. Pant University of Agriculture &amp; Technology, Pantnagar and In charge Dean at P.G. College, Central Agricultural University (CAU), Barapani, Meghalaya., and Chairman, School of Crop Improvement and he is continuing as Professor, Biotechnology at P.G. College, CAU, Barapani, Meghalaya.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-07 23:26:57','2019-02-13 17:47:50',1),(333,35,20,'1541613914.jpg','Usman Pato','usmanpato@yahoo.com','','Agricultural Technology','Editorial board member','Indonesia','Riau University','46','',1,'2018-11-07 23:35:14','2018-11-07 23:35:14',1),(334,25,20,'1541614400.png','George C. Charalambous','drcharalambous@yahoo.gr','','Head of Emergency Department','Editorial board member','Greece','Frederick University','11','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Coordinator of the Postgraduate Program in &quot;Health Management&quot; at Frederick University Cyprus. Surgeon, Doctor of Medicine from University of Athens and holds two postgraduate degrees in Surgical Anatomy and in Health Care Management. He has several publications and has participated with presentations in a lot of prestigious international conferences both domestically and abroad. Participated in National Committee of the Ministry of Health as a special consultant and is a member of scientific societies such as the Greek Surgical Society, the Society of Emergency Medicine and the Scientific Society of Health Policy and Management. . He has written a Handbook for Emergency Departments entitled &quot;Emergency Response&quot;, as he translated and edited the Greek version of Emergency Nursing Procedures, Jean A. Proehl</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research interest :</span></span></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Surgery, Health Systems and Policy, Emergency Medicine </span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-07 23:43:19','2018-11-07 23:52:05',1),(335,25,20,'1541614823.jpg','Wagih Ghnnam','wghnnam@gmail.com','00966556922516','Ass. Prof.  General Surgery','Editorial board member','Egypt','Mansoura University','12','',1,'2018-11-07 23:50:23','2018-11-07 23:52:22',1),(336,35,20,'1541615237.jpg','Irmak Baran','irmakmor@yahoo.com','','Associate Professor,Clinical Microbiology','Editorial board member','Turkey','Ankara Numune Education and Research Hospital','13','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Irmak Baran was born in Ankara, Turkey. She attended TED Ankara College High School. After that she studied at Gazi Univercity Medical School. After graduating as MD, she trained as a Medical Microbiologist in Ankara Numune Training and Research Hospital. She is currently working as an Associate Professor in the same hospital. She has published research articles in many SCI journals. Her research interests are antimicrobial resistance, MALDI-TOF and molecular bacteriology. She knows English, French and Turkish. She is a proud cat mom and avid choir soprano in her free time.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-07 23:57:17','2018-11-07 23:57:17',1),(337,25,20,'','Rania Refaat','raniarefaat_1977@hotmail.com','','Assistant professor in Radiodiagnosis Department, Faculty of Medicine','Editorial board member','Egypt','Ain Shams University','14','',1,'2018-11-08 00:06:11','2018-11-08 00:06:11',1),(338,25,20,'','Amir Elalouf','Amir.Elalouf@biu.ac.il','972-54-7908004','Lecturer','Editorial board member','Israel','Bar-Ilan University','15','',1,'2018-11-08 00:13:56','2018-11-08 00:14:22',1),(339,25,20,'1541616549.jpg','Bahar Salehi','bahar.salehi007@gmail.com','','Professor','Editorial board member','Iran','Shahid Beheshti University of Medical Sciences','16','<h3><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><em><strong>Research Interest</strong></em></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Microbial Nanotechnology, Microbial Biotechnology, Medical Microbiology, Biomedical Ethics, Medical Ethics.</span></span></h3>\r\n',1,'2018-11-08 00:19:09','2018-11-08 00:22:26',1),(340,25,20,'1541617284.jpg','Sadaf Sheikh','sheikh.sadaf@gmail.com','00923062567638','Resident IV, Emergency Medicine','Editorial board member','Pakistan','Aga Khan University Hospital','16','',1,'2018-11-08 00:31:24','2018-11-08 00:31:24',1),(341,25,20,'','Ajay Sharma','ajaysharmapharma1979@gmail.com','91-9575848894 ','Professor','Editorial board member','India','Amity University Madhya Pradesh','17','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">My area of research interest is drug discovery and development from natural products and traditional medicines. I am engaged in diverse research areas with knowledge of pharmacology, natural product chemistry, biotechnology and pharmacognosy. I have extensively worked and published in the areas of pharmacological evaluation of isolated natural products for antimicrobial, antioxidant, anticancer, anti-inflammatory activity using <em>in vitro</em> and <em>in vivo</em> models and growth inhibitory activity against pathogenic bacteria, phytochemistry, food technology and nutrition, ethnopharmacology, fingerprinting and standardization of marker compounds in medicinal plant products and dietary supplements, optimization of large scale extraction, isolation and characterization of natural products of commercial value, bioactivity guided fractionation. I am also working on <em>in vitro</em> multiplication for endangered plants, bioconversion of secondary metabolites using plant pathogenic bacteria and fungi and their pharmacological screening.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-08 00:40:43','2018-11-08 00:40:43',1),(342,28,20,'1541618577.jpg','Eric Lontchi Yimagou','lontchifrenzy@yahoo.fr','','Post-Doctoral Research Fellow in Endocrinology/Diabetes','Editorial board member','USA','Albert Einstein College of Medicine, Bronx','04','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Dr Lontchi Yimagou, is a Postdoctoral Research Fellow in the Diabetes Research Center at Albert Einstein College of Medicine. His interests are clinical metabolic research of diabetes physiology and glucose clamp methodology. He has been actively involved in projects related to the epidemiology and pathophysiology of diabetes for the past 8 years, both at national and international levels. His current work relates to the potential approach to impact the pathogenesis of hypoglycemia associated autonomic failure that will restore life-sustaining responses to hypoglycemia in patients with type 1 diabetes. He has also evaluated the Changing Diabetes in Children Project in Cameroon. He has traveled to CMC Vellore, India in the past year to oversee our research delineating the pathogenesis of malnutrition diabetes.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">He earned his PhD in Physiology and Pathophysiology from the University of Pierre and Marie Curie (Paris, France). His PhD thesis focused on environmental factors associated with diabetes in Africa, specifically the role of Human herpes virus type 8 infection in ketosis-prone atypical diabetes. He holds an MPH in in Public Health Nutrition from the University of Paris 13 (Paris, France). He is the recipient of a number of fellowships including the American Diabetes Association postdoctoral fellowship (USA, 2018), the Henry Christian and the Eastern Regional Scholar Awards from the American Federation for Medical Research (USA, 2017), the travel grant award from the European Association for the Study of Diabetes, a fellowship grant from l&#39;Institut Servier (Paris, 2015), a fellowship grant from the French Government (Paris, 2014), the and Jean Claude Mbanya Fellowship Award from the African Diabetes Congress (Cameroon, 2014). He has published several original research articles in peer reviewed journals and is currently a member of the editorial board of the Journal of Clinical Research Diabetes and Medicine.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-08 00:53:01','2018-11-08 00:53:01',1),(343,15,20,'','Adel Hamed Abd Elgawwad Elbaih','elbaihzico@yahoo.com','','Department of Emergency Medicine, Faculty of Medicine','Editorial board member','Egypt','Suez Canal University','24','',1,'2018-11-08 01:05:32','2018-11-08 01:05:32',1),(344,20,20,'1541619850.jpg','Muhammad Akram','makram_0451@hotmail.com','92-3452888394','Assistant Professor,Department of Eastern Medicine, Directorate of Medical Sciences, Faculty of Science and Technology','Editorial board member','Pakistan','Government College University Faisalabad','13','',1,'2018-11-08 01:14:10','2018-11-08 01:14:10',1),(345,22,20,'1541850395.jpg','Andrew Furey','lucina.mason@med.mun.ca','','Chief Of Division of Orthopedic Surgery','Editorial board member','Canada','St. John\'s, Newfoundland and Labrador','03','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Andrew Furey is an orthopaedic surgeon, community leader, physician, medical educator and the founder of Team Broken Earth, a national medical aid charity that began in St. John&#39;s, Newfoundland and Labrador. Since founding Team Broken Earth, Andrew has led over 20 missions to Haiti, Bangladesh and Guatemala with his colleagues from Memorial University and Eastern Health. Team Broken Earth continues to grow nationally and internationally. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Team Broken Earth is a true national movement that began right here!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">It now includes teams from 7 Canadian provinces and territories, engaging over hundreds of doctors, nurses and volunteers each year as the organization provides critical aid and medical education to people in need around the world.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Dr. Furey was recently awarded the 2017 Humanitarian of the Year Award, also honoured to accept on behalf of Team Broken Earth, the Meritorious Service Cross from Governor General David Johnson. He is a proud past recipient of the Atlantic Business Magazine Top 50 CEOs Award and is active in the local innovation and business community through his work on the Board of Directors of several private companies. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Andrew is a very proud Newfoundlander, he lives in St. Phillip&#39;s with his wife and three children.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-11-10 17:16:35','2018-11-10 17:16:35',1),(349,35,20,'1541852245.jpg','Omur Baysal','omurbaysal@mu.edu.tr','','Department of Molecular Biology and Genetics','Editorial board member','Turkey','MuglaSitkiKocman University','49','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research Area</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Microbiology, host-pathogen interactions, molecular cell biology, bioinformatic applications in molecular biology and genetic, omics sciences</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><