d 2002 respectively. DNA Technologies, Swansea, England, Gene Manuplation and Genomics, Western Michigan State, USA and Cancer Research, Hawaii Cancer Research Center. Dr. Vural has a number of national/international publications and research as well as lessons for undergraduate and graduate students. She has written international book and book chapters. She is editor and referee in the international journals. The university has received official duties for industrial cooperation, domestic and international consulting, expertise and representation at UNESCO meetings. She has also worked on many scientific projects.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#dc3545\">Research Interest</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Molecular modeling studies on cancer molecular biology and epigenetic mechanisms, genomic and metabolic pathways. Plant, animal, human, microorganism, tissue, blood, hair, forensic medicine as well as organic substances isolated from archaeological remains, archaeometry, biological anthropology. Gene manipulation, identification of gene expressions related to diseases, mutation detection, cell culture studies, apopitosis and cancer developmet, siRNA, miRNA, and the many metabolic and necrotic pathway studies and on living and ancient DNA assays and OMIC technologies.</span></span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-12-21 17:04:39','2018-12-21 17:05:03',1),(364,27,20,'1545392481.jpg','AGM Mostofa','agmmostofa2013@gmail.com','','Department of Pharmaceutical Science','Editorial board member','USA','Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center','00','',1,'2018-12-21 17:11:21','2018-12-21 17:11:44',1),(365,38,20,'1545925612.png','Dr. Jin Seop Bak','jsbwvav7@kaist.ac.kr','+82 1031597789 ','Professor','Executive editor','United Kingdom','United Cultural Convention (UCC)','01','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">JinSeopBak has a college-degree in Yonsei Univ., a MS/PhD in Korea Univ. with top-honors, and LittD/ScD/PhD in IBC (in Cambridge). He was in Faculty of Kyonggi Univ. and KAIST (as Project-Leader). He was appointed to the post of Secretary-General/Professor/Director General (for Asia)/Adviser in IBC. He worked as a researcher/scholar/judge especially in UC Berkeley (conditionally), Seoul National Univ. and MIT (conditionally). In Korea Univ., Prof. Bak played a key role in teaching Physical Chemistry. He is a leading member of many academies and nonprofit/profit organizations (e.g., Mensa). His main area of investigation is Life/Natural/Applied Sciences. He has achieved many publications, 2 patents, 14 grants. He is a reviewer of more than 100 journals, and member of 50 editorial boards. He has been cited especially in Marquis Who&#39;s Who and IBC.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Research interests:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">I believe that my experiences make me both the ideal researcher and global leader for performing advanced highthroughput technological studies.Until now, I generally explored almost every possible academic endeavor, including Biological Sciences, Food Sciences, Natural Sciences, and Applied Sciences</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-12-27 21:16:51','2018-12-27 21:22:33',1),(366,38,20,'1545925940.jpg','Dr. Jesus Simal-Gandara','jsimal@uvigo.es','','Full professor in nutrition and food science ','Executive editor','Spain','University of Vigo','02','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Visiting researcher </strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Laboratoire de Chimie Analytique II (Prof. Mahuzier &amp; Dr. Becue), Facult&eacute; des Sciences Pharmaceutiques et Biologiques, Universit&eacute; de Paris-S