 on food functionality&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-12-27 21:22:20','2018-12-27 21:43:29',1),(367,38,20,'1545976271.jpg','Weiguang Wang','weiguang.wang@manchester.ac.uk','+44 (0) 775 109 5757','Research Assistant in the Manufacturing Group','Executive editor','United Kingdom','The University of Manchester','03','<p style=\"margin-left:0.25in; margin-right:0.25in\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Weiguang Wang is a PhD graduate from the School of Mechanical, Aerospace and Civil Engineering, The University of Manchester, UK; Research Assistant in the Manufacturing Group and its Medical Engineering Research Centre, School of Mechanical, Aerospace and Civil Engineering, The University of Manchester, UK; Teaching assistant in Additive Manufacturing &amp; 3D Product Modelling, and Metrology, Robotics &amp; Bioengineering for the Mechanical Engineering Program and Master Programs in Advanced Manufacturing Technology &amp; Systems Management, and Mechanical Engineering Design.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0.25in; margin-right:0.25in\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">His research focuses on the design, fabrication and evaluation of electro-active scaffolds for tissue engineering, which requires an extensive knowledge on additive manufacturing, biomaterials and regenerative medicine. His PhD project, fully funded by the School of Mechanical Aerospace and Civil Engineering and the Marwick Bequest for Postgraduate Research in Engineering, The University of Manchester, UK, focused on the use of polycaprolactone scaffolds reinforced with graphene and carbon nanotubes to modulate cell proliferation and differentiation. As part of this research project, scaffolds with different architectures and material compositions were assessed from morphological, mechanical, and biological (<em>in vivo</em> and <em>in vitro</em>) points of view, showing that they are suitable candidates to be used for bone regeneration.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0.25in; margin-right:0.25in\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Main Research Interests:</span> </strong>3D Printing/Bioprinting; Biomaterials; Tissue Engineering;<strong> </strong>Regenerative Medicine.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0.25in; margin-right:0.25in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,'2018-12-28 11:21:10','2018-12-28 11:21:10',1),(368,38,20,'1545976761.jpg','Rusu  Teodor','rusuteodor23@yahoo.com','0040724719774','Director, Office of Soil Survey and Agrochemical Cluj','Executive editor','Europe','University of Agricultural Sciences and Veterinary Medicine Cluj-Napoca','04','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Prof. dr. Rusu Teodor from University of Agricultural Sciences and Veterinary Medicine Cluj-Napoca, Romania, teach Agrotechnics, Experimental Techniques and Rural Development. Director of the research center for Sustainable Agricultural Systems and Minimum Tillage Technologies (since 2011), has worked as a soil pedologist for the 3 years, and agrotechnics for the last 20 years, specializing in soil monitoring, soil tillage, soil quality, minimum tillage, no-tillage, sustainable agricultural technologies and climatic changes. PhD Supervisor on Agrotechnics (since 2009). Deputy Director of the Department of Technical and Soil Sciences (2009-present). Director, Office of Soil Survey and Agrochemical Cluj (2014-present). He was Vice-Dean of the Faculty of Agriculture (2008-2012), Master Program responsible Rural Development (2010-present) and judicial-technical expert in Agriculture specialization. Professional experience - through the publication of 25 books, courses and guidance published in national and international publishers; 315 scientific papers (from which 47 ISI) and consultancy; organizing symposia: soil compaction - processes and consequences (2007); soil tillage systems (ed. 5: 2008; ed. 6: 2011; ed. 7: 2013; ed. 8: 2015); ESSC Conference 2016. Hirsch factor: Web of Science 7; Scopus 8; Google Scholar 12; Publons 8.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Research Interest:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Agrotechnics, herbology and soil management; soil sciences &ndash; pedologic studies and land evaluation, pedoameliorations and soil erosion control studies; technique experimentally and analysis of variance; soil conservation systems for a sustainable agriculture, anti-erosion systems, minimum soil tillage, no-tillage, carbon sequestration; integrated control of weeds and correct use of herbicides; weed biology and ecology, weed assessment; crop rotation and differentiated agrotechnics; rural development and climatic changes.</span></p>\r\n',1,'2018-12-28 11:29:20','2018-12-28 11:29:20',1),(369,38,20,'1545976949.jpg','Idress Hamad Attitalla Saleh','idressattitalla2004@yahoo.com','690421-5198','Professor','Editorial board member','Libya','University of Omar Al-Mukhtar','05','',1,'2018-12-28 11:32:28','2018-12-28 11:32:28',1),(370,38,20,'1545977204.jpg','Waleed Fouad Abobatta','wabobatta@yahoo.com','0020235720617','Director','Executive editor','Egypt','Horticulture Research Institute  Agriculture Research Center','06','<p style=\"margin-left:13.5pt; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Abobatta is a Dr at Agriculture Research Center, he&rsquo;s a member of Scientific Committee for Greenhouses Plantation, and he is a member of Scientific Team for National Campaign for Navel Orange improvement, Abobatta is a supervisor of M. Sc. And Ph.D. thesis in different branches of agricultural science.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:13.5pt; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Abobatta published more than 