,Times,serif\">Psoriasis</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Diabetic foot</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:#00b050\">Current Updates in Dermatological Problems</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Journal Outline</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Current Updates in Dermatological Problems (CUDP) </strong>is an international, peer-reviewed, open access electronic journal that emphasizes on the latest clinical and experimental research in all aspects of skin disease and cosmetic interventions from molecular studies to clinical investigations. The journal expands it horizon with updates of research based on a process of bilateral feedback between the clinic and the laboratory, in which incompletely understood clinical phenomena are examined in the laboratory and the knowledge thus acquired is directly reapplied in the clinic.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Scope</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">CUDP welcomes articles from across the globe but specially encourages articles on pure clinical dermatology, information relating to skin, its ailments and different modes of therapeutics. As scientific and scholarly journal it invites dermatologists, venereologists and leprologists etc. to showcase writing, experiences and work in this journal that will exhibit great promise in terms of readability, teaching, learning and sharing dermatological problems and its treatment at an international level.</span></p>\r\n','<p>Coming Soon</p>',1,'2018-07-01 13:46:00','2018-07-19 23:35:05',1),(25,20,'1530433254.jpg','Emergency Medicine and Trauma Care Journal','Medicine and Trauma Care','Emergency Medicine and Trauma Care Journal','Emergency-Medicine-and-Trauma-Care-Journal','Emergency-Medicine-and-Trauma-Care-Journal','Emergency-Medicine-and-Trauma-Care-Journal','Emergency-Medicine-and-Trauma-Care-Journal','<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Coverage Topics</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Emergency Medical Services</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Intensive Care Units</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Acute Illness and Injury&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Trauma</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Sepsis</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Burn</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Acute Coronary Syndrome</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Poisoning</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Stroke</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Critical-care Medicine</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Medical Toxicology</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Wilderness Medicine</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Pediatric Emergency Medicine</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Disaster Medicine</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Tactical Medicine</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Ultrasound and Pain Emergency Medicine</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Pre-Hospital Emergency Medicine</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">International emergency medicine</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:#00b050\">Emergency Medicine and Trauma Care Journal</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Journal Outline</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Emergency Medicine and Trauma Care Journal</strong> (EMTCJ) is an electronic online scholarly and practical applicability of emergency medicine and trauma care approach based international journal focussed with key information for both the academic and practicing emergency physician and medicos. The journal acts as unique point of knowledge for increase the ability to understand, recognize and treat emergency conditions including hospital emergency medical services, pediatric emergency medicine, injury and disease prevention, health policy and ethics, disaster management, toxicology, and related topics.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Scope</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><strong>Emergency Medicine and Trauma Care Journal</strong> (EMTCJ) is an open access, peer-reviewed journal which covers a variety of topics related to all aspects of emergency medicine, trauma care. We publish articles which are relevant to those working in both hospital and pre-hospital environments.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">The journal aims to encourage the dissemination of local and international knowledge in an area that is one of the most challenging areas of medicine. It also encourages the inclusion of trauma and intensive care as the latest sub-specialities in the field of emergency medicine.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">The journal publishes a roughly equal mix of original research articles and case reports. It also publishes trauma, disaster preparedness, and commentaries on resuscitation, evidence-based reviews, minor injuries, clinical operations, original research, paediatric emergencies, acute medical, decision making reviews, evidence-based reviews, editorials, correspondence, and replications on clinical practice.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">This journal provides enough information to reduce the suffering from the cases of trauma and emergency injuries for communication amongst health professionals with academic, clinical and research interests in emergency practice mainly focuses on nurses, ambulance staff, paramedics and doctors.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\">Trauma causes individual patterns of injury and involves shock, fractures, soft tissue and organ injuries. Treatment therefore requires the joint effort of emergency medicine, orthopaedic and trauma surgery, critical care medicine and rehabilitation. Both scientific progress and the in-depth experimental and clinical research within individual disciplines contribute to the ongoing continuous improvement of trauma care.</span></p>\r\n','<p>Coming Soon</p>',1,'2018-07-01 13:50:53','2018-07-23 23:27:17',1),(26,20,'1530433517.jpg','Insights of Cardiology Open Access','Cardiology','Insights of Cardiology Open Access','Insights-of-Cardiology-Open-Access','Insights-of-Cardiology-Open-Access','Insights-of-Cardiology-Open-Access','Insights-of-Cardiology-Open-Access','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif\"><str